title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Use a large skillet or Dutch oven.
Saute onion and pepper in margarine until pepper is soft (not brown).
Add pimentos, milk and broth; heat.
Add soup, salt and garlic; bring to a boil.
Add chicken and heat thoroughly.
Stir in spaghetti (drained and washed).
Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Add grated cheese and bake until cheese has melted.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine. Place in bowl. Add flour, salt and pepper; mix well. Gradually add beef bouillon. Fry bread cubes in margarine. Combine with onion mixture. Place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with 1/2 cup shredded Swiss cheese and Parmesan. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted, 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown together ground beef or ground chicken and onion.
Heat together chicken soup, water and sour cream.
Dip corn tortillas in hot oil to soften.
Place meat mixture into tortillas and roll up.
Place in sprayed casserole, seam side down.
Pour soup mixture over enchiladas.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake until bubbly and heated through.
Diced green chilies can be added to soup mix.
Sprinkle green onion on top.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Cover bottom of ungreased 9 x 15-inch pan with 1 1/2 cups crumbs.
Melt margarine and chocolate together (microwave).
With electric mixer beat egg yolks; add powdered sugar, chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Beat egg whites and fold into chocolate mixture; add nuts.
Spread over crumbs, then spread softened ice cream.
Freeze.

title: salsa
directions: Use equal amounts of each green peppers, banana peppers and onions.
Use double amount of tomatoes.
Chop up everything.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together (except pecans) with mixer until lemon colored.
Place pecans in bottom of an unbaked pie shell.
Pour lemon colored mixture over the pecans and bake for about 40 minutes at 350°.
Yields 9-inch pie.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Let first 6 ingredients come to a hard boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Beat until mixed.
Pour into buttered dish when it begins to thicken.
Let it cool.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump crushed pineapple in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon on contents of cherry pie filling.
Next "dump" on a large box of white or yellow cake mix.
Cut up butter or margarine on top of this.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: white lightning texas chili
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place in large Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans.
Soak 8 hours, drain and return to Dutch oven.
Add 3 cans chicken broth and next 7 ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 2 hours or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining can of broth, chicken and next 3 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Top servings with cheese, salsa and sour cream. Serve with warm tortillas.
Yield:
12 cups.

title: viva la chicken
directions: Wrap whole chicken breasts in foil; bake at 400° for 1 hour. When cool, bone, skin and cut in pieces.
Cut tortillas in 1-inch strips.
Mix soups, milk, onion and salsa.
Grease large 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put 2 tablespoons broth in bottom of pan. Alternate layers of tortillas, chicken and soup mixture.
Top with cheese; cover and refrigerate 24 hours to allow flavors to blend. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Soften tortillas in hot oil for 15 seconds on both sides. Drain on paper towels.
Place 2 tablespoons of cheese and 1 teaspoon of onion in each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam side down in large, flat baking dish.
Melt margarine; blend in flour and seasoned salt.
Add broth; stir and cook until thick and bubbly.
Stir in sour cream and peppers.
Cook until heated, but do not boil.
Pour over tortillas and bake 20 minutes at 425°. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: crock-pot lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger. Cook noodles and drain. Add butter. Stir to melt. Layer in crock-pot, starting with sauce, then meat. Follow with noodles and cheese. Cook on low for 4 hours.

title: cucumber-dill pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large salad bowl.
Chill well.

title: banana-split brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix brownie mix as directed on package. Pour mix on 14-inch round pizza pan or baking stone.
(If using baking stone, you will need parchment paper.)
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix and pack into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add melted oleo; mix well and add eggs.
Add milk; blend well.
Add vanilla and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and then at 300° for 10 to 18 additional minutes.
Pie should not "wiggle" in the center and take care to cover crust with foil if edges brown too quickly. Top with Cool Whip.

title: bailey baked beans
directions: Brown the onion and ground beef.
Mix all the ingredients and bake for 1/2 hour.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Top with cheese.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix corn (do not drain) and creamed corn, sour cream, melted butter and Jiffy corn bread mix; mix well.
Pour into baking dish. Bake at 325° to 350° for 60 minutes.

title: ham delights
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Split the rolls with long knife. inside of rolls after splitting them.
Lay slices of ham (you can have ham shredded at deli) on bread.
Add slices of cheese on top of ham.
Return top part of separated roll to bottom part.
Use the same foil pans that rolls were bought in.
Wrap in foil and bake approximately 20 minutes.
These freeze well; unthaw and heat the same way.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Stir-fry zucchini, onion and Italian seasoning in hot oil for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook down, 5 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle on more seasonings, salt and pepper.
Transfer vegetables to a casserole dish; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly and brown.

title: no bake cookies improved
directions: Mix together the sugar, milk and cocoa.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add margarine and peanut butter; stir until melted.
Add oatmeal and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: chris' funky four cheese lasagna
directions: Bring large pot of water to a boil, lightly salted.
Cook noodles al dente.
Make sure they are separated in water.
Mix Ricotta, Parmesan, egg, salt and pepper.
Lightly oil a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and spread 1/2 cup tomato sauce on bottom.
Lay 3 noodles lengthwise.
Spread 1/3 Ricotta mixture on top first layer. Top with 1/3 Mozzarella and 1/3 of the Provolone.
Spread another 1/3 of Ricotta on top and another layer of Mozzarella and Provolone.
Spread remaining Ricotta on noodles and sauce over the cheese.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 minutes until bubbly. Allow lasagna to cool and set before cutting.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place cooked chicken in pieces in pan.
Mix soups, chicken, broth and sour cream.
Pour on top of chicken.
Fix Stove Top stuffing as directed on box; instead of using water, use chicken broth.
Put on top of chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: green bean and shiitake mushroom sauté
directions: Fill a large stockpot 2/3 full with lightly salted water; bring to boil.
Meanwhile in skillet over medium-high heat, cook mushrooms and onion in hot oil for 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Add beans to boiling water and cook 5 to 7 minutes until crisp-tender; drain.
Add garlic and thyme to mushrooms and cook, stirring for 1 minute.
Stir in broth, vinegar, sugar and pepper and bring to boil; continue to stir.
Pour mixture over drained green beans.
Toss to coat beans and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and water.
Cook until clear; add jello, lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir until dissolved.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt margarine.
Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add margarine and oil. Stir until smooth.
Add eggs, beat until well mixed.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Stir well. Refrigerate.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Cook bell pepper, onion, garlic clove, tomato paste and tomatoes until done and add macaroni.

title: taco soup
directions: Simmer on low for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with plain or jalapeno cornbread.

title: chicken silver(a tasty newspaper recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Cut four sheets of foil, each 1 foot square.
Stir together the ginger, garlic, mango chutney, vinegar, butter and red pepper flakes.
Divide the leeks equally, placing 1 portion in the center of each piece of foil.
Season both sides of chicken with salt and pepper to taste; place on top of leeks. Spread 1/4 of the chutney mixture on each chicken breast.
Sprinkle with the slivered peppers and snow peas; season with salt and pepper.

title: potato salad
directions: After boiled potatoes have been cooled, discard skin and slice into a bowl.
Mix mayonnaise and eggs in a separate bowl.
Add celery, onion, salt and pepper.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix milk, lemons and eggs thoroughly.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Beat the egg white for meringue.
Bake at 325°.
Place in refrigerator and let cool.

title: sweet minglers
directions: In a large microsafe bowl, melt chocolate at High for 1 minute; stir and heat an additional 30 seconds at High or until melted.
Stir in peanut butter and peanuts.
Pour mixture over Crispix cereal.
Place confectioners sugar in 2-gallon storage bag.
Add coated cereal to sugar and close bag tightly.
Toss until cereal is coated with sugar.
Store in an airtight container in refrigerator.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Boil shrimp in shrimp boil, then peel and cut shrimp in small pieces.
Add all ingredients together and chill.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together well.
Make ahead of time.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Brown meat lightly in electric skillet at 325°.
Sprinkle half of the dry spaghetti sauce mix over the meat.
Layer 1 layer of noodles over meat, layer cottage cheese over the noodles, then put another layer of noodles over the cottage cheese.
Sprinkle remaining spaghetti sauce, parsley flakes, salt and 1 cup shredded cheese over the mixture.
Add tomatoes and water.
Cover tightly and set skillet temperature at 225°.
Cook and check in 30 to 35 minutes or until noodles are done.
Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella cheese over top.
Cover, turn off skillet and let stand for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: light pineapple pie
directions: In large bowl, combine pudding mix, and milk according to directions. Fold in pineapple chunks and whipped topping. Blend thoroughly. Pour into pie crusts. Refrigerate until set.

title: raspberry bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except raspberries.
Mix well.
Fold in raspberries.
Grease pans and bake at 350 degrees for 35 - 40 minutes.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together. Spread beans in 9 x 13 dish, top with guacamole. Top with sour cream mix, then shredded cheese, then tomatoes, & green onions. Use with chips.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown and chop ground beef; put in crock-pot and cut cheese in chunks and add to beef.
Add sauce and tomato and pepper.
Turn crock-pot on low to melt.
Serve warm with chips.

title: applesauce
directions: Place in microwave-safe dish for 5 minutes.
Mash, return for another 3 to 5 minutes.
Unbelievably good!

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Slice beef across the grain into very thin slices.
(Tip: To make slicing easier, freeze beef for 1 hour.)
Cook beef over medium heat in hot oil in a heavy skillet with garlic until beef is brown.
Add onion and cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce; bring to a boil and add broccoli. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer until veggies are tender. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: prune nut cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients
and
wet
ingredients
separately. Add the dry ingredients to the wet ones and mix well.
Bake at 350° for one hour in a
greased
and
floured
tube pan.
This cake also makes well as a loaf, makes 2 loaves.

title: petite pecan pies
directions: Cream by hand the first 4 ingredients, adding the flour a little at a time.
Divide dough in 24 small balls the size of walnuts.
Press in small cupcake pans to make the shells.

title: low-fat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon in large bowl.
Mix cereal, milk and sugar in another bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in Egg Beater and applesauce. Add to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.)

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Combine all ingredients in large baking dish.
Crush small bag potato chips on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy squash custard
directions: Heat oil and butter in large skillet.
Add squash, onions and garlic; saute until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Combine beaten eggs, cheese, dill, salt and pepper.
Transfer vegetables to buttered 8-inch skillet baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells; drain.
Cool in a single layer on wax paper. Combine all other ingredients.
Fill each shell with 2 tablespoons cheese mixture.
Spread bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish with thin layer of sauce.
Place shells in pan; cover with sauce and remaining Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 36 shells.

title: josephine's cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Shape into balls.
Roll in sugar and flatten slightly.
Bake at 350°.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onions, celery and carrots in chicken broth until tender.
Add cornstarch and thicken to the consistency of gravy.
Remove from stove and stir in remaining ingredients and serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: frozen pops
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O gelatin, instant soft drink mix and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Pour into ice cube trays, small paper cups or frozen pop molds.
Insert wooden sticks or paper spoons diagonally in each ice cube section or at an angle in molds or cups for handles.
Freeze until firm, 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 20 to 24 pops.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Combine soda, shortening, salt and vanilla.
Add sugar gradually.
Cream well.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Drop from spoon and press down with a glass with a wet cloth on it.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked orange roughy with cheese and mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2 quart baking dish with margarine.
Evenly scatter the scallions and mushrooms over the bottom of the baking dish.

Place the fish fillets on top in a single layer (overlap or tuck under the thin ends of the fillets). Mix the wine and lemon juice together and pour over the fish. Sprinkle with the marjoram and black pepper.
Evenly distribute the cheese strips over the fillets.
Crumble a large piece of waxed paper and wet it.
Shake off excess water and place the paper loosely across fish.
Bake for 7 minutes.
Remove from oven, take off waxed paper.
Sprinkle fish with bread crumbs.
Bake for another 7 to 9 minutes.
Stick fish under broiler just long enough to brown, about 1 minute.

title: marshmallow nut fudge
directions: Place brown sugar, milk and butter in pan and cook until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from fire; add vanilla and beat a few minutes until it begins to thicken. Add marshmallow and nuts, beat a few minutes and pour in buttered dish.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: bavarian cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vinegar, flour, salt and syrup.
Cook until thick.
Let cool.
Whip the whipping cream.
Combine all ingredients.

title: favorite baked beans
directions: Empty 1 can of beans into a greased bean pot (or casserole). Combine sugar and mustard and sprinkle half of the mixture over beans.
Top with remaining beans, rest of sugar mixture, the bacon and top with the catsup.
Bake, uncovered, 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Grease large casserole dish with butter.
Cut meat into serving pieces and arrange in pan slightly overlapping.
Sprinkle soup mix over meat.
Add mushrooms, green pepper and tomatoes. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 365° for 2 hours.

title: spanish rice and beef
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add water, tomatoes and seasonings. Bring to a boil and boil about 2 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork. Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cheese to soften.
Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into ball and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.
Great for parties.

title: delicious chocolate sheet cake
directions: Add 1 box sifted powdered sugar and 1 cup pecans.
Spread on hot cake immediately upon removing from oven.

title: easy vegetables
directions: Microwave vegetables and drain.
Crush crackers and stir them into cooked vegetables in a large baking dish.
Cut Velveeta into cubes and combine with vegetables.
Melt margarine and drizzle over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: our perfect apple pie
directions: In large bowl, combine first four ingredients.
Using a pastry blender or two knives, cut in shortening until evenly crumbly.

title: eggplant-cheese casserole
directions: Peel the eggplant; cut in 1-inch cubes.
Drop into rapidly boiling water.
Cook 8 minutes or until tender on outer edges. Remove from heat and drain immediately.
Mash with potato masher and set aside while you prepare rest of dish.
Melt butter in skillet and saute the onions until clear and glazed.
Do not overcook; set aside.
Beat eggs until light and frothy; add salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Then add sauteed onions, butter and all. Then stir in the mashed eggplant.
Mix all well.
Place in suitable buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle the bread crumbs or cornflakes over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6. Serve piping hot.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all vegetables.
Mix sugar, salt, oil, vinegar, water and paprika.
Pour over vegetables.
Best if sets overnight.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Place flour in bowl.
Add buttermilk, oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla in their order.
Bake at 350° until done.
When cake is done, slice into 2-inch squares while still in pan.
Pour icing on while hot.
Serves 20.

title: quick ambrosia
directions: Thaw frozen whipped topping. In a bowl, combine undrained pineapple with dry pudding mix.
Stir in oranges and coconut. Fold into the frozen whipped topping.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: salisbury steak and gravy
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, egg and 1/3 can mushroom soup together.
Shape into patties and place in skillet.
Fry on medium heat until well done.
Drain off grease and top with remaining mushroom soup, milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer 10 minutes and serve.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until very smooth.
Add chopped nuts.

title: cherry bread
directions: Mix all gently.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a regular loaf pan or 45 minutes in two medium loaf pans.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break cake in small pieces.
Put half in punch bowl.
Cover with half the pineapple, then half cherry pie filling, then half the prepared pudding and half Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.

title: spinach dip with feta cheese(bulgaria)
directions: Heat 1 Tbsp. of the olive in a skillet over medium heat, add spinach, toss until wilted but still bright green, takes about 3 minutes. Transfer to colander and press out excess liquid. Chop spinach coarsely on a cutting board. Combine 4 Tbsp. olive oil, feta cheese, sour cream, garlic and lemon peel in a food processor, blend until smooth. Transfer to bowl and mix in spinach. Add salt and pepper if desired. Cover and chill 2-3 hours. Serves well with breadsticks and fresh vegetables.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and oleo.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spoon into baking dish and refrigerate until firm.
Dissolve Jell-O in water and strawberries.
Pour Jell-O mixture into baking dish and let congeal before serving.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except salad oil in a blender.
Mix well and add salad oil slowly.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add vanilla, eggs and fruit cocktail.
Mix well.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 325° for about 35 minutes.
Boil sugar, margarine and milk about 1 minute or until it starts to thicken.
(Optional:
Add 1/2 cup coconut or nuts.) Poke cake full holes with fork.
Pour icing over cake while hot. Enjoy!

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add taco seasoning mix. In microwave or in saucepan on stove, combine cheese, soup, milk and green chilies.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Warm tortillas in microwave until soft, about 45 seconds to 1 minute.
Place desired amount of meat mixture in tortillas and roll.
Place in baking dish and pour cheese sauce over tortillas.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400° or until bubbly.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello and marshmallows in hot water.
Refrigerate until thick, about 30 minutes.
Add cream cheese; beat.
Add vinegar, pineapple and nuts.
Refrigerate.
Can use 1 lemon and 1 lime jello.

title: ice cream sundae  pie
directions: In a medium bowl, stir slightly softened ice cream.
Spoon ice cream into pie crust and freeze until hard.

title: sensibly delicious double chocolate chip brownies
directions: Melt 1 cup chocolate chips, sugar, applesauce and margarine in large saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add egg whites; stir well.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in remaining chocolate chips and nuts. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 20 minutes, just until set.

title: best banana cake
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix together and add eggs, one at a time. Add to mixture bananas, buttermilk and pecans.
To a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan, add mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tim's black bean chili
directions: Bring beans and 6 cups of water to a boil in a 5 to 6 quart pot.
Cover.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine first four ingredients using enough milk to work smooth.
Add pecans and frost cooled cake.

title: fried green tomatoes(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Combine egg and buttermilk; set aside.
Combine 1/4 cup all-purpose flour, cornmeal, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper in a shallow bowl or pan.
Dredge tomato slices in remaining 1/4 cup flour; dip in egg mixture and dredge in cornmeal mixture.

title: potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Mix potatoes, cream cheese, sour cream, butter, salt and pepper to taste in large bowl.
Put in glass baking dish and grate Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: country-style steak
directions: Brown round steak on both sides.
While meat is browning, warm soup, water (or milk) and onion soup in small saucepan, then add to meat.
Cook in frying pan.
Keep covered.
Cook over low heat about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: tuna salad casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Stir in 1 cup Corn Chex.
Spoon into shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle cheese over salad.
Crush remaining Chex to 3/4 cup. Combine with melted butter.
Sprinkle over cheese and return to oven.
Bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: no bake fudge brownies
directions: Melt over hot (not boiling) water, the chocolate morsels stirring until smooth. Add sweetened milk, crumbs and 1 1/2 cups nuts. Stir until well blended. Press into foil-lined 8-inch square pan. Press remaining 1/2 cup nuts into top of brownie. Let stand at room temperature until firm. Cut into 2 inch squares. Makes 16 (2-inch) brownies.

title: spinach and feta quiche
directions: Prepare and bake pastry shell.
With your hands, squeeze as much moisture from spinach as possible; set spinach aside.
In a blender or food processor, whirl Feta cheese, cottage cheese, green onions,
oil, basil, pepper, garlic salt and fresh garlic until smooth.
Add eggs and milk; blend well.
Pour into a bowl and stir in spinach.
Pour into baked pastry shell and bake in a 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar, syrup, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Pour into pie shells; top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans for about 10 minutes and drain.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl, except French fried onion rings. Pour into 2-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top casserole with onions and bake another 10 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix coconut, pecans and 3/4 stick of butter.
Put these into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
At this point, mix German chocolate cake mix per instructions and pour over the mixture in the pan. Mix 1/2 stick butter and cream cheese until soft.
Add powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mix and bake at 375° until done.

title: beef stew
directions: In a large Dutch oven, add vegetable oil, flour and roast; brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat. Cover, simmer on low for 30
minutes, until vegetables are tender. Serves 6.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix the ingredients, one after the other, as listed.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until browned.
Serve hot.
Serves approximately 10.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: In saucepan, simmer milk.
Mix dry ingredients and stir into the hot milk.
Stir mixture until it thickens.
Add egg yolks, slowly, and butter.
Cook slowly, stirring continuously, until thick.
Add vanilla just before pouring into molds or bowls to cool.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Stuff mushroom caps with cream cheese; top with a piece of sausage.
Bake at 350° until sausage is cooked.

title: mike's baked apples
directions: Core and peel apples.
Garnish with butter, raisins, nuts or honey.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well; let come to a rolling boil, then simmer 1 1/2 hours until thick and creamy.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with cooking spray.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat flour, butter, sugar and salt until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Press firmly into prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 23 minutes, or until golden brown.
Top with filling.

title: blackberry-rhubarb jam
directions: Wash fruit; combine with sugar in large heavy saucepan, mixing thoroughly.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Seal while hot in sterilized jars.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put soup mix in a large bowl; add milk and mix well.
Add meat, mixing all ingredients thoroughly.
Form into 1 large or 3 small loaves.
Do not add salt.
Place strips of bacon on top
and bake at 350° for 1 hour for small loaves and 1 1/2 hours for large loaf.
Serves 8.

title: fried rice
directions: Make sure you have one inch of oil in your wok.
Turn on high and brown garlic.
Add chicken and cook until almost done.
Add onion, pepper and salt, and carrots.
Cook until tender and add soy sauce (to taste) and rice.
Brown and serve!

title: zucchini coconut bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Place in 2 large greased pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until center is done.

title: country coconut pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Beat in eggs and flour. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Mixture will look curdled. Bake in 450° oven 10 minutes; reduce heat to 300° and bake about 30 minutes more or until firm. Serve warm or cold.

title: canned green tomatoes
directions: Clean and slice green tomatoes.
Pack in jars.
Put 1 teaspoon salt in each jar.
Dissolve 1/2 teaspoon alum in a gallon of water.
(One teaspoon alum to 2 gallons of water usually will be enough for 7 quarts of tomatoes.)
Process in hot water for 25 minutes.
Remove immediately.

title: coffee and baileys
directions: Put rack in center of oven and heat to 350°.
Generously grease cookie sheets and set aside.
In medium bowl cream butter and sugar about 3 minutes.
Add coffee and Bailey's; mix well. Add flour and baking soda and mix well.
Turn dough out onto board; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Roll out to 1/16 inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Egg wash cut cookies. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake about 7 minutes.
Cool. Makes 6 dozen.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Add 2 to 3 drops yellow food coloring to broth.
Bring broth to boil. Blend cornstarch and water; add to broth.
When thick, stirring rapidly, add well beaten egg (pour in a thin stream) to broth.
Remove from heat immediately.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix. Roll into balls. Chill for 1 hour.

title: foolproof chocolate cake
directions: Sift the cake flour, cocoa, sugar and salt together 3 times; put into a big mixing bowl.
Add the eggs, sour milk with soda and salad oil.
Mix, then add the vanilla and hot water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft.
Add sugar and peanut butter and then fold in milk and Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust and place in freezer until firm.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in water until tender.
Mix flour, sugar and butter; add to raisins.
Cook until thick.
Add grated lemon rind and juice of 1 lemon.
Pour into uncooked pie crust.
Top with crust.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 35 minutes.

title: date nut chewies
directions: To toast pecans, bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for about 7 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg well.
Beat in sugar, then beat in milk, vanilla and nutmeg to taste.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Combine eggs, milk and salad oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until flour is moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Bake on hot griddle.
Gently sprinkle a few of these choice berries atop the pancake before turning.
Be sure the butter and syrup are hot. Makes about 12 dollar-sized or eight 4-inch pancakes.

title: aunt frieda's pound cake
directions: Cream the butter with the sugar. Add extract.
Beat egg yolks. Add to mixture.
Mix well.
Sift flour before measuring.
Sift dry ingredients. Add to first mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour. Add stiffly beaten egg whites, folding in.
Grease and lightly flour two 8-inch layer pans or 1 large loaf pan. Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour for layers; 1 hour for loaf.

title: oatmeal crunchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Measure flour, soda, salt and mace into a sifter.
Cream shortening with brown sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and milk.
Sift in flour mixture, blending well to make a thick batter.
Fold in oats and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls about 3-inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 minutes or until lightly golden.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool completely on wire racks.

title: hot mexican dish
directions: Crumble and brown ground beef.
Drain excess fat.
Add 1 package dry taco seasoning and cream of mushroom soup.
Stir thoroughly until mixed good then pour in casserole dish.
Top with thin slices of cheese.
Heat in 400° oven until cheese melts. Serve with tortilla chips and salad.

title: rhubarb punch
directions: Combine rhubarb, 7 cups of water and cinnamon sticks and cook to mush and strain.
Add the lemon juice, pineapple juice, water and sugar.
Serves 50.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well. Refrigerate.
Use melon baller to make even size balls.
Melt chocolate chips and Parawax over hot water. Dip balls into chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper. Refrigerate or freeze.

title: venison barbecue
directions: Place meat in crock pot with onion and cook until the meat falls away from the bone. Remove all fat, bone and gristle. Pour sauce over meat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: tea cakes
directions: Stir together the flour, soda and salt.
Add the butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla. Add egg and stir until fluffy. Stir in dry ingredients. Blend in buttermilk.
Drop by tablespoons on ungreased baking sheet.
Press flat with flat bottomed glass dipped in sugar.
Space 1 1/2-inches apart. Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Have all ingredients at room temperature.
This cookie does not get hard.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Arrange graham crackers on broiler pan.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over them.
Boil butter and sugar about 2 minutes and pour over graham crackers and pecans.
Place under broiler for 3 minutes.

title: strawberry bars
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; mix in oatmeal.
Cut in butter until the mixture forms coarse crumbs. Beat egg and milk.
Gradually add egg mixture to flour mixture; mix well.
Spread half of the dough in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Spread with jam.
Drop remaining dough by spoonfuls evenly over jam.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into bars about 1 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all
ingredients
into blender to No. 6 or high and blend (about 2 minutes).	Pour into a greased 9-inch glass pie dish. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry icy(kids)
directions: Blend and freeze.
To serve, put in microwave to defrost for approximately 2 minutes.

title: potato puff casserole
directions: Blend softened cream cheese into hot potatoes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 1-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: banana milk drink
directions: Place everything in blender and blend well.
Refreshing and nourishing for teenagers.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, lite sour cream, sugar and lemon juice in a small bowl.
Combine apples, grapes and celery in a large bowl. When you have the ingredients in the small bowl mixed well, pour over ingredients in the large bowl.
Chill and serve.
Stir in marshmallows just before serving (and walnuts if desired).
Recipe serves 6.

title: chinese hamburgers
directions: Combine the ingredients using 1/2 small can tomato sauce. Make into patties and fry until brown.
Add rest of tomato sauce and simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes about 8 patties.
The sauce makes good gravy.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla. Add sifted flour, salt, cocoa and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours.
Form into balls about the size of small marbles, between the palms of the hands.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and bake in a moderate oven, 350°, for about 20 minutes.
Cool.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Yields six dozen small cookies.

title: sugarless applesauce cake
directions: Cook raisins, dates and water until water is evaporated and fruit is soft.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Combine well and form into a ball.
Refrigerate until solid. Then take the shrimp ball and roll into a mixture of 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 3 tablespoons of chopped parsley.
Enjoy!

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in Pyrex dish.
Blend in sugar with fork.
Add vanilla and stir in egg until smooth.
Slowly add flour and stir until completely blended.
Fold in peaches.
Bake at 325° until top is lightly brown.

title: honey peach butter
directions: In a large kettle, cook the peaches in water until soft.
Press through a sieve or food mill.
Measure 12 cups pulp; return to the kettle.
Add sugar and honey.
Cook, stirring often, until mixture thickens, about 1 1/4 hours.
Stir more frequently as it thickens to prevent sticking.
Pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process for 10 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Yield:
6 pints.

title: gwumpki casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add soup.
Fill 1/2 empty soup can with milk and 1/2 with water.
Stir into meat mixture.
Add rice and stir.
Place cabbage (approximately 5 cups) in a greased 4 to 6-quart casserole dish.
Pour meat sauce over cabbage.
Do not stir.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: scallops au gratin
directions: Rinse scallops in cold water; drain and set aside.
Saute mushrooms in 1/4 cup oil.
Remove mushrooms and reserve drippings. Combine milk and cornstarch.
Stir to remove lumps.
Pour into drippings.
Add mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened.
Stir in scallops, mushrooms and cooking wine.
Pour mixture into a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: turnip relish
directions: Mix and let stand in refrigerator 1 week.
Put in jars.
Keeps 3 months or more.

title: seasoning
directions: Sift together 3 times. Store in tightly closed container. This is good on all meats.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Cook hamburg and onion in frying pan.
When done, cover bottom of baking
pan or casserole with meat.
Add carrots and peas and then top with soup. Top with scoops of mashed potato. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: corn dogs
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Blend shortening with eggs, then add milk.
Mix well.
Add to dry ingredients.
Now you're ready to dip hot dogs in batter.
Have your pan ready with grease to float hot dog (350°).
Done when they come back to top.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Cook spinach as per directions on box.
Squeeze out water. Mix cream cheese and soup.
Add spinach and onions.
Pour into greased casserole.
Crush crackers; melt butter and add to crackers.
Put crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: good punch
directions: Layer bottom of oblong baking dish with low-fat chocolate graham crackers.
Mix 1 package of NutraSweet vanilla pudding according to the directions.
Mix in 1 small container of reduced fat Cool Whip and spoon on top of crackers.
Layer top with graham crackers and place in refrigerator for about 6 to 8 hours.
Serve chilled.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate coated pretzels or peanuts
directions: Pretzels:
Melt 1/2 package almond bark, stirring constantly. Dip pretzels and place on wax paper to dry.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine ingredients and form in balls.
Pour barbecue sauce over and cook at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: chicken and vegetable skillet
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil and brown chicken; drain.
Add peas and carrots, Lipton soup mix and parsley; blend with water. Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve with hot mashed potatoes, if desired.

title: meat ball casserole
directions: Fry meat balls until brown.
Remove from pan.
Saute onion and add tomatoes.
Cook carrots and potatoes until tender. Combine vegetables in casserole.
Top with meat balls.
Heat in oven until casserole begins to boil at 350°.

title: onion pie
directions: Preheat heat oven to 350.
Bake pie shells for 8 minutes.

title: green bean salad
directions: Bring vinegar to boil in a saucepan; add sugar and one tablespoon salt.
Open vegetables and drain.
Pour vegetables in a large bowl.
Pour vinegar over vegetables.
Let stand 3 or 4 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: broiled herbed lamb chops
directions: Heat the broiler.
Rub the lamb chops thoroughly with half clove of garlic.
Brush with olive oil and sprinkle with the oregano.
Pepper and salt (just a sprinkle on each chop).
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat for about 3 to 4 minutes each side for medium rare.

title: apple cake and frosting
directions: Beat eggs and oil until foamy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat 5 minutes.
Add rest of dry ingredients and mix well.
Add apples and nuts, mix well.
(Suggest use of electric mixer.)
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: antipasto
directions: Mix all ingredients together the night before; cover and refrigerate.

title: uncle rick and grandma lawson's beef jerky
directions: Slice flank steak lengthwise with the grain into 1/4-inch strips. Combine soy sauce, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix with the steak strips and let stand 10 to 15 minutes to marinate.
Stir 2 to 3 times while marinating.
Drain and arrange strips in a single layer on a rack set in shallow baking pan. Bake in a very slow oven at 150° overnight or 12 hours until dried.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Mix and put in greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with 1 cup crushed corn flakes and dot with oleo.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brown rice
directions: Place all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook in a 325° oven for 30 minutes. Cover with foil and continue baking until rice is tender and all liquid is absorbed.

title: cherry-cheese pie
directions: Whip whipping cream with 1/4 cup powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
In another bowl, whip cream cheese with 1/4 cup powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Then mix both mixtures together. Pour into pie shell, evenly, and spread with cherry pie filling. Must be refrigerated at least 4 hours before serving.

title: brigidas' pork loin
directions: Cut excess fat from pork loin.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, let set for 30 minutes.
Put oil in pressure cooker and heat.
When hot add garlic, peeled but whole, and bread.
When they are brown take out and put aside.
Quick fry the pork loin (in 2 pieces) in the oil until brown.
Mash the garlic and bread together and add to the pot when the meat is brown.
Add the wine, water and chicken broth.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes at medium-high setting.
When done take the meat out and cool.
Slice meat into thin slices.
Put what is left in the pot into blender and liquify, creating the meat sauce, which accompanies the pork loin.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: mexican-style baked corn casserole
directions: Combine and pour into well-greased 7 1/2 x 11-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: herbed yogurt cheese
directions: Drain yogurt in strainer (cheesecloth).
Refrigerate covered for 4 hours (should end up with 1 cup yogurt).
Combine the drained yogurt with the rest of ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Store in fridge and serve with bread or crackers; chilled or at room temperature.
One-fourth cup equals 76 calories, 2 grams fat.

title: chocolate dump cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slowly melt the butter, water and cocoa.
Pour over the flour and sugar, then mix.
Add eggs, milk, soda and vanilla.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: italian stuffing
directions: Cook sausage, diced salami, onions, celery and parsley.
Tear bread and add to eggs, mixing with hands.
Add other ingredients. Place in glass casserole (13 x 9 x 2-inch) uncovered at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix together tomatoes, celery, onion, and salt and set overnight. Drain (DO NOT RINSE) about 2 hours.
Place sugar, vinegar, celery seed, cayenne pepper, and green peppers in pot and add drained, tomato mixture.
Bring to a boil and cook about 15 minutes.
Pack into hot jars and seal at once.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions into a gallon jar.
Mix the remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour it over jar contents. Stir every day.
Ready to eat in 2 weeks.
No need to stir anymore after 2 weeks if spices haven't settled to bottom.

title: southern style green beans
directions: Boil together for a few minutes.

title: diabetic banana bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt and add to sugar mixture.
Mash bananas and add. Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: lime cheesecake
directions: Mix.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool before filling.

title: frog-eyed salad
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in 2/3 cup pineapple juice and egg.
Heat and stir until thick.
Add lemon juice and set aside to cool.
Cook pasta according to package and drain.
Combine cooked mixture with pasta.
Cover and chill in refrigerator.
After mixture is chilled, stir in all other ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: irish stew(serves 8)
directions: Place in layers in an ungreased casserole the meat, onions, potatoes, carrots, celery, etc.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix together oil, eggs, vanilla and sugar.

title: peppered ribeye steaks
directions: Brush steaks lightly with olive oil.
In a small bowl, combine all seasonings.
Sprinkle seasonings over steaks and press into both sides.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Grill steaks, turning once, over medium-hot coals for 14 to 18 minutes for rare, 18 to 22 minutes for medium or 24 to 28 minutes for well done.

title: family breakfast
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard together.
Place cubed bread in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Add layer of sausage, then egg mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before cooking, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Blend in milk.
Add eggs, one at a time, and flour, a little at a time.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet.
Place 6 tortillas in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine hamburger meat, onion, mushroom soup, water, chilies and cheese.
Divide mixture into half.

title: chicken cheese pie
directions: Saute onions and pepper in oleo until tender.
Stir in flour and broth.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add chicken, carrots and egg.
Turn into a pie shell.
Top with slices of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Remove sausage from casing and fry until fully cooked.
Hold excess fat aside.

title: stroganoff
directions: Brown beef, salt and onion.
Combine paprika, nutmeg and flour.
Sprinkle over beef mixture.
Add soup and mushrooms and cook about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add sour cream and simmer over low heat.
Serve over cooked medium noodles.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Butter bottom of baking dish.
Take chicken off bone and place in bottom of dish.
Pour mixed vegetables on top of chicken.
Mix cream of chicken soup with chicken broth and pour over vegetables. Mix flour and milk together.
Pour on top to make crust.
Slice butter on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° or until golden brown.

title: tidbit biscuits
directions: Stir baking mix, milk and dill weed together. Beat for 30 seconds. Drop by very small spoonfuls on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan or foil wrapped cookie sheet.
Press a cube of cheese into each biscuit, covering totally with batter.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni.
Cube and grate cheese.
Mix milk and eggs. Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Mix all together but grated cheese.
Pour in pan and top with grated cheese.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Mix well and let congeal.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar, nuts and vanilla well and spread over gelatin.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave chocolate and margarine in large bowl on High for 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate until well blended.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and walnuts until well blended.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook winter mix until tender; drain.
Mash and add Cheddar cheese soup.
Cook diced potatoes and diced onion until tender. Cook in just enough water to cover.
Add water, onion and potatoes to soup mixture.
Add milk and butter to desired consistency.

title: swiss steak with potatoes
directions: Cook steak with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
With wooden mallet, pound steak between wax paper until 1/2 inch thick. Cut in serving pieces.
Heat oil in a large skillet and add onion and garlic; saute until tender.
Add tomatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add potatoes; cover and simmer 45 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Stir in lemon peel and juice.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip. Spread evenly in bottom of crust. Press berries into cream cheese layer; reserve a few for garnish. Pour 2 cups milk in large bowl; add pudding.
Beat 1 minute. Let stand 1 minute. Gently stir in 1 cup Cool Whip. Spoon over berries in crust. Refrigerate 4 hours. Garnish with berries and Cool Whip.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake; let cool.
Put in bottom of punch bowl.
Mix pudding and put on top of cake.
Add pineapple, strawberries, Cool Whip and coconut in layers.

title: spicy catfish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine bread crumbs and spices.
Set aside.
Mix catfish fillets with ketchup, then coat both sides with bread crumb mixture.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake for 10 minutes until lightly browned or until fish flakes with a fork.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Brown beef in Dutch oven.
Add all remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.

title: quick chicken supreme
directions: Brown unfloured chicken in melted butter in Dutch oven or deep frying pan.
Remove chicken to plate.
Stir pepper and olives in drippings.
coat well.
Add soup and water; mix.
Put chicken back in and simmer until tender, approximately 30 minutes.
Boil 4 to 6 servings vermicelli; drain and rinse.
Put noodles in large dish and pour on chicken mixture.
Top with 1 cup grated cheese.
Place in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: In bowl, combine first 5 ingredients and beat until stiff (at least 15 minutes).
Fold in heavy cream, whipped.
Mound into cooked 9-inch pie shell and freeze.
Take out of freezer 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: overnight cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage; chop onions and green pepper. Slice olives. Heat oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper until sugar dissolves. Pour over cabbage, green pepper, onions and olives. Mix gently and store in refrigerator overnight. Keep, covered, in refrigerator. Serves 20. Must do ahead.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put green peas in microwave for 2 minutes to cook, then add to mixture and refrigerate.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt margarine and mix with cracker crumbs.
Put most of the crumbs on the bottom of a 9x13 pan.
Save rest to sprinkle on top. Mix milk and pudding.
Add slightly melted ice cream and cool whip.
Mix well.
Pour mixture on top of crumbs.
Add the rest of the crumbs over the top.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package; set aside to cool.
Drain thoroughly.
Melt margarine.
Saute onion, then remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and spinach.
Mix well and refrigerate for 1/2 hour or more, until mixture is stiff enough to roll into balls.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar; beat.
Stir dry ingredients; blend thoroughly.
Pour into a long dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, corn syrup and water in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cook, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened.
Add jello, stirring until dissolved.
Cool.
Place strawberries in pie shell; pour in gelatin mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Boil carrots until tender; drain. Add Velveeta cheese to carrots; melt cheese. Put mixture in a greased dish. Melt butter; crush crackers and mix in with butter. Sprinkle on top of carrots and cheese. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: smothered hamburger steak
directions: Mix beef with 1/2 cup water and remaining ingredients except onions and gravy. Shape in 4 large patties about 1/2-inch thick. Brown on one side, turn.
Add onion and brown slightly. Add gravy. Cover and simmer about 35 minutes. Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter.
Add powdered sugar, then egg yolks; beat to creamy consistency.
Add vanilla; mix well. Add flour, a little at a time.
When well mixed, add nuts.
Drop by half teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake until brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together corn flakes and oleo.
Put on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: deviled chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a large rimmed baking sheet. Remove and discard skin from chicken.
Place chicken on baking sheet.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Add other ingredients in this order:
bell pepper, pimento, mushrooms, salt, water, onion, garlic, shrimp and bay leaf.
Cover skillet.
When steaming freely, switch to lower heat for 30 minutes.
Cook rice separately.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Prepare angel food cake mix according to instructions.
Cool. Cut angel food cake into bite-size pieces.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with cake pieces.
Whip the whipping cream together with cream cheese and powdered sugar.
(Can use Cool Whip instead of whipping cream.)
Spread over top of cake pieces.
Fruit pie filling or fresh fruit syrup with fresh fruit may be used for topping.

title: cool mexican dip
directions: Mix all together and chill for 1 hour.
Serve with taco chips.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredient in large bowl.
Blend for 1 minute, beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased or floured pan 9 x 13-inch.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: oriental beef patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Form into 8 flat patties.
Fry patties in a little hot fat over low heat until brown on both sides.
Serve with rice.
This recipe can be doubled if desired.

title: hershey cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add to mixture alternately with syrup.
Blend until mixed.
Pour into greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.
Add topping to cake.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Combine.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: frankfurter rinderrouladen(rolled beef)
directions: Dice the bacon and fry lightly together with the finely chopped onion and a crushed clove of garlic.
Add the carrot and gherkin, finely chopped and seasoned.
Place the filling on each side of meat.
Roll up and tie with a string.
Heat the oil and butter and in it fry the rolls on all sides.
Add the red wine and water and simmer over low heat.
Add to the frying juices the tomato puree, the flour mixed with cold water and the cream; cook for a few minutes.
Cut the rolls into slices and serve with mashed potatoes.

title: crab salad spread
directions: Butter bread lightly and cut in cubes.
(Electric knife works real well to remove crust and to cut bread in cubes.)
Mix eggs, bread and onions and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, mix celery, mayonnaise and crab meat.
Add to bread mixture and mix well. Refrigerate 4 hours.
Serve on crackers.

title: michigan blueberry pie
directions: Mix blueberries and lemon juice.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, flour, lemon rind, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and butter.
Add this mixture to the berries, mixing well but carefully, then pour into pastry shell.
Brush top with milk; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: refried bean dip
directions: Heat over low heat until cheese has melted.
Can be served from crock-pot with tortilla chips.

title: fresh red sauce
directions: Combine the chilies and boiling water in a bowl; let them steep for about 10 minutes.
Transfer the mixture to an electric blender; blend on high speed for 30 seconds.
Scrape out the jar with a rubber spatula.
Add onions, oil, garlic, oregano and salt. Blend again until the red chili sauce is a smooth puree.
Taste for seasoning.
This can be used for dipping fresh cooked shrimp or over a broiled or baked fish.

title: ham-mushroom-pineapple skewers
directions: Alternate first 3 ingredients on small bamboo skewers.
Brush with mixture of equal parts soy sauce and sherry.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes.
Makes about 20 , about 25 calories each.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Combine other ingredients. Pour over carrots.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sour cream chicken nachos
directions: Combine sour cream, cheese spread and picante sauce in saucepan; stir over low heat until cheese spread is melted.
Stir in chicken.
On serving platter, layer half of chips, cheese spread mixture, lettuce, tomato and olives; repeat layers.
Top with additional sour cream, if desired.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream margarine with 3 tablespoons sugar.
Add chopped pretzels.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fast antipasto
directions: Place catsup, oil, vinegar, garlic and anchovies in large saucepan.
Heat to boiling; boil one minute.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Simmer 1 minute.
Remove and cool. Keeps well refrigerated for several weeks.
Makes 3 pints.

title: baking powder biscuits number 2
directions: Mix and
sift
dry ingredients.
Work in butter and add milk. Mix to a soft dough with knife.
Toss on board and roll until 1/2-inch
thick.
Shape
with cutter.
Place on buttered pans and bake in a very hot oven at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hobo stew
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add chopped onions.
Cook until onions are done; drain.
Prepare sauce.
Add milk to mushroom soup and heat.
Add cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
In a buttered casserole, place a layer of thin sliced potatoes, then a layer of meat mixture, then a layer of peas or corn.
Do this twice.
On top, place chopped green pepper and cover with the mushroom cheese sauce.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Cook at 350° or until potatoes are done.
I use a large cake pan and double the recipe.
This is also good reheated.
Very good.

title: creamy vegetable soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over high heat, bring first 7 ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add corn and peas.
Cover and simmer 5 more minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in warm milk and butter until well blended.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: maple tree muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and nuts in a mixing bowl. Combine remaining ingredients in a separate bowl; beat well.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients; stir just until flour is moistened.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin pan wells.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in muffin comes out clean.

title: alexander
directions: Over crushed ice in cocktail shaker, pour remaining ingredients.
Shake well.
Strain mixture into a cocktail glass. Serves 1.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine ingredients in order given in large mixing bowl.
Beat 4 minutes on medium speed.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° or until done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Serve with whipped cream flavored with 1 tablespoon molasses.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk.
Mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Garnish with nuts and whipped topping.

title: dina's spinach salad
directions: Rip spinach into bite sized pieces.
Add cut apples and bacon.
Mix together orange juice, and mayonnaise with wire whip. Pour dressing over spinach, apples and bacon before serving. Serves 8.

title: cinnamon-raisin biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, raisins, milk, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll out and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Bake at 500° until light brown.
Make vanilla glaze by mixing powdered sugar, water and vanilla.
Spread on warm biscuits.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on box (2 or 3 layers).

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello and 1 cup boiling water.
Add thawed strawberries and juice; add pineapple and juice.
Add bananas and as many walnuts as you like.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into 9 x 12-inch glass cake pan.
Refrigerate both halves.
When almost set, cover half in cake pan with sour cream and add rest of mixture on top. Refrigerate.
Enjoy!

title: butterscotch thins
directions: Mix well. Roll very thin and cut with cookie cutter. Bake at 350° on a greased cookie sheet.

title: old-fashioned lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine 2 cups of the flour with 10x sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat evenly in pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes longer or until lemon topping is set and lightly browned.
Cool completely.
Dust with 10x sugar.
Cut in 1 x 2-inch bars.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 48 bars.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: calzones
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in large skillet; drain well.	Return to skillet.
Stir in 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce and Italian seasoning. Unroll French loaf; roll into a 16-inch square.
Cut into 4 squares.
Spoon 1/2 cup beef mixture onto center of each square. Fold over to form a triangle, pressing edges to seal.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.

title: fudge candy
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, salt and milk together in a thick saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it comes to a bubble.
Start timing and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat immediately.
Add morsels, marshmallow cream, vanilla and crushed nuts.
Beat all this real good and put in a buttered platter.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add raw rice and add 3 soups. Pour into greased casserole (13 1/2 x 9-inch).
Place chicken pieces on top, bone side up.
Bake 1 hour, covered, at 350°. Uncover after first hour; turn chicken over and bake another 45 minutes to 1 hour, uncovered, until brown.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix soup, chicken and water in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Drop bite size pieces of biscuits into boiling mixture. Reduce heat.
Simmer until dough is done.
Serves 2.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix and drop in hot, boiling chicken broth.

title: cider punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pan with the exception of the sugar and ginger ale.
Sweeten to taste and then chill.
When ready to use, add ginger ale and serve.
Serve very cold.
Makes about 9 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Beat the egg slightly with rotary beater.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
(To prevent spills, place pie pan on oven rack or on open oven door when filling with pumpkin mixture.)
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake for 35 more minutes.
Cool.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Mix 1 cup sugar with rhubarb and place on bottom of cake pan.
Mix the eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder and salt and pour over fruit.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: texas torte
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with Mexican food.

title: easy cherry dessert
directions: Mix crushed graham crackers with melted butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Dream Whip as directed; add softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Whip again.
Spread mixture on top of cracker mixture; spread cherry pie filling over top.
Chill.
If desired, serve with whipped cream.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine soda and buttermilk and let stand a few minutes.
Cream sugar, margarine and shortening.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in egg whites; gently stir in pecans and coconut.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) greased, floured layer pans at 325° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done.
Frost cooled cake with cream cheese icing.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except the flour together.
Then add the flour to make a stiff dough.
Place part of the dough on a lightly floured pastry cloth.
Knead dough to desired consistency.
Roll out about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Place on floured cookie sheet in a 325° oven until firm. Remove from sheet to wire rack immediately. Stores well in airtight container or in freezer.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine the cracker crumbs and butter; put in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: mom's lasagne
directions: In a medium skillet, cook and stir ground chuck and garlic until meat is brown.
Drain; add tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on package and drain.
In an ungreased baking dish, 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch, alternate layers of meat sauce, noodles, cheese and cottage cheese, beginning and ending with sauce.
Bake uncovered 20 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: between the sheets
directions: Blend with crushed ice.
Pour into cocktail glass.

title: refrigerator cucumbers
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and let stand 3 hours; drain.
(Do not heat.)
Dissolve the sugar and vinegar.
Mix well.
Combine with cucumbers. Also celery seed, if desired.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep for 1 month.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Mix sugar, oranges and pineapple together.
Add marshmallows, coconut and sour cream.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine both soups and broth.
Layer 1/2 chicken, 1/2 dressing and 1/2 soup mixture.
Repeat again.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove lid and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: eddie's apple crumb pie
directions: Arrange pared, sliced apples in pie crust.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon mixed together.
Sift together other flour and 1/2 cup sugar; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture on apples.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce oven to 350° and bake an additional 40 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus, saving some juice to mix with soup.
In a casserole dish layer:
crushed potato chips, asparagus, sliced Velveeta cheese and soup mixture.
Repeat.
Top with Velveeta cheese.
Cover and microwave 4 to 5 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Layer in casserole: hamburger, noodles, zucchini, 1/3 can Cheddar soup and 1/3 can mushroom soup.
Layer 2 more times.
Add 1/2 can water poured over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top last 10 minutes with buttered bread crumbs.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook sausage.
Add to crock-pot with other ingredients.
Cook on low 4 hours.

title: peanut butter and cracker fudge
directions: Combine the sugar, milk, butter, and cocoa in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 1 minute (rolling boil). Drop a small amount from tip of spoon into a small container of cold water.
If it can be formed into a soft ball, it is ready to remove from the heat.
Stir in the peanut butter, vanilla, and crumbled crackers.
Drop onto wax paper using about 1 tablespoon for each pattie.
Cool until set.
Makes about 40 to 45 fudge patties.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flavoring.
Mix 1 tablespoon less than 2 cups flour and dry pudding in another bowl.
By hand, mix eggs in, one at a time.
Mix all ingredients together; pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes. Do not open oven or cake will fall.

title: ritz cracker cookies
directions: Spread thinly the peanut butter between 2 crackers, then dip in hot melted chocolate.
Repeat.
Let stand until cool.

title: gourmet mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
Drain and mash.
Add all other ingredients.
Cut into a buttered baking dish.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: "fasoulakia yahni" - braised green beans
directions: Saute onions lightly in olive oil in large saucepan.
Add tomato sauce; add salt and pepper and simmer for about 15 minutes. Add string beans and remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour or until tender.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease and flour large cookie sheet. Sift together in large bowl flour and sugar.
Melt in saucepan the oleo and cocoa.
Add water and bring to a boil and add to flour mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla, soda and cinnamon.
Hand mix only.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Boil broccoli, cauliflower and carrots for about 10 minutes; drain.
Add and mix in a large bowl the sour cream, cream of mushroom soup, onion and Swiss cheese.
Mix well together.
Pour into baking dish; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with fried onion rings and heat 3 minutes more.
Take out of oven and ready to eat.

title: hot mushroom pinwheels
directions: Separate rolls into 4 rectangles; pinch perforations together.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain fat.
Cube and melt cheese in the microwave.
Combine all ingredients in a crock pot.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: salmon patties
directions: Beat egg and add parsley, onion salt and lemon juice.
Add salmon (liquid and all) and flakes and mix with a fork.
When mixed well, add crackers and stir until well mixed and moistened. Form into firm patties to prevent crumbling.
Fry in about 1/8-inch of shortening until brown; drain.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except milk, and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add milk to moisten.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix in order given.
Dough will be sticky.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork or with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute celery, onion and mushroom pieces in butter or margarine. Cook broccoli and drain according to package directions.
Drain well.
Add mushroom soup, melted cheese and all other ingredients. Can add sliced almonds, if desired.
Dip with Fritos or Doritos.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Saute meat and onion.
Add tomato sauce and spices.
Cook noodles until tender.
Lightly oil an 8 x 13-inch baking dish. Arrange a layer of the meat, then the cottage cheese, then the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix all together and serve on lettuce leaf with crackers.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put
all
ingredients in blender.
Mix until thoroughly blended.
Pour
into
a 10-inch greased and floured pie plate. Bake at
for
one hour or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Results will be a crust, filling and topping.
Be sure to use a 10-inch pie plate.

title: raised cookies
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Cut flour, sugar and oleo together to make coarse crumbs.
Mix the eggs and yeast into crumb mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out and pat on a mixture of 1 cup brown sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Roll jelly roll fashion. Slice into cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost as desired.

title: fried ham with redeye gravy
directions: Heat a large heavy skillet over medium heat.
On each slice of ham, sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon of sugar.
Place a ham slice in skillet, sugar side down.
Cook until brown.
Turn and sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon sugar on second side.
Repeat with remaining ham slices and sugar.
Remove ham and keep warm.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour into dish.
Chop tomatoes and drain.
Chop green onions and slice black olives; put on top of mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
May add jalapeno peppers.
If desired, serve with corn chips.

title: cocoons
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; blend in flour until smooth.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Shape mixture into fingers or small balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not let cookies get too brown for they will taste scorched. Remove from cookie sheet and roll in powdered sugar.

title: cinnamon cream squares
directions: Cream until smooth.
Press rolls onto cookie sheet (1 package).
Spread cream mixture over top.
Smooth second package of rolls on top of this; crimp edges.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until brown.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Cut into squares.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Cream cheese in mixer.
Add remaining ingredients except blueberries.
Mix on medium speed for 4 minutes.
Fold in blueberries.
(Drain blueberries on paper towels and pat dry.) Put in tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: aunt dede's vegetable salad
directions: Mix sugar, water, vinegar and oil in a small saucepan.
Bring to a rapid boil, stirring constantly.
Cool completely.
Mix the vegetables with cooled dressing and refrigerate.

title: nutmeg sauce
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and salt.
Stir in hot milk and cook in top of double boiler.
Stir until mixture coats a spoon.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and nutmeg.
Chill.
Good on sliced pound cake.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: In large saucepan, melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter over very low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Stir in cereal.
Press 1/2 of mixture in a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or dish.
Chill.
Set remaining mixture aside.
Melt over hot water (not boiling) the semi-sweet chocolate morsels, sugar, margarine and water, stirring constantly until smooth.
Spread over chilled cereal mixture.
Spread remaining cereal evenly on top.
Press in gently.
Chill until firm (1 hour).
Makes 25 squares.

title: crispy herb baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease or line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan or 13 x 9-inch pan with foil.
In medium bowl, combine potato flakes, Parmesan cheese and garlic salt; stir until well mixed. Dip chicken pieces into margarine; roll in potato flake mixture to coat.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender and golden brown.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: easy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Start with the garlic.
Peel all the cloves of an entire head! Whatever the chemistry of this recipe, it does not end up being garlicky and the whole cloves in the finished product are a sweet edible vegetable.

title: jim's mother's chicken and rice casserole
directions: Brown chicken in small amount of oil and margarine; remove from pan.
Add celery, onion and green pepper to drippings and saute.
Add rice and saute, stirring constantly until slightly translucent.
Add can of tomatoes that have been blenderized for just a few seconds, water and chicken bouillon.
Arrange chicken down into rice, cover and bake at 350° until rice is almost done. Spread defrosted peas over casserole and continue to cook for at least 10 minutes.
(I prefer to use boneless chicken breasts or tenders.)

title: pork-n-bean casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add other ingredients.
Heat until well mixed.
Place in a casserole dish.
Place cheese slices on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers. Prepare pudding with the 3 cups of milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture over graham crackers and top with another layer of graham crackers.
Pour a layer of pie filling on next, to complete the dessert.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well.

title: great grandma's cornbread
directions: Mix all together well. Pour into 9 x 13 pan that has been well-greased. Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown on top.

title: roast pheasant
directions: Rub goose with salt and place on rack in shallow pan.
Roast in moderate gas oven (325°) for 25 minutes per pound.
After goose has roasted about 1 hour, prick skin so fat will run out. Pour off fat as it accumulates.
If dressing is desired, follow directions for Stuffed Roast Duck.

title: fourth of july pie
directions: Cut up fruit and take out seeds or pits.
Put fruit into crust.
Mix Cool Whip with fruit.
Decorate the top with extra fruit.
Chill in refrigerator and enjoy.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: *Use large can of pumpkin.
It makes 3 batches.
Just triple recipe.

title: southern raised biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and water; let stand 5 minutes.
Add buttermilk (I warm buttermilk).
Set aside.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Mix and turn out on floured board.
Knead 4 or 5 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with round cutter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: connoisseur casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients; place in Pyrex dish.
Add crackers, margarine and almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Saute onion in oil; add to tomato sauce.
Wash and dry eggplant; cut ends off.
Make 1/4-inch round slices.
Spread on platter; salt it.
Let stay for 1/2 hour.
Dry slices with paper towel.
Put some flour in paper bag; add slices, then shake excess off.
Dip both sides in beaten egg and saute in hot oil quickly until brown on both sides.
Cover bottom of baking pan with some sauce.
Arrange slices overlapping in layers.
Cover each layer with sauce and grated cheese.
On top layer add a little oregano. Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as label directs; drain.
