Rinse with cold water. In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, Italian dressing and mustard; mix well.
Add cucumber, tomato, green pepper, green onion, salt, pepper, tuna in large pieces and macaroni.
Toss to mix well.
Turn into salad bowl.
Refrigerate, covered, until well chilled, about 4 hours.

title: black bread
directions: Combine flours in a large bowl. Set aside three cups. Sprinkle yeast over 1/2 c warm water.
Stir until softened, set aside.
In large mixing bowl
stir together reserved 3 c flour mixture, cocoa, caraway seeds, salt and instant coffee.
Heat in a saucepan, 2 c water, honey, vinegar and butter until just warm. Butter does not need to be completely melted.
Blend well with cocoa mixture.
Add yeast, stir until thoroughly mixed.
Stir in enough additional flour, 1 c at a time until dough no longer clings to sides of bowl.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl and mix with an electric mixer.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or more if it is still jiggly in the center.
Cool.
Serve with whipped topping, if desired.

title: cocoa brownies(quick mix and very good brownies)
directions: Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Start oven 10 minutes before baking; set to moderate (350°).
Sift flour, measure, resift 3 times with next 3 ingredients, the last time into a 3-quart mixing bowl or the large mixer bowl.
Add butter, eggs and vanilla.
Use wooden spoon and beat 100 strokes per minute for 3 minutes by hand or 2 minutes on medium speed on mixer.
Clean off beater and remove.
Stir in nuts with a wooden spoon until just distributed. Turn into prepared pan and spread out to even thickness.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until barely done.
Mark, cool in pan on cake rack, then cut and store like brownies.
Makes 16 (2-inch) brownies.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix bananas, sugar, eggs and shortening in mixing bowl and set aside.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately to fruit batter.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add rest of ingredients and stir by hand.
Grease cookie sheets.
Spoon in six portions (divide in six portions on sheets in sort of loaf shape).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Slice and put back in oven for 10 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine vegetables and chilies in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat until blended well.
Pour over vegetables and toss lightly.
Cover and chill 6 to 8 hours.
Stir gently before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crayfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet or heavy pot.
Saute onions, garlic, green pepper and celery until onions are clear.
Add 1/8 cup water and simmer covered until vegetables are tender
(about 15 minutes). Add crayfish fat and cook covered for 15 minutes on very low heat.
Stir occasionally.
Add tails and other seasonings. Cook 15 minutes.
Add green onions and parsley and cook 5 minutes for seasoning to blend.
Makes 4-5 servings.
Serve with rice.
Can add 1 tablespoon of flour to thicken.

title: grandma's carrot soup
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine.
Add onion and cook until softened.
Add the water and the chicken bouillon and bring to a boil.
Mix the cornstarch with the milk and add it to the broth together with the salt and carrots.
Lower the heat and simmer, stirring constantly, until it thickens and boils.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese and croutons, if desired.
Makes 5 servings.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a large skillet, heat olive oil (low-fat, saute in water). Saute garlic for a minute, then add pecans and pumpkin seeds. Saute until pecans begin to become soft (pumpkin seeds will pop and puff up).
Add cooked rice and mix well; continue to saute.
Add about a tablespoon of water and soy sauce.
Add onion powder.
Mix well and cook until heated through.
Serve immediately.
Serve with favorite vegetables on side or on top.

title: meat loaf 1
directions: Mix ingredients and form into loaf, then cover with Sauce.

title: hot spinach
directions: Cook spinach; drain.
Reserve 1/2 cup of juice.
Make sauce of margarine, flour, milk and spinach liquid.
Combine all ingredients in casserole and top with toast crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in a mixing bowl.
Make hole in center and add eggs, shortening, buttermilk, soda and vanilla. Mix together as you would biscuits.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Roll 3/8-inch thick on generously floured board.
Cut with 3-inch cutter and bake at 425°.
Yields 6 to 7 dozen.

title: cobbler dough
directions: Cut shortening into flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk and beat until smooth.
Spread on top of sugared fruit and bake about 45 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini.
Saute carrot and onion in butter until soft. Add soup and cream; add 3 cups croutons and zucchini, stirring gently.
Place in greased casserole.
Put remaining croutons in butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: simple french onion soup
directions: Beat yogurt with a fork until smooth.
Add salt, sugar, red pepper and black pepper.
Mix well.
Add cucumber and onions; mix. Serve well chilled or at room temperature as desired.

title: frog eye salad
directions: In a small saucepan mix sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in pineapple juice and egg.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Set aside and cool. Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Combine cooked mixture with macaroni.
Cover and place in refrigerator until chilled.
Combine drained fruit, whipped topping and marshmallows.
Stir lightly.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine vinegar, oil, salt, pepper and sugar in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Cool. Combine vegetables
and stir into vinegar mixture.
Cover and place in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients in skillet.
Cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve immediately.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together cornmeal, flour, salt, pepper and sugar.
Add onions, buttermilk and juice from corn.
Mix well.
Add butter and egg.
Drop by small tablespoons into 370° deep fat (or oil).
Cook until golden brown.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In ungreased square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch) stir together flour, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix in oil, milk and vanilla with a fork, stirring until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly in pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Pour hot water over batter. Do not stir.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil until crumbly; reserve 1 cup.
Pat remaining mixture lightly in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, drain fat; add onion and cook until tender. Put remaining ingredients in a large bean pot or 2-quart casserole.
Stir in the beef and onion.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish noodles
directions: In an electric skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon. In the bacon grease, brown the hamburger and onion.
Add tomatoes, water and noodles.
Salt, pepper and add chili powder to taste.
Crumble the bacon and add to the other ingredients.
Place lid on the skillet and simmer 40 minutes.
You may have to add extra water if the tomatoes are not real juicy.

title: schnitzel
directions: Pound veal until thin.
Sprinkle meat with lemon juice on both sides.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper. Blend eggs, water and oil.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese; set aside.
Coat veal with flour, egg mixture and then cheese with bread crumbs.
Fry in margarine or oil.

title: buttermilk crappies
directions: Combine buttermilk and soy sauce in large bowl.
Mix together well and set aside.
In large bag, combine cornmeal, flour, lemon pepper, seasoned pepper, seasoned salt and table salt.
Shake well to mix ingredients.
Dip crappie fillets in buttermilk mixture and then in bag.
Shake well to coat fillets.
Deep-fry in peanut oil until golden brown.

title: vermicelli soup(makes 6 servings)
directions: In a soup pot or Dutch oven, brown vermicelli in hot oil.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute until onion is tender.
Add peas and carrots, tomatoes with their liquid, green chilies, chicken broth and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Garnish each serving with parsley.

title: shrimp de jonghe
directions: Add seasoning to melted butter.
Stir in sherry; toss with bread crumbs.
Place shrimp in four baking dishes.
Spoon buttered crumbs over each to form crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Split chicken breasts almost through.
Stuff with ham slices and 1 slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Secure with toothpick.
Dip in beaten egg and cracker crumbs.
Melt margarine in dish.
Place chicken in this and bake until done.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Add yeast and sugar to warm water to dissolve yeast.
Add to all other ingredients and mix.
Roll out on floured paper to 1/4 inch thick.
Spread melted butter on half of the dough, then fold over and cut.
Put biscuits on buttered pan and put melted butter on top of biscuits.
Let rise at least a half hour before baking. Bake at 150° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Place milk, butter and flour into a saucepan and slowly bring to a boil, stirring frequently until mixture becomes thick.
Add 4 tablespoons finely grated cheese and 4 well beaten yolks to the mixture; season with salt and pepper, stir and add 4 egg whites stiffly whipped into mixture.
Place in souffle dish and dust with bread crumbs.
Add lemon juice and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pickled beans
directions: Wash beans until clean of any dirt or spray that may have been used on them. String and break green beans. The fuller or more mature the beans are, the better for pickling. Wash beans again to make sure they are clean enough to eat. Using a large open pan, cook beans by covering them with water in the pan. Cook until their color changes and they are tender when tested with a fork. Let cool. Drain the water off. Pack into a stone churn in approximately 2-inch layers. On top of each layer, sprinkle heavily with salt, approximately 3 tablespoons of salt per layer of beans. Use all the beans and fill churn as full as possible. Top the beans with a saucer turned upside-down and a clean rock from the creek on top of the saucer to keep it weighted down. Tie a clean cloth around the top of the churn and put a lid or a heavy plate on top of cloth. This protects the brine from gnats, also known as Lewis Grizzard's fruit flies which people in the south inherited.

title: cooley punch (red)
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Combine lemonade and juices; chill.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale, cherries and sliced fruit.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onions. Drain off fat.
Put back on the stove. Add tomato sauce and ketchup. Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: venison cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie crust for 9-inch pie.
In skillet, brown meats and drain.
Stir in 1 teaspoon salt, oregano, pepper, bread crumbs, tomato sauce, onion and green pepper.
Pour into shell.
Mix together 1 egg, 1/4 cup milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt, Worcestershire sauce and shredded cheese.
Pour this mixture over meat mixture and bake for 30 minutes.
Preparation time 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine flour and salt; mix well.
Cut Crisco into flour with pastry blender.
Add water and mix well and shape into ball. Divide into 6 portions.
Roll out on floured board, large enough to cover cored apple completely.
Place a peeled and cored apple onto prepared crust.
Into center of apple fill with sugar, cinnamon and a dab of butter.
Fold up crust to center of apple, dab with water to make crust thick.
Bake in oven approximately 45 minutes at 400° or until lightly browned.

title: old-fashioned bean soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or high 5 to 6 hours.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts; 10 servings.

title: first prize applesauce cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: meringue
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and cornstarch.
Mix and add water.
Cook in microwave until it thickens; cool.
Beat egg whites, salt and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Beating at high speed, gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar and the cornstarch mixture.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Spoon on pie filling. Seal to edge.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, then bake at 400° for 4 minutes.

title: chicken strata
directions: Cube six slices of bread.
Place half in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
(I usually spray with Pam first.) Combine chicken, vegetables, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Spoon over bread cubes.
Sprinkle remaining bread cubes over mixture.
Combine eggs and milk; pour over all.
Cover and chill overnight.
Spoon soup over strata.
Butter remaining two slices of bread and cube. Sprinkle cheese over the top during the last few minutes.
Serves 6.
May be doubled and made in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: crustless vegetable quiche
directions: In large bowl, combine rice, Swiss cheese, flour, broccoli, mushrooms and onions.
Place in 10-inch pie plate sprayed with vegetable oil spray.
Top vegetable mixture with red pepper slices.

title: dry garlic chicken wings
directions: Place wings on baking pan.
Cook at 250° to 350°, until partially cooked.
Drain and add sauce to wings.
Put back in oven; finish cooking.
Allow sauce to thicken.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add scalded milk and butter.
Add cinnamon.
(You may wish to add a dash of nutmeg.) Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until mixture is firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and spoon on top of pies.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: crab mold
directions: Melt cream cheese in top of double boiler.
Stir in soup and crabmeat.
Combine water and gelatine; let stand 1 minute.
Mix gelatine with mayonnaise and onion.
Add to crab mixture.
Pour into lightly oiled mold.
Refrigerate several hours or until firm. Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in large pot; drain well.
Add cans of vegetables, undrained.
Bring to boil, stirring to avoid sticking.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook at least 30 minutes.
Serve with cornbread for delicious lunch.
Put leftover soup in Ziploc bags (when cool) and freeze.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil skinned chicken until meat falls from the bone.
Chop chicken.
Save 2 cups of broth and mix with flour and cook until thickened.
Add celery soup and blend.
Add chopped chicken, vegetables and pepper and salt.
Place in casserole.

title: pineapple cream cheese dip or cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Drain crushed pineapple, chopped nuts (very fine), chopped onions (very fine), chopped peppers (very fine).
Mix all ingredients together as a dip or as a cheese ball.
Refrigerate until chilled about 1 hour or 2 before serving.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients thoroughly; let set overnight.
To serve, carve out round bread.
Place dip inside.
Serve with the remaining bread and vegetables.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower.
Layer a thin layer of rice on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Then layer with chicken. Then layer with broccoli and cauliflower.
Mix milk with both cans of soup and pour on top of everything (you can add a thin layer of rice before pouring on the soup).
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top, then cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
(It tastes better when cheese is melted slowly.)

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together chips, peanut butter and oleo.
In large bowl, pour in Rice Chex and then pour melted mixture over it and stir until all coated.
Pour in powdered sugar and shake in covered bowl until coated.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Amounts depend on the number of people to be served.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together and shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cold pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta. In small bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar, sugar and seasoning. In large serving bowl, combine pasta, dressing and remaining ingredients. Cover and refrigerate.

title: ramsey's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Mix with spice, dressing, cucumbers and tomatoes.
Refrigerate and serve cold. Serves 8 to 10.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown onion and meat; arrange in layers with tortillas and cheese.
Put beans in center and arrange another layer of meat, onion, tortillas and cheese.
Then mix soup and tomatoes and pour over the top.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Mix all together and spread on celery sticks.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together, pour into oblong Pyrex dish. Put in refrigerator and let it set overnight.

title: golden fry batter
directions: Place all except half of the milk in a jar and shake vigorously until well mixed. Add rest of milk and shake again lightly. Good for frying squash, green tomatoes, okra, onion rings, apple rings, etc.
Before frying, shake the vegetable, etc., in small bag of flour. Dip in batter and fry in deep fat until brown.

title: quick chop suey
directions: Brown the meat; add boiling water, bouillon cubes, soy sauce and molasses.
Mix cornstarch and cold water together; add to meat mixture, stirring until thickened.
Add celery and onion; cover and cook for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot rice or Chinese noodles.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix and serve with fresh jicama slices or broccoli flowerets

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients up until olive oil. Form into 4 cakes and coat with corn meal. Heat oil - when hot add crab cakes and cook 3-4 minutes on each side. Serve immediately, or loosely cover and transfer to a warm oven.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: In large salad bowl, toss lettuce, celery, onions and chicken; add wontons, sesame seed and almonds and toss lightly.
Dress with Oriental Salad Dressing.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Chop and drain vegetables.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water and add boiling water.
Let cool.
Fold in vegetables and mayonnaise.

title: burrito casserole(makes 8 to 10 burritos.)
directions: Put burritos in a long baking pan for 20 minutes at 350°. Turn over before 20 minutes is up.
While you are waiting, mix salsa and soup together in a large bowl.
When 20 minutes is up, pour the salsa and soup mixture over burritos.
Put grated cheese and green onions all over the burritos.
Bake until cheese is melted and mixture is bubbling at 350°.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Chill at least 2 hours or store in freezer until needed.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Good hot or cold.

title: chocolate flakes
directions: Melt chocolate over lukewarm water in double boiler.
Add vanilla, nuts and corn flakes and mix well.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Let stand until set.
Yield:
48 cookies.

title: health bread
directions: Bring raisins and water to a boil; boil for a few minutes, then cool.
Beat together eggs, sugar and salt.
Add raisins and water mixture and soda in buttermilk to egg mixture.
Stir in All-Bran, oatmeal and flour.
Put in greased pan.
Bake 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: candy peanuts
directions: Melt sugar and water, add nuts and salt and food color.
At medium heat cook until liquid disappears while watching and stirring.
Spread on baking sheet and put in oven at 3350 degrees until dry.
Check after 10 minutes.
Stir and carefully life from foil and return to oven if not dry.
When dry, allow to cool and store in a tight jar.

title: texas caviar
directions: Bring oil, vinegar and Worcestershire to a boil, add peas and soup and bring to a boil again.
Remove from heat, add remaining ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve hot or cold as a dip.

title: reese's bars
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, margarine and crumbs together; pat firmly into a 7 x 12-inch pan (or 8 or 9-inch square pan).
Melt chocolate chips; spread over bars.
Makes 20 to 25 squares.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Chop stems and add to sausage and Cheddar cheese; mix well.
Roll small amount sausage mixture and place in mushroom caps.
Place on baking pan and bake at 400° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes or until sausage is cooked through.

title: arkansas spice cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, salt and spices.
Mix alternately with water into butter mixture, then fold in raisins, apple, nuts and candy.
This makes a big cake.
Bake in a tube pan in a 350° oven; start checking after 45 minutes.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Combine sugar and butter in bowl.
Add egg white, milk, and vanilla to mixture.
Mix together until mixture is formed into ball.
Take small amount of mixture and form into little balls. Place cinnamon in a bowl and roll the balls (a few at a time) until they are evenly coated with cinnamon.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, for about 1 hour at 350°.
Stir before serving.

title: mormon bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add milk and oil.
Mix well.
Pour into gallon jar with a lid that fits loosely so it can breathe. Refrigerate at least 4 hours before using.

title: chicken and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large casserole, combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Bake covered for 35 to 45 minutes. Remove and cover. Return to oven and bake for an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Casserole will appear soupy but will thicken while standing.
Cool for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil in heavy skillet until transparent.
Combine with next 5 ingredients in bowl; mix well. Melt Velveeta cheese with soup in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add to broccoli and rice mixture; mix well.
Spoon into buttered baking dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese and almonds. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: meal in a skillet
directions: Saute onion and pepper, add hamburger.
Cook until brown. Drain off excess grease.
Add corn, stir well.
Put tomatoes on top of this, add noodles.
Cook slow until noodles are done. Sprinkle on cheese and let melt.
Serve.

title: ham salad filling
directions: Rinse frozen peas under running cold water to separate, drain. Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: mrs. ruth o'neal's famous yeast roll recipe
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add milk.
Add the sugar and salt to the lukewarm mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Add softened shortening and beaten egg.
Mix well.
Add flour.
Mix in with spoon, then with hand.
Knead to make dough soft.
Put in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Knead and make into rolls.
Place into muffin tins or on flat sheet and let rise for 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: patsy's barbecue sauce
directions: *Depending on how hot you want it to taste, use 1/2 teaspoon for mild and spicy, 1 teaspoon for warm and tangy or 2 teaspoons for hot.

title: green tomato jelly
directions: Put tomatoes and sugar in a nice heavy pot.
Bring to a rolling boil that you
can't
stir
down.
Take off heat.
Add jello (any flavor desired).
We
use
raspberry jello.
Put in jars and seal.

title: veggie bars
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and place flat on a 12 x 15-inch jelly roll sheet.
Beat one egg and spread over crescent roll crust. Bake according to directions on package (use a wooden spoon to flatten crust down during baking).
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing together.
Spread on cooled crust.
Spread vegetables evenly over surface.
Spread Cheddar cheese evenly over surface. Cool for 2 hours and then cut into bars.

title: apple-pork shaken bake
directions: Peel and core Apples, place in bowl with Sugar, Flour, Cinnamon, Nutmeg - coat well.
Spread evenly on bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Coat Chops with Shake-n-bake and place on top of apples mixture.
Bake at 400 for 45 minutes.

title: breaded pork steak italian style
directions: Put in a bowl and mix well the bread crumbs, flour, black pepper, 1 tablespoon salt, parsley and cheese.

title: asparagus supreme
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in flour.
Add milk slowly and stir until thickened.
Add yolks, cheese and onion; stir until cheese melts.
Fold in asparagus after removing from heat; season to taste.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in greased 1 quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: something good for breakfast
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Place frozen dough in pan. Sprinkle dry pudding mix, sugar and nuts over the rolls.
Melt margarine and pour over all.
Put on counter and let it set overnight.
In the morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Let sit for 5 to 10 minutes.
Turn out onto plate.
Pull apart and enjoy!

title: strawberry souffle
directions: Use equal parts V-8 juice and undiluted canned beef bouillon. Add celery salt, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce to taste. Heat thoroughly and serve as appetizer.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix cheese and milk until smooth.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill until firm or overnight.

title: cajun cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased 9x13 inch pan at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cocoa buttermilk cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, powdered buttermilk, cocoa, baking soda and salt into mixer bowl.

title: butch's chili
directions: In a large pot brown ground chuck and stew meat until brown but not dry.
Remove meat from pot and drain.
After pouring grease off, add 4 teaspoons oil to large pot and heat on medium setting. Add chopped onion, peppers and garlic; simmer until onions are clear.
Add 2 cups water; bring to a simmering boil.
Add meat, salt, black pepper, paprika, cumin, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder.
(At this point you may have to add more water than listed.)
Keep plenty water in at this point and simmer about 1 hour.
Taste and add salt and red pepper to taste.
After the hour, add tomato sauce, tomatoes and beans.
Make sure you have enough water.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Note:
Omit salt and soda if using self-rising meal.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil; keep hot.
Cook onions and garlic in oil until tender.
Add all other ingredients, except wine, and blend. Cook for 5 minutes.
Return chicken to skillet.
Simmer for 45 minutes covered.
Add wine; cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Skim off fat, take out bay leaf and serve chicken with sauce poured over it.

title: lemon sheet cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl beat the cake mix and eggs until blended. Fold in pie filling. Spread into a greased 15 X 10 X 1 inch baking pan.

title: seven-cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: may day strawberry punch
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the sugar and water; heat almost to boiling, stirring to dissolve the sugar.
Remove from heat; stir in the juices.
Chill.
In a blender, pure berries.
Add to juice mixture; chill 30 minutes.
Transfer to punch bowl; add soda.
If desired, float additional strawberries on top.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Remove from heat. Add rest of ingredients.
Place in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in 350°
oven.
Bake
to
minutes, testing with a toothpick, testing for doneness.
Do not overbake.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Add flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cocoa.
Stir in milk and shortening.
Blend in nuts.
Spread in a 9-inch square pan. Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and cocoa.
Pour water over entire batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
During baking, cake mixture rises to top and chocolate sauce settles to bottom.
Invert squares of pudding on dessert plates. Dip sauce from pan over each piece.
Serve warm with or without whipped cream.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple, juice, pecans, pudding and bananas together. Then add the Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix well and chill.

title: frying pan cookies
directions: Boil sugar, oleo, and milk to a rolling boil for 3 minutes. Stir in oats, cocoa, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: one pot pork chops
directions: Brown chops.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer for 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: To a standard brownie recipe or mix, add 1 cup of Reese's pieces peanut butter candies.
Bake at 350° for 27
to 29 minutes. When cool, frost with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Microwave cheese until melted.
Add salsa and mix.
Add cilantro.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Cut cake into 16 even pieces; line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with cake pieces.
Spread over cake, the pineapple.
Mix pudding with milk.
Pour over cake and crushed pineapple; spread evenly. Cover pudding mixture with bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut into 8 even pieces when completely chilled.
One piece equals 1 milk, 1 bread and 1 fruit.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put white sugar and cinnamon in a small plastic bag.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and shake in bag until coated with sugar mixture.
Melt oleo; add brown sugar and pecans in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Place 1/2 of biscuit pieces into a greased Bundt pan.
Pour 1/2 of the boiled mixture on top.
Then put the remaining biscuit pieces on top and pour the remaining boiled mixture on top.
Bake at 350°; do not overcook!

title: bacon fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon in skillet, remove bacon,
drain some of the grease.
Add cabbage to remaining hot grease and cook until cabbage is brown and tender.
Add worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat crumble the bacon and stir it in the cabbage.

title: vegetable latkes
directions: Peel and coarsely shred potatoes and carrots.
Shred zucchini. Place in a bowl with onion.
Combine eggs, egg whites, salt and pepper; stir into vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle flour over top; stir to mix.
Heat nonstick pan over medium heat; brush with oil. Drop batter by heaping tablespoonfuls into pan; flatten lightly. Cook until browned.
Turn; brown other side.
Add oil as necessary.
Transfer to paper toweling to drain.
Keep warm until all latkes are cooked.
Makes 36 mini latkes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apples in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and salt with beaten eggs; will be crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Mix cinnamon and butter.
Drizzle over crumb mixture. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken veggie pasta toss
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add chicken and garlic.
Stir-fry about 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink in center.
Transfer to serving dish.
Add broccoli, mushrooms and tomato to skillet.
Stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes until crisp-tender.
Return chicken to skillet to heat.
Transfer mixture to large serving bowl.
Add linguine, Parmesan cheese, basil, salt and pepper.
Toss to mix.
Add milk.
Toss.
Serve immediately.

title: zora's party snack
directions: Brown together hamburger and Italian Hot Sausage.
Drain well.
Add Velveeta cheese, oregano and Worcestershire Sauce. Spread mixture on top of Party Rye Bread.
Place in broiler. Broil until bubbly.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift cocoa, flour and sugar together.
Mix well.
Add milk and egg yolks.
(Set egg whites aside for meringue.)

title: mocha frosting
directions: Over low heat melt chocolate, coffee and water in small saucepan until
smooth.
Set
aside for cooling.
Cream butter until light and
fluffy. Beat in yolks one at a time.
Beat in cooled chocolate mixture, then beat in 10x sugar.
Refrigerate until thick enough to spread.

title: lemon lush
directions: Prepare pudding and pie filling.
Cool in refrigerator. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: wanda's fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and cream; bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Take off burner and add semi-sweet chocolate.
Stir until melted.
Add marshmallow cream; mix until well blended.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into buttered sheet pan.
Let cool.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a
large bowl, mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Set aside. In a medium bowl, put white and brown sugars, vanilla, butter and eggs.
Mix together until well blended.
Pour flour mixture into second mixture and mix until a stiff dough.
Mix in chips.
Drop onto
cookie
sheet with a teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and cider vinegar.
Chop up the broccoli and onion.
Crumble the bacon.
Pour mixture over the broccoli, onions and bacon.
Cover and chill before serving.
Enjoy!

title: fruit juice cubes
directions: Freeze in ice trays.
Release cubes and store in freezer until needed.
When ready to serve, fill each glass with cubes and pour ginger ale over cubes.
As the cubes melt, you will have a tasty fruit punch.
Keep a supply stored in your freezer.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump apples in a bowl with eggs, sugar, oil, nuts and all the spices. Add flour last.
Stir together until well blended.
Use a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
With electric mixer, beat sugar and butter together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to batter along with vanilla and nuts.
Beat again.
Turn batter into pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove from oven and cool on rack.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Mix the flour, salt and pepper.
Coat the chicken pieces. Heat the oil and then brown and cook chicken until cooked well. Remove chicken from pan and set aside and keep warm.
Add the onions and garlic to the frying pan and stir in the paprika, cooking for one minute.
Stir in the chicken broth and bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened.
Stir in the sour cream and cook for 2 minutes or until heated through. Arrange chicken on top of the noodles and top chicken with the sauce.

title: dirty rice
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Stir in the consomme and onion
soup, then 1 cup rice.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and
put through cookie press for desired shapes.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: chuck wagon steak
directions: Pound in flour in the steak on top of the stove.
Add all ingredients, then boil slowly until meat is tender, about 3/4 of an hour or so.
Delicious with mashed potatoes.

title: shrimp and green noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Line a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish with noodles.
In large frying pan, saute shrimp in butter until pink and tender (about 5 minutes).
Cover noodles with shrimp.
Combine soup, sour cream, mayonnaise and chives. Add mustard and sherry.
Pour sauce over shrimp and sprinkle Cheddar cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients with enough boiling water to form a semi-firm patty.
Fry in deep oil and cook to golden brown.

title: cobbler
directions: (Spray pan with Pam.)
Mix together all but fruit and butter. Melt stick of butter in pan.
Pour batter in 9 x 13 pan, then pour fruit in the center.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add cinnamon if you like.

title: heavenly hashsocorro, new mexico
directions: Drain liquid from berries and pineapples and use for liquid in jello.

title: chicken and biscuit
directions: Heat soup in pot until all lumps are out.
Place biscuits in baking pan in single layers.
When soup is hot and thinned out, pour soup over biscuits and cook until biscuits are golden brown. Heat oven according to biscuit can.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Chop fine and blend together the onion, green pepper and eggs. Add mayonnaise, chili sauce and relish.
Mix well.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator to blend flavors.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: cookies
directions: Put them in the microwave.
Set the timer first.
Check on them and if they're not ready, you set the timer some more.
And then you eat them!
They taste delicious!

title: individual meat loaves
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together and form into individual meat loaves (6 or 8). Place into shallow baking dish; set aside.

title: royal greek salad
directions: In a large bowl combine lettuce, cucumber, tomato, celery and onion.
Marinate in your favorite red wine vinegar and oil dressing for 1/2 hour.
Toss, then place on huge platter.
Add beets, peppers and black olives; sprinkle crumbled Feta cheese over salad. Chill and serve.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup warm water.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: chili soup
directions: Adjust seasoning according to your taste.
You can add more water, bouillon and instant potatoes if the spices are more than you want.
This makes a lot, but it freezes well.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix margarine and powdered sugar.
Add graham crackers, peanut butter and vanilla.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on top.
Chill thoroughly.
Serves 12.

title: autumn pudding
directions: Cook apples and most of the blackberries, sugar and half the water until soft and tender.
Dissolve gelatin in remaining hot water and add to cooled fruit mixture.
Line a pudding basin with bread and pour in fruit mixture.
Cover with a circle of bread, a saucer and a weight on top.
Leave to set overnight.
Turn out, sprinkle with sugar and decorate with blackberries.
Serve with whipped cream or custard sauce.

title: special boiled shrimp
directions: In an adequate cauldron containing 2 gallons of water, place salt, bay leaves, garlic clove and mustard.
Bring to a boil and add shrimp and maintain the boil until the shrimp float and are easily removed from the shell.
Drain and place in the refrigerator with a damp pad of paper towels until cold and ready to eat with your favorite cocktail sauce.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken in baking dish and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Turn oven off and let set 5 to 10 minutes longer in oven to firm.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and green peppers in fat slowly, until tender.
Add hamburg and fry until brown.
Add tomatoes, rice, salt, pepper and chili powder and mix thoroughly.
Pour into casserole.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oleo, then add eggs and apples. Add flour sifted with baking soda and spices. Add nuts. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Omit baking soda if self-rising flour is used.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Beat until creamy and the glossy look is gone.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cherry nut ice cream(this was my grandpa's favorite ice cream!)
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, lemon, vanilla, milk and cream. Blend thoroughly.
Pour into a gallon freezer can.
Pack with ice and salt.
Freeze until almost firm.
Add fruit and nuts.
Complete freezing.

title: chocolate swirl cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in a large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, 1 teaspoon baking soda and salt; add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Combine syrup and 1/4 teaspoon baking soda.
Measure 2 cups batter into a small bowl; blend in syrup mixture.
Add coconut to remaining batter; pour into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Pour chocolate batter over vanilla batter in pan; do not mix.
Bake at 350° about 70 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan. Cool completely; glaze or frost as desired.

title: swiss chocolate crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare chocolate pudding and spread pudding in bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Combine dry cake mix, nuts or coconut and melted butter.
Sprinkle over pudding and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until center of Crunch springs back when touched lightly with finger.

title: pizza bars
directions: Beat together cake mix and butter until it forms a soft light mixture.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Add marshmallows. Sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Sprinkle on butterscotch chips. Add milk, poured over the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: In large bowl, break up crab meat into fine shreds; mix in remaining ingredients, except butter or margarine and lemon wedges.
Divide mixture into 8 portions.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat into hot butter or margarine, spoon 4 portions; with pancake turner, lightly flatten portions into patties.
Fry patties until golden brown.
Repeat with other 4 portions.
Serve with tartar sauce and lemon wedges.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Scrape larger seeds out of cucumbers.
Combine ingredients in blender or food processor.
Process thoroughly.
Chill for several hours.
Garnish with dill weed or chives.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Mix soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add carrots.
Mix and put in refrigerator.
Will keep for several days.

title: monkey bread(cinnamon pull aparts)
directions: Grease and flour an angel food cake pan or Bundt pan.
Cut biscuits into quarters and dip in a mixture of 1/2 cup white sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Place biscuits in pan.
In saucepan, melt the margarine, 3/4 cup white sugar and 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon. Pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes and invert on plate.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos (save 1 cup for the top).
Melt butter, pour over Oreos and spread into cake pan.
Mix cream cheese, milk and pudding together; fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Spread rest of Oreos on top.
Chill.

title: fast easy moms pizza
directions: Cut english muffins in half, put tbsp. pizza sauce on each add cheese on each and meat, put on bakers pan and put under broiler for 5-10 minutes and watch very closely they could burn if not watched, easy supper or snack for the kids they will be a big hit.

title: edna's baking powder biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift the flour, baking powder, cream of tartar, salt and sugar.
Add shortening and blend with pastry blender or 2 forks until the consistency of coarse cornmeal. Combine egg and milk; beat well.
Pour liquid mixture into the dough and stir with a fork unti just blended.
Put on floured board and knead about 5 minutes.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: tofu lasagna
directions: Cook the noodles as directed.
Wash with cold water; set aside.
Have sauce, grated cheese, mushrooms and parsley ready for assembly.
Mix tofu, Parmesan and garlic.
Line the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan with a layer of noodles.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the tofu mixture, 1/2 of the mushrooms, 1/2 of parsley, 1/2 cup of sauce and some cheese.
Repeat steps, ending with a layer of noodles. Sprinkle with cheese and top with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pork chop stuffing
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides and place in baking dish.
Mix crumbs, onions, butter, 1/2 c. water and seasoning.
Blend soup with the other 1/2 c. water and pour over stuffing.
Add stuffing mixture on top of the pork chops and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: glazed apples
directions: Mix sugar and water and add a few drops of red food coloring. Boil 6 minutes.
Add apples, peeled if desired, quartered and cored.
Add margarine and cook until syrup is thick and apples are tender.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Soften margarine and cream cheese.
Blend in flour.
Pinch off enough dough and roll into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls.
Press into small muffin tins to form tarts.

title: teriyaki
directions: Slice meat across the grain in very thin slices.
Marinate for 4 hours.
Use round steak or chuck.
Broil for 10 to 12 minutes or less.

title: best sugar cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheets.
Preheat oven at 400° for 10 minutes. Sift dry ingredients 5 times.
Cream the butter and shortening until mixed. Add sugar and flavorings and cream well.
Beat in eggs until fluffy. Add flour in 2 or 3 portions.
Mix until smooth. Add milk and mix.
Chill 1 hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak into long strips.
Cut green peppers into strips.
Cut tomatoes into quarters.
Lightly brown the meat in oil; add peppers, onion, garlic, tomatoes and cumin, then salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine butter, flour and pecans, mixing well.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes (cool completely). Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 1/2 cups whipped topping; blend thoroughly.
Spread over crust; chill.
Combine pudding mixes and milk; beat 2 minutes with mixer at medium speed. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding layer, garnish with finely chopped pecans and refrigerate for several hours.

title: sauce piquant
directions: Fry deboned chicken in oil.
Remove chicken.
Add flour to oil and brown.
Add onions, celery and bell pepper.
Add garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Fry for a few minutes.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and cream of mushroom soup.
Add handful onion tops and parsley.

title: "the ribs" hot bacon dressing(shawano, wi)
directions: Blend first 8 ingredients in food processor or blender.
Heat to desired warmth.
Use as dressing over spinach, bacon and eggs. Add Roquefort, if desired.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Pour oil in a large skillet or chicken fryer.
Heat until few drops of water dance when dropped in oil.
Heat should be on medium-high.
In a saucepan, under medium heat, mix bottle of hot sauce, honey and margarine until margarine is melted; stir.
Turn heat to low and let simmer for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour into a container with a lid.
Rinse the chicken wings under cold water. Drain water.
Dredge wings in the mixed seasonings.

title: herbed zucchini casserole
directions: Combine squash, tomatoes and onion in greased casserole. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, basil and oregano.
Dot with butter. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until squash is tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate chip kiss cookies(yields 4 dozen)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove wrappers from chocolate pieces. In large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add flour; blend until smooth.
Stir in small chocolate chips.
Mold scant tablespoon dough around each chocolate piece, covering completely.
Shape into a ball; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set. Cool; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Enjoy!

title: baked crispy chicken
directions: Combine egg, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, red pepper sauce, onion and celery salt.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Marinate overnight or several hours in the refrigerator, turning chicken several times.
Melt butter or margarine.
Coat chicken pieces in potato flakes until well coated.
Bake skin side down at 400° for 25 minutes.
Turn and bake for 20 to 30 minutes more until chicken is done.

title: caribbean chicken salad
directions: Broil chicken and cut up into small chunks.
Combine chopped walnuts, celery, red onion, raisins, cantaloupe (cut into small cubes) and mayonnaise or Miracle whip.
Blend well and add chicken. Serve on bulky rolls or pita bread.

title: chocolate chip scones
directions: Combine flour, sugar, biscuit mix and chips and mix.
Melt margarine; add to milk.
Combine wet ingredients with dry ingredients.
Mix quickly into soft dough.
Turn onto floured surface and knead lightly.
Roll out to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick and cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes until done all the way through.
Makes about 2 dozen scones.

title: fiesta roll-ups
directions: Combine the black beans, cream cheese, sour cream, seasoned salt and garlic salt in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until blended scraping the bowl occasionally.
Stir in the monterey jack cheese, red onion and green olives.
Spread the bean mixture over 1 side of each of the tortillas; roll to enclose the filling. Chill, tightly wrapped in plastic wrap for 2 hours.
Cut into 3/4 in slices just before serving.

title: taco pie
directions: Fry and drain meat.
In large pan, mix garlic powder, all soup, 1/2 can water, onion and taco sauce.
Add meat and heat until hot; add cheese.
Cook on low heat until cheese is melted. Stir in chips and serve immediately.

title: hungarian cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers very thin.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Squeeze out all liquid and mix with sour cream and seasonings.
Sprinkle paprika on top for color. Serve cold.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out thawed bread dough into rectangle.
Divide ingredients into half and put half on each rectangle in order listed.
Roll up dough, pinch together and seal.
Place on greased cookie sheet and brush dough with milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Done when bread is golden brown.

title: choco-lite brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom only of an 8-inch square pan. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt; blend well.
Add margarine, vanilla and eggs. Stir just to combine.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 18 to 23 minutes or until set. Do not overbake.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cool completely. Cut into bars.
Yields 24 bars.

title: raisin waffles
directions: Mix flour, salt,
baking powder and cinnamon in large bowl. Beat egg whites until stiff in separate bowl.
Mix yolks, milk, oil and raisins in third bowl.
Add milk mixture to flour mixture. Stir just until blended.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour onto hot waffle iron.

title: peanut butter salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together well in a small bowl with electric beaters or a wire whisk.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes, onion and cilantro; add Key lime juice, salt, pepper and picante sauce.
Mix well.
Serve immediately with Tostitos chips.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Keep refrigerated.
Best when made 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.
A good substitute for potato salad.

title: chocolate-nut bars
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sweetened condensed milk, chocolate pieces, pecans and vanilla in bowl; mix well.
Spread mixture in greased 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Microwave (High setting) for 8 minutes, or until top of mixture is dry, giving dish one-quarter turn three times.
Cool in dish on wooden board or heatproof counter.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 32.

title: cherry pizza
directions: Make pastry and pat on pizza pan.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.
Mix cheese, sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Pour over crust and bake 10 minutes.
Spread filling and chill.

title: banana nut brownies
directions: In a bowl combine butter, sugar, and cocoa.
Stir in eggs, milk, and vanilla.
Blend in flour, baking powder, and salt.
Stir in bananas and nuts.

title: sweet and sour sauce for grilled meats
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over desired meat (beef, deboned chicken breasts or chicken breast strips for fajitas). Refrigerate overnight.
Grill, broil or bake.

title: mama's hot water corn bread
directions: Bring 2 quarts water to a rolling boil.
Mix dry ingredients together while water is heating.
Add boiling water to dry ingredients to form a mush.
Use a wooden spoon so as not to pull heat out of mixture.

title: garden loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan with foil; grease foil.
In a large bowl, stir together onion, celery, carrots, green pepper, walnuts, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and dillweed.
In a small bowl, stir together the mayonnaise and eggs until smooth.
Stir mayonnaise mixture into vegetable mixture until well mixed.
Pour mixture into prepared pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool in pan for 15 minutes, then invert loaf and remove foil.
Place right side up on serving platter and serve immediately.
Loaf may also be kept in refrigerator and reheated for serving the next day.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken salad
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in teriyaki sauce for several hours. Bake in microwave until cooked.
Cut into cubes.
Fry won ton strips in a little sesame oil or vegetable oil until crisp.
Drain on paper towels. Boil the sugar, vinegar, salt, oil, pepper and sweet and sour sauce.
Cool.
Mix lettuce with chicken, sesame seed and green onions.
Add dressing and won tons immediately before serving.
Serves 6.

title: taco seasoning substitute
directions: Mix all together.
This is a substitute for 1 package of taco seasoning.

title: mom's deep refried sardines
directions: Pat sardines lightly to dry; remove head and tail.
Dip in flour, then into eggs.
Roll in dry bread crumbs.
Heat fat to 350°.
Add only as many sardines at one time as will float uncrowded one layer deep.
Deep fry 3 minutes or until lightly browned.
Turn sardines often.
Remove to absorbent paper; keep warm.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch buttered dish.
Pour undiluted soup over ground beef and onion. Spread vegetables over beef.
Spread potatoes over top of mixed vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Add milk if thick.
Serve with corn chips.
Great at parties.

title: unkie's barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer several hours.
Barbecue chicken in basket about 2 1/2 hours.
Baste frequently.
This is especially good on chicken.

title: meat balls in sauce
directions: Melt the butter in frying pan and add green pepper and onion. Cook until tender.
Stir in chicken and rice soup, tomato soup and beef stock.
Using the first four ingredients, make meatballs. After the meatballs are cooked, drop them into soup mixture. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, oil, sugar and eggs. Beat with spoon until well blended. Fold in cake mix and blend until smooth, forming a stiff dough. Drop by teaspoonfuls on a baking sheet 2 inches apart. Press with fork and sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 2 dozen.

title: 7- up cake
directions: Prepare cake from first five ingredients.
Bake in an oiled and floured 12 X 9 inch pan for 45 minutes.
When cool, frost.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well and press into an 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: old henry bars
directions: Stir melted margarine into brown sugar and oats in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Press into a well-greased jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch). Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove pan from oven and turn heat down to 200°.
Cool slightly and then spread with peanut butter and sprinkle with chips.
Return to oven for 3 or 4 minutes until chips soften enough to spread over peanut butter. Score into bars and refrigerate.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Remove shells from eggs.
Halve eggs lengthwise. Carefully remove yolks and place in a small bowl.
Mash yolks with fork. Add mayonnaise, dressing and paprika.
Mix well.
Lightly spoon back into egg white halves. Sprinkle with additional paprika or black pepper.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: rice and shells
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in uncovered dish at 350° for about an hour (until liquid is absorbed).
Cover when out of oven.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place generous amount on hamburger buns.
Wrap individually in foil.
Heat in oven about 20 minutes until cheese is melted at 350°.

title: steam ahead broccoli
directions: Rinse the broccoli and separate into florets from the stalks. Trim the stalks by peeling away 1/8-inch of the outer peel. Cut the stalks in spears or pieces as desired. Cut the florets to the desired size. Place 1/2-inch water in a 10 to 12-inch saut pan and bring to a boil. Add the stalks first, then the florets. Cover the pan; bring the water back to a boil and simmer for 2 to 3 minutes. When the broccoli is a bright green color, remove the pan from the heat. Drain the water and immediately run cold water into the pan. This will stop the cooking process and retain the beautiful color of the broccoli. When the broccoli is cold, drain it and set aside until you are ready to reheat it.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, salt and pepper; drain.
Cover 13 x 9-inch baking dish with shredded potatoes and top with onion, hamburger, cheese, soup and water.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: cranberry souffle
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Heat cranberry sauce until melted.
Then, strain off 1/2 cup juice, adding it to dissolved gelatin.
Next, blend together mayonnaise and cream cheese and add to gelatin mixture with lemon juice and salt.
Blend thoroughly. Turn into freezing tray and chill until firm 1-inch in from edge but soft in center (20 to 25 minutes).
Turn into bowl and whip until fluffy.
Fold in remaining cranberry sauce, diced oranges, nuts and celery.
Pour into molds and chill until firm (about 1 hour).
Unmold; garnish with salad greens and top with Hellmann's real mayonnaise.

title: worlds best cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg and mix well.
Add oil, mix well.
Add oatmeal, corn flakes, coconut and nuts; stir well. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture, mix well and add vanilla. Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake a 325° for 12 minutes or until they are light brown.
This makes "gobs of cookies".
They freeze well.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Make white sauce (milk, flour, butter and salt).
Beat egg whites until stiff.
To the white sauce add cheese and beaten egg yolks.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour in a buttered souffle dish and set in a pan of hot water.
Bake 45 minutes or until firm in a slow oven and serve at once.

title: peanuts and pretzel candy
directions: Melt chocolate.
Stir in peanuts and pretzels.
Drop by spoon on wax paper.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix mushroom soup, water and rice.
Place in bottom of roaster or casserole.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle soup mix over chicken and cover.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: spoon bread
directions: Put milk in saucepan over medium heat. Slowly stir in cornmeal and cook, stirring occasionally, until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and salt.
(If you use salted butter, omit added salt.)
Set aside to cool for 15 minutes.
Fold beaten eggs into cooled mixture.
Stir well, but do not beat.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 quart souffle dish or baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until bread has risen well and top is lightly browned.

title: pecan chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow dish or plastic bag. Pour dressing over chicken. Cover and marinate in refrigerate for 1 hour. Drain, dip chicken in combined crumbs and pecans; press to coat. Cook chicken in margarine in large skillet over medium heat 10 minutes on each side until tender.

title: all strong men go crazy some time
directions: Here's one for cooks with poor memories at the grocery store. The name supplies clues to the ingredients.

title: quick and easy hash
directions: Brown meat, onion and potatoes in a little shortening or oil in a skillet.
Add broth or gravy and simmer, covered, until heated through.
Season to taste.
Add a little more liquid, if it gets too dry.

title: artichoke quiche
directions: Beat eggs.
Drain artichokes; cut and set aside.
Saute onion in some of the artichoke marinade.
Cool.
Add artichokes, onion and croutons to the eggs.
Stir in the pepper, oregano and parsley, then the cheese.
Pour into buttered pie tin (for cutting into dinner portions) or into a square baking tin (for cutting into cocktail bites).
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until browned and bubbly.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together 2 or 3 times in a bowl the flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add the eggs, oil and carrots.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour the mixture into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or two 9-inch round pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix and bake 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 of cheese mixture and brown.

title: asparagus spears with lemon tarragon butter
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in tarragon and lemon peel.
Simmer 2 minutes over low heat.
Pour over warm asparagus.
Serves 4.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine margarine, eggs, sugar, corn syrup, oats, salt and vanilla in bowl; mix well.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Spoon into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
In the same pan, stir in other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes. Take a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with corn chips.
Over that you pour the prepared meat mixture.
Sprinkle the cheese on top so it covers the pan good.
Bake at 375° until cheese is brown and corn chips have absorbed liquid.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Chop cooked chicken to measure 3 cups.
Mix in salad bowl with chopped celery, drained canned mandarin oranges, drained canned pineapple and toasted almonds.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook 10 minutes after boiling, stirring constantly.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well. Add cinnamon and milk and sweet potatoes.
Mix well and spread in baking dish.

title: porcupines(method:  skillet)
directions: Finely chop onion.
In a large bowl, mix together the meat, rice, salt, onion, garlic salt, pepper and 1/2 cup water.
Shape meat mixture into tablespoon size balls.
Brown meatballs in large skillet; drain fat from meat into a heat-resistant can.
In medium bowl, stir together the tomato sauce, 1 cup water and the Worcestershire sauce.
Pour sauce over meatballs.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute until tender the green pepper in 1/2 cup of milk and scald the rest of milk.
Melt butter; add flour and scalded milk, then add green pepper and remaining milk. Add mustard, nutmeg, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper; add cream sauce to crab and egg mixture.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and grated white American cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces and spread 1/3 in bowl.
Next mix pudding as directed on box.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour 1/3 of pudding mixture over angel food cake, then sprinkle 2 crushed candy bars.
Layer all this until used up.

title: sarama(yield: 8 servings)
directions: 1. Par broil cabbage.
Remove from pan and let cook some 2 cups of water in pan.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes at 450°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scallops florentine
directions: Thaw scallops, if frozen.
Cut any large scallops in half. Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well.
Keep warm.
Meanwhile, in a medium skillet combine water, wine, salt, tarragon, pepper and garlic.
Bring to boiling; add scallops. Cover and simmer for 1 to 2 minutes or until scallops are opaque. Remove scallops from skillet with slotted spoon.
In a small bowl combine milk and flour.
Stir into liquid in skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 1 minute more. Stir Parmesan cheese into mixture in the skillet.
Return scallops to skillet; heat through.
Serve scallop mixture over spinach. Makes 2 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Melt margarine in pan; add potatoes and onion.
Pour soup over potatoes.
(Do not mix).
Mix sour cream and oregano and pour over potatoes.
(Do not mix).
Sprinkle 2 cups cheese over potatoes.
Sprinkle 1 cup corn flake crumbs over top.
(Do not mix).
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot. Great for any occasion.

title: chili con carne and beans
directions: Brown meat.
Drain fat; reserve 1 tablespoon.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in fat.
Put meat and onion mixture in large pot.
Add all ingredients except beans.
Rinse salsa jar and cans with water and add to pot.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add beans and simmer 15 minutes more.
Add more water if needed.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Top chili with chopped onions and grated Cheddar cheese.

title: jammed up chicken
directions: Mix together the salad dressing, jam and soup.
Place chicken pieces in a baking dish and put mixture over them and let stand a few hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: cream puff pie chocolate eclair
directions: Beat sugar, milk and pudding; mix until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip or Dream Whip.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with oil.
Place a layer of graham crackers on bottom of foil pan; top with 1/2 of pudding mixture, then add another layer of graham crackers.
Add rest of pudding mixture, then finish with layer of graham crackers on top and ice with chocolate icing, then add almonds. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in pan the sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo (medium heat) until it starts to boil. Remove from heat, cool 1 minute, then add other ingredients.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding enough flour to make stiff (but can still stir).
Put into loaf pan and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Boil 6 quarts of water with 2 tablespoons of salt.
When boiling, add spaghetti and cook until desired doneness.
Pour oil in serving bowl.
Add chopped tomatoes.
In separate bowl, mash garlic with salt.
Add to tomatoes and oil.
Add basil and ground pepper to taste.
Cover and let stand for an hour.
Drain hot spaghetti and toss in a bowl with sauce.
Serve at once.

title: coolest banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk in large bowl.
Stir in whipped topping, sour cream and Miracle Whip.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, 1 1/2 cups cheese, sour cream and green onion.
Soften tortillas in oil (hot).
Top each tortilla with 1/2 cup chicken mixture.
Roll tortilla; repeat.
Top with cheese and taco sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Cover with foil the last 10 minutes if enchiladas get too hard.
May add sour cream.

title: granny's sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in large pot until tender (about 20 minutes). Drain and when cool enough to handle, remove skin.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
The potatoes will be in long wedges.
Arrange in a greased shallow baking dish.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Thinly slice apple.
Place orange juice, brown sugar, molasses, cinnamon and nutmeg in small pan.
Bring to boil and cook 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue burger mix
directions: Brown meat in skillet; add vegetables.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns; garnish with pickle slices.

title: home town potato salad
directions: Dice 4 hard-boiled eggs with fork.
Mix all ingredients in large jar, except potatoes.
Put diced eggs with potatoes in large mixing bowl.
Pour jar full of ingredients over potatoes and eggs. Mix together gently.

title: next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: bama chicken
directions: If gravy is desired, when almost tender, add about 2 cups of water and bring to a boil.
Mix flour, Kitchen Bouquet and 1/4 cup of water.
Slowly pour this mixture into boiling liquid, stirring constantly.
(If liquid is not boiling and mixture is not stirred in well, gravy will have lumps.)
When well mixed, lower fire and continue to simmer until chicken is tender.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix everything together, except sausage.
Add sausage.
Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake on cookie sheet, covered with foil, for 15 minutes at 325°.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter
directions: Peel oranges very carefully; separate each section and put it on a plate or cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Eat with a toothpick.

title: corn pudding
directions: Do not drain corn.
Mix all together. Pour into 2 qt. greased dish.
Cover and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake uncovered another 15 minutes.
8 -10 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Place hamburger in microwave-safe colander and place in microwave-safe bowl.
Cook at 70% for 5 minutes.
Stir to break up meat.
Repeat until meat is done.
Discard grease in bowl.
Place meat in colander under hot water.
This removes excess fat.

title: leslie's crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together the night before.
Next day, bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown and bubbly.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion and let simmer for 3 minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce and seasoned salt and let simmer 5 minutes.
In a separate pot, cook shells.
Add sauce and hamburger mixture to shells.
Layer in baking dish with cheese and pepperoni.
Sprinkle oregano on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Crumble raw ground beef into water.
Add all ingredients except spaghetti, cheese, crackers, beans and onions and bring to a boil.
Stir well, breaking meat up before it cooks.
Cover and simmer two or more hours, stirring occasionally.
The proper way to serve this chili is over spaghetti on an oval dish.
(Cut peppers in pieces and divide among plates.)

title: beefy noodle bake
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add 3 tablespoons margarine, celery and onions. Cook 10 minutes. Mix soups, milk, salt and pepper. Mix noodles with beef mixture. Then combine beef and soup mixtures together and pour into a 9 x 12 inch baking dish that has been sprayed with pam. Cover with foil and bake in 325 degrees oven for 1 hour. Uncover and sprinkle crushed chips on top. Bake 12 - 15 minutes longer uncovered.

title: divinity
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook.
To test, drop small amount in cold water.
If it forms a ball, drop on wax paper by spoonful to cool.

title: chicken flautas
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Shred and mix with rest of ingredients.
Soften tortillas in oven.
Overlap 2 tortillas by half.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Sprinkle taco seasoning on beef. Mix thoroughly.
Chill several hours.
Chop lettuce and tomatoes. Add to beef mixture with cheese.
Pour on Catalina dressing.
Mix well.
Mix half of tortillas in salad.
Just before serving, sprinkle rest of chips on top.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar thoroughly.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: low-fat oven glazed chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Arrange in a 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Spoon mixture of soup, water, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes or until chicken tests tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: jalapeno bread (hot)
directions: Mix well.
Bake in greased pan (approximately 9 x 14-inches) at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground meat with salt and pepper.
Drain.
Saute onions and green pepper with meat.
Mix mushroom soup, tomato soup and water; add garlic powder and grated cheese.
Cook spaghetti; add to meat and mix with rest of ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bill curry's barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add other ingredients, mixing well. Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: my aggie's favorite salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and store in refrigerator for up to two weeks.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°, grease and flour a tube pan.
Measure all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Blend for 30 seconds on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat for 3 minutes on high, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 60 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: frozen salad
directions: Pour water over jello and cool, but not set.
Add 7-Up.
Let mixture partially set.
Drain pineapple; save juice for topping. Fold pineapple into partially set jello.
Put marshmallows on jello when well set.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: In a 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish, melt butter or margarine on High for 40 to 60 seconds.
Roll chicken in melted butter or margarine until coated.
Combine remaining ingredients in a plastic or paper bag.
Add pieces of chicken one at a time, shaking to coat with cheese mixture.
Reserve any remaining cheese mixture; set aside.
Arrange chicken skin side down in dish, with thicker pieces to outside of dish.
Cover with a paper towel to absorb spatters.
Cook on Medium 9 to 11 minutes per pound.
After half the cooking time, turn chicken pieces skin side up.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese mixture.
Complete cooking on Medium.
Let stand 10 minutes on stay hot or brown 5 to 6 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: chinese noodle casserole
directions: Saute onions; add celery continuing to saute.
Add soup and milk.
Heat until bubbling.
Add cashews.
Place noodles in oiled casserole and pour cashew mixture over noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Mix cereal with butter.
Blend sugar into eggs.
Add cereal mixture and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Place in a pot of hot water.
Bake at 375°
for 30 minutes.
Stir.
Bake 20 minutes longer or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: turkey and dumplings(made in microwave)
directions: Combine vegetables and water and cook in microwave and drain. Stir powdered milk, cornstarch, basil and pepper into veggies. Stir in the chicken broth.
Cook, uncovered on High 6 minutes until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Stirring 1 time a minute. Stir in the turkey and cook until bubbly.

title: chicken rotel casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Reserve 1 cup of chicken broth. Pick chicken off bone.
Saute onions.
Mix soups and broth.
Heat until well blended.
Crush Doritos.
Place 3/4 of Doritos in the bottom of a buttered 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.

title: milk gravy
directions: Mix all together.
Pour mixture into skillet (make sure heat is low at first as milk mixture will clump when poured in hot grease).
After mixture has warmed, bring heat to medium, stirring constantly, when it starts to bubble (scraping bottom).
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine ingredients, except peanut butter, and boil 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter.

title: pumpkin pecan bread
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, soda, spices and salt.
Combine beaten eggs, milk, pumpkin and oil; mix well.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well until combined.
Stir in nuts.
Grease and flour 4 (7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pans when cooled completely.

title: glazed carrots and onions
directions: Cook carrots until done.
Add onions and cook 5 minutes longer; drain.
Return vegetables to saucepan.
Add butter, brown sugar, salt and ginger, stirring constantly for 5 minutes or until vegetables are glazed.

title: roasted red potatoes with lemon and olive oil(healthful eating)
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch ovenproof casserole dish, arrange potatoes. Combine lemon juice, olive oil, salt and pepper; pour over potatoes.
Roast in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender, turning 3 to 4 times to baste.

title: pasta in a pot
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Brown meat with onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Drain grease.
Add sauce to meat mixture and set aside.
Combine eggs, sour cream and Mozzarella.
Set aside.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Boil together the sugar, water, syrup, salt and cornstarch until it is thick and clear. Remove from heat and add raspberry jello and then cook 1 minute longer. Cool.
Add 1 quart fresh raspberries and pour over cooled crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pasta with potatoes
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
While noodles are cooking, prepare potatoes following directions for frying in oil.
Drain on paper towel.
Place noodles on a heated serving platter.
Add butter, Mozzarella cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and salt.
Toss until noodles are coated with butter and cheese is melted.
Spoon potatoes on top of noodles.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Serves 8.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Use buttermilk to make thick batter.
Drop by spoon in hot shortening.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together with mixer on medium speed. Add mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Add oil slowly until absorbed.

title: mexican dumplings
directions: Brown onion and garlic in oil.
Add hamburger and brown. Drain well.
Add tomato and salsa.
Roll crescents into 1/4-inch balls and drop in.
Place cover to partly cover pan.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Cover until cheese melts.

title: mushroom-sherry bisque(makes 4 cups)
directions: Finely chop 1/2 pound mushrooms and onion in blender or processor.
Transfer to heavy saucepan.
Add broth.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
