title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake.
Crumble half in bowl.
Spread half of mousse over cake then half of Cool Whip and sprinkle 1/2 crushed candy.
Repeat layers.
You may use chocolate Cool Whip.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Sprinkle on chili powder and garlic to taste.
Add tomatoes, beans, water and rice.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Top with crushed chips and grated cheese. Cover until cheese melts.
Serve in skillet.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix with butter, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Press into bottom of casserole dish.
Saute onion and green pepper. Cook meat. Add remaining ingredients.
Put cottage cheese on top of noodles, then meat mixture.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.
Add Mozzarella cheese and cook 10 more minutes.

title: walnut pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs about 3 minutes.
Add sugar and mix well.
Then add remaining cake ingredients.
Pour batter onto a jelly roll pan lined with foil, sprayed generously with cooking spray.
If nuts are desired just sprinkle onto batter.
Bake at 375° for 12-15 minutes.
While cake is baking prepare a piece of waxed paper sprinkled with powdered sugar to turn the cake out on, roll cake up and set aside to cool.

title: quick fruit pie
directions: Melt the stick of butter or oleo in the pan you will be baking in.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk and pour batter into pan.
Put fruit over top of batter.
Batter rises to top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: seafood linguine
directions: Cook pasta.
Saute garlic and oregano in butter, stirring frequently, about 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, until the cheese melts.
Place hot cooked pasta on serving plate; top with sauce.

title: black beans and rice
directions: May use any raw vegetable you desire.

title: "copper pennies"
directions: Layer carrots, green pepper and onion in a dish.
Heat remaining ingredients.
Do not boil.
Pour over carrot mixture and let set in refrigerator for at least 24 hours before serving.

title: mexican supper
directions: Saute beef and onion in oil until blood cannot be seen.
Add all other ingredients except cheese and tortillas.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
In large casserole baking dish, cover bottom 1/8-inch deep with meat mixture.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Add a layer of tortillas.
Alternate meat, cheese and tortillas, ending with meat and cheese, until all has been added.
Bake about 25 to 30 minutes or until cheese top is slightly brown in a 375° oven.
Makes about 10 to 12 servings.

title: salad dressing
directions: Using funnel, pour ingredients into ketchup bottle.
Shake well before each use.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Shred or chop vegetables very fine.
Mix together with mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Spread on bread.
Make closed or open sandwiches.

title: fruited wild rice stuffing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use as stuffing for game bird, turkey, capon or chicken, or turn into buttered 2-quart casserole and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°, covered.
Yields 6 cups.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Prepare pastry.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pastry lined pie pan.
Beat eggs slightly, beat in the remaining ingredients.
Pour cream mixture into pie pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal "candy" cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk and cocoa.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute; remove from heat.
Add rest of ingredients, ending with oatmeal. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.

title: squash casserole
directions: Bake at 250° about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ginger biscuits
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add vanilla, candied ginger and ground ginger.
Mix until well blended.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients lightly.
Add the sour cream and vanilla.
Mix and combine with the flour, baking powder and salt.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix sugar and 1/2 cup margarine. Add egg yolks and extract. Form into teaspoon size balls and place in small tart pans.

title: jenn's famous sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, oil and margarine until fluffy.
Add eggs and flavoring.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Press down with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fancy fudge
directions: Thoroughly combine dry ingredients in a heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Bring to a "bubbly" boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring to 234° (soft ball stage).
Bulb of candy thermometer should not rest on bottom of saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir!
Cool at room temperature to 110°.
Beat until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
Quickly spread in a lightly buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Cool.
Makes approximately 3 dozen squares.

title: tuna chip casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, tuna and peas in bowl.
Crush chips.
Layer soup
mixture in baking dish.
Top with layer of chips, then layer of soup mixture.
Top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread slices and place pieces in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Brown sausage and drain off fat.
Spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Beat together the eggs, milk, mustard and salt and pepper and pour over mixture. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(The cheese will rise to the top during baking.)
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marge's easy cherry-chocolate cake
directions: Mix eggs and chocolate mix first, then add cherries and cinnamon.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven or until it tests done in the center.

title: red snapper
directions: Slowly saute the first 4 ingredients in oil until tender.
Add remainder of ingredients and simmer until tender (approximately 10 minutes). Serve over cooked rice.

title: shrimp in butter sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shrimp, in a large pot and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Add shrimp and bring to a boil again. Cook for 6 to 10 minutes.
Serve with plenty of French bread to dip in the butter sauce and eat along with the shrimp.
Serves 4.

title: microwave spaghetti sauce
directions: Crumble ground beef in microwave dish with green pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook on High for 2 or 3 minutes.
Keep an eye on it. Cook until no pink shows.
Put remaining ingredients in with meat and stir it.
Cook on Medium for 26 to 28 minutes in microwave.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Place the crescent rolls flat and press together to make a crust in a cookie sheet.
Then place the sausage and the cheese on the top of this crust and then mix the eggs with the milk and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ruth's original wild rice casserole
directions: Wash and soak wild rice for 4 hours. Boil until near done. Brown beef. Saute celery, onion, green pepper and pimento.
Last 2 items may be omitted. Add butter and soup. Bake until done. Add liquid if needed.
Other meats that blend well with wild rice are chicken or pork sausage.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg, if desired.

title: whipped coffee dessert
directions: Whip egg whites very stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and instant coffee.
Whip the cream and add 2 tablespoons sugar, dash of salt and vanilla.
Fold whipped cream into egg whites.
Add browned almond slivers.
Spoon into paper lined muffin cups.
Freeze. Take out of freezer shortly before serving
to slightly thaw. Serves 10.
Can be made well in advance.
Will keep in the freezer for up to two weeks.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump together into a large bowl and stir until blended.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° until the top springs back.
In a Bundt pan, bake approximately 45 minutes.
In a tube pan, bake approximately 1 hour.

title: amaretto fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips and Eagle Brand milk on low heat until well blended.
Add Amaretto and almond extract; whip well.
Pour into wax paper lined 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours or more. Roll into 1-inch balls and into chopped almonds.
Refrigerate. Make a couple of days ahead.

title: divinity
directions: Cook the sugar, water and syrup until it cracks when put in cold water.
Pour over beaten egg whites and beat.
Add nuts. Beat until mixture becomes quite stiff.
Drop on waxed paper using teaspoons.

title: poor man's noodles
directions: Combine flour, butter and salt and mix with fork.
Make well in center.
Add egg and water.
Beat with fork.

title: barbecue cocktail franks
directions: Simmer sausages in barbecue sauce until glazed, about 30 minutes.
Serve hot with toothpicks.

title: carrot spread
directions: Put all ingredients in a medium mixing bowl and blend well. Serve on warm toast or dark bread.
Keep refrigerated.

title: tomato lucee
directions: Combine everything, but tomatoes. Pour over thickly sliced tomatoes, placed in a flat-bottomed serving dish. Assemble 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Boil about 5 minutes.
Good on spareribs and chicken.

title: green and yellow squash
directions: Saute peppers, onions, garlic and mushrooms in oil until soft. Add yellow squash, sliced round and zucchini, cut on a slant. Cook slowly in own juice until tender.
Serves 6.

title: rapidrise pizza dough
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, undissolved yeast and salt.
Stir very warm water and oil into dry ingredients.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 4 to 6 minutes. Cover; let rest on floured surface for 10 minutes.
Lightly oil 1 (14-inch) or 2 (12-inch) round pizza pans.
Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Form dough into smooth ball.
Roll dough to fit pans. Add own sauce and toppings.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.
Time depends on size and thickness of crust and toppings.

title: monkey bread i
directions: In a plastic bowl with a tight-fitting lid, combine pudding mix, sugar, cinnamon and pecans, if desired. Pour the butter into a shallow bowl. Cut the biscuits into quarters. Dip several pieces into the butter, then place in the plastic bowl; cover and shake. Remove covered biscuits to a greased 10-inch fluted tube pan. Continue until all the biscuit pieces are coated. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in pan for 30 minutes before inverting onto a serving plate. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: a. gilbert's rum cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts evenly in bottom of greased and floured 10-inch tube or fluted cake pan.
Combine cake mix, eggs, water, oil and rum in a large mixing bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed with mixer for 4 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean from center of cake or cake begins to pull away from side of pan.
Don't underbake.
Cool in pan.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat eggs and cream cheese together.
Add sugar and vanilla. Pour mixture into Graham Cracker Crust.

title: caramel corn(cracker jacks)
directions: Lightly salt popcorn and set aside.
In a 3-quart saucepan bring honey or white syrup, brown sugar and margarine to a boil. Boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Take off heat and add vanilla and baking soda.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour over popcorn; add peanuts, if desired, and stir.
Butter a roasting pan and pour in caramel corn.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Butter a sheet of aluminum foil and place corn on this to cool.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of wax paper.
Pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat oil and butter in skillet.
Chicken over high heat for 3 minutes on each side.

title: hamburger cookies
directions: Separate icing into two parts; color one part yellow and the other part red.
Tint one cup of coconut green.
Bake your favorite recipe of cake like brownies.
After they cool, cut into small squares.
Take one vanilla wafer cookie, put a small amount of yellow icing on flat part of cookie, then take a square of brownie, roll into hamburger shape.
Place on top of icing, then put a little coconut on top of the brownie.
Take another cookie and put red icing on the flat part of the cookie.
Place on brownie.
Looks like a little hamburger.

title: self-crust pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except water, then stir in water gradually until well mixed.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings.
Contains 150 calories per serving.

title: vegetable pizza(appetizer or party food)
directions: Press rolls in pizza pan, joining all seams (spray pan with Pam first).
Bake at 375° until golden brown (8 to 10 minutes).

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for at least 30 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Stir cornmeal into 2 cups of milk and let
mixture come to
a boil, making a mush.
Add balance of milk and
add	well beaten eggs.
Stir in salt, baking powder and
melted
butter. Bake 30 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: spicy green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.	Drain and serve cold.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except powdered sugar and lemonade; beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Punch holes with fork all over top of cake.
Mix lemonade and sugar; pour over cake.
Bake another 5 minutes.

title: two crust blueberry pie
directions: Wash and drain berries and sift flour over them, mixing carefully, until each berry is lightly coated.
Stir the sugar well into the first and pour into a pie lined with pastry.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with an upper crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°, then about 40 or 45 minutes at 300° until golden brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Drain crushed pineapple well.
Slice cherries in half.
Mix cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted margarine together.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine eggs, 2 sticks of margarine and sugar.
Beat with electric mixer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Spread over graham cracker layer.
Put sliced bananas on next layer, crushed pineapple on next and then spread Cool Whip on top.
Add chopped cherries and sprinkle nuts on last.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: crock-pot teriyaki steak
directions: Slice steak into narrow strips and place in crock-pot Combine remaining ingredients except pea pods in small bowl.
Pour over steak.
Cover and cook on low (200°) for 6 to 8 hours.
Add partially thawed pea pods the last 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: oreo cookie pie(easy for children to make)
directions: Let ice cream soften.
Crush Oreo cookies.
Add cookies to softened ice cream.
Put mixture into shell and freeze.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Heat to boil for 3 minutes.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and combine.
Cool.
Fold in remaining ingredients; chill until firm. Cut into squares and serve with whipped topping if desired.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put Oreo cookies in food processor until they look like "dirt."
Mix butter, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Make pudding using only 3 1/2 cups milk.
Mix butter mixture and pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer filling and "dirt" in a flower pot making sure to leave enough "dirt" for the top.
Plastic plant is optional.

title: rudolph cinnamon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients (except gumdrops) in a large bowl. Put quarter size amounts of dough on a buttered pan. Bake 350° for 10 - 20 minutes. Add one gumdrop to each cookie for red rudolph nose.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Butter 9-inch pie pan.
Put washed berries on bottom; sprinkle sugar and chopped nuts over the berries.
Cream butter, sugar, flour, eggs and extract.
Pour over berry mixture and bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage-corn casserole
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet; drain grease.
Put all but 1/2 cup in a buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Stir 1 cup stuffing mix into sausage remaining in skillet; reserve.
Combine corn with onion and remaining stuffing mix.
Spoon into dish on top of sausage.
Put skillet mixture over corn.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: apple bran walnut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 (1/2-cup) muffin tins.
Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Whisk buttermilk, oil and eggs in small bowl.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until just blended. Let stand 15 minutes at room temperature.
(Batter can be prepared 2 days ahead and refrigerated.)
Mix remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of batter into prepared tins.
Cover evenly with apple mixture.
Spoon remaining batter into tins.
Bake until tester comes out clean, about 23 minutes.
Cool on rack at least 3 minutes.
Muffins may be kept, wrapped in foil and frozen, for up to 2 months.
Rewarm in oven before serving.

title: applets or cotlets
directions: Cook apples for 1 minute; add sugar and simmer for 30 minutes. Soak gelatin in water; add to apples, dissolve, remove from stove.
Add Rose flavoring, nuts and lemon juice.
Pour into buttered pan dusted with powdered sugar.
Cool; cut in squares and roll in powdered sugar.
Dry.
Note:
For cotlets use 1 c. apricot puree (baby food) instead of grated apples.
Leave out Rose flavoring.

title: glorified corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Cut into squares and serve hot. May be frozen.

title: quiche
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in prepared pie crust.
Bake at 450° (placing pie on cookie sheet) for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken and barley bake
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine onion, carrots, water, barley, bouillon granules, poultry seasoning and garlic.
Heat mixture to boiling.
Pour hot mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange chicken breast atop mixture.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until tender.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shake and scramble breakfast
directions: In a container with a tight fitting lid, combine the first 5 ingredients.
Cover and shake until well mixed.
In a small skillet, melt butter over medium heat; add egg mixture.
Cook and stir until eggs are completely set.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Stir in shortening. Meanwhile, dissolve yeast in warm water. Add with buttermilk to flour mixture to make soft dough. Turn on lightly floured board. Roll to 1/4 inch thickness. Cut with round cutter. Brush with melted butter and fold over to make pocketbook rolls. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or light brown. Dough does not have to rise before baking. Dough may be stored in refrigerator before baking.

title: pecan delight
directions: Beat egg whites.
Fold in sugar, pecans, crackers and vanilla. Place in greased pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes. Top with whipped cream.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls and refrigerate overnight.
Roll balls in melted almond bark, vanilla and/or chocolate.
Makes about 40 balls.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except soup.
Form balls.
Roll balls in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Brown meatballs in oil. Remove meatballs.
Pour off oil.
In same pan, add can of soup and 1/2 cup of water.
Bring to boil.
Return meatballs to pan. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: boardwalk fries(serves 4)
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut into French fry wedges.
Place in bowl of cold water for 5 minutes to crisp.
Put potato and remaining ingredients in large Ziploc bag.
Shake to coat.
Empty into baking dish in a single layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Brown beef.
Add taco seasoning and tomato sauce.
Heat tortillas.
Fill with meat, roll and put in casserole dish.
Pour heated enchilada sauce over tortillas. Sprinkle cheese and olives on top.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine margarine, flour and brown sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: candy orange slice cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Place flour in large bowl; add dates.
Dice and slice orange slices; chop the nuts.
Coat the orange slices and dates with flour.
Add this and coconut to cream mixture.
This makes stiff dough that should be mixed with hands. Place in greased 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan.
Bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours at

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients; beat one minute.
Add remaining ingredients and beat another one minute on medium speed.
Makes 2 or 3 loaves.
Grease pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: mincemeat
directions: Put all in large kettle or roaster and cook slowly for several hours.
Stir frequently to prevent catching on.

title: lasagna
directions: Grease 1 (4-quart) or 2 (2-quart) baking dishes.
Cook celery, onion and garlic in fat drippings until tender.
Add ground beef and brown until crumbly but not hard.
Pour off drippings.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, cayenne pepper and bay leaf.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender.
Arrange half of the noodles in the baking dish.
Pour half the sauce over noodles. Cover with a layer of cottage cheese and mozzarella cheese. Repeat with remaining noodles, sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lisa's chicken dish
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and wine in bowl.
Blend well.
Layer in casserole the chicken, mushrooms, sauce.
Put a little sauce in bottom first.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fried mushroom nuggets(appetizers)
directions: Rinse mushrooms and pat dry with paper towels.
In a bowl, blend the flour, garlic salt and club soda until smooth.
Dip mushrooms in batter and fry in about 1-inch of oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels before serving.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water in a large bowl. Let stand 5 minutes.
Add oil and remaining ingredients.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 4 hours. Stir again and spoon into well-greased muffin tins, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes until golden.

title: mulligatawny soup
directions: Cook onions, celery and carrots in soup pot in olive oil until tender.
Add margarine, flour and curry powder.
Stir and cook for one minute.
Add chicken broth; bring to boil.
Add chicken; simmer for one minute.
Add apple, rice, thyme and pepper and simmer for 15 minutes more.
Makes six 1 cup servings with 156 calories each.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in an oblong pan at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: workperson's roast
directions: Place the roast in center of large sheet of foil wrap.
Cut slits in roast and push in cut sections of fresh garlic.
Pour mushroom soup over roast.
Pour the Worcestershire sauce over soup.
Sprinkle dry soup over that.
Add seasoning salt, salt and pepper to taste.
Add meat tenderizer, depending on cut of meat. Pull foil up and seal across top and ends; be sure it is sealed tightly, leaving space above and around roast.
Place in cake pan and put in oven at 250° from 7:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.
Your roast is tender and juicy and your gravy is made, too.
Enjoy it.

title: grandmama's butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread out on cookie sheet.
Brush top with beaten egg whites and sprinkle top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate before serving.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Melt the caramels on low heat with the cream.
May use half and half or mocha mix.

title: sticky buns(for breakfast)
directions: Thaw bread and break into small uniform chunks.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan (can add nuts or raisins).
In saucepan, melt butter, stir in dry pudding, brown sugar, cinnamon and milk. Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cool and pour evenly over bread.
Cover with damp towel, place in warm place until bread reaches top of pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Invert immediately over serving platter.
Serve warm.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Rinse heaping cup of medium grain rice (not instant rice). Heat milk; add rice.
Cook rice and milk until rice is soft.
Beat 6 egg yolks.
Add sugar and salt to rice when soft.
Add beaten egg yolks and stir fast to whip pudding.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Remove from heat.
As pudding cools, fluff every 10 minutes or so.
Great warm or cold.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese. Pour into greased casserole dish; top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Beat with egg.
Add the other ingredients and cook until thick, but do not boil.
Chill.
Good over any combination of fruit.

title: good beef roast
directions: Boil water, onion and bouillon in small saucepan until onion is just tender.
Place roast in roaster pan with cover.

Pour onion mixture over roast. Bake in a 375° oven until fork-tender. Remove roast. Skim fat from gravy. Leave as is and serve with roast or thicken with 2 tablespoons flour; or cook sliced carrots, quartered potatoes and 1 small onion in gravy and serve with roast.

title: jackie b's seven minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in top of a double boiler.
Place over boiling water.
Beat with mixer until mixture holds soft peaks.
Remove top of boiler; beat until mixture holds stiff peaks.
Beat in vanilla.

title: red beans and sausage
directions: Cook sausage.
Mix kidney beans, onions, tomatoes and salt and pepper, then add cooked sausage.
Place on low to moderate heat for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, shredded cheese, onion, celery and cream cheese.
Then blend in crab meat.
Then add Tabasco sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: cookie sheet slice
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir together in a bowl:
flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Spread 2/3 of batter on greased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Spread one can fruit pie filling (any kind).
Drop remaining dough on top. (Add a bit of milk to dough to make spreading easier.)
Bake in a preheated oven.

title: chicken and tomato stir-fry
directions: Mix
chicken
with
salt,
pepper and 1/2 of the onion. Let it sit for 1 hour.
Measure and prepare all other ingredients.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook Duncan Hines yellow cake mix as directed (2 layers). Allow to cool completely.
Mix and refrigerate the sour cream, sugar and thawed coconut.
When cake layers are cooked, cut them - making four layers.
Pour chilled filling between layers, reserving one cup of filling for frosting.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs in half lengthwise.
Slip out yolks and mash with fork, then add salt, dry mustard, pepper, mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Mix together well.
Fill whites with egg yolk mixture. Arrange eggs on large serving plate.
Cover and refrigerate no longer than 24 hours.

title: baked chicken wings
directions: Snip off tips from wings and cut each into 2 pieces.
Place in large bowl and add oil, honey, soy sauce, garlic and lemon juice. Season well and toss; marinate for 1 hour.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and salt; continue beating.
Fold in scalded milk, cream and vanilla.
Pour into ice cream freezer.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Put in large glass dish.
Press down in dish and put extra ketchup on top of the meat loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: "peach cobweb"
directions: Melt butter and pour it into a 9 x 12-inch shallow baking dish.
Combine dry ingredients and combine with milk and nuts to make batter.
Pour batter over melted butter in bottom of pan. Top with sliced and sugared peaches.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°. Serve either warm or cold and with whipped cream or ice cream or plain.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Mix in deep bowl the first 3 ingredients; beat with mixer until stiff peaks.
Beat a long time.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: chicken in lemon sauce
directions: In a large frying pan, place margarine and melt over medium heat.
Add chicken and saute about 10 minutes or until chicken is brown and fork can be inserted with ease.
Remove chicken to a dish appropriate for broiling in oven.
Drain margarine from pan and add wine, lemon peel and juice. Cook 1 minute.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour in cream, stirring constantly, and heat but do not boil.
Pour sauce over chicken; sprinkle with cheese and mushrooms. Set oven at broil with rack 6-inches from heat. Broil until chicken is lightly browned.
Garnish with lemon wedges and parsley.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: mexican dish a lotta
directions: Cook and drain grease off hamburger.
Add 12 ounces of picante sauce to meat.
Add 1 can of drained corn.
Simmer.

title: chicken noodle spinach bake
directions: Dip chicken in reserved chicken broth, then coat with bread crumbs; set aside.
Combine sour cream, egg, garlic and flour until smooth.
Add onion, spinach and 1/2 of cheese.
Spread in buttered baking dish.
Top with chicken and remaining bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and bake 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: veggie pizza appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Press crescent roll dough onto sides and bottom of a jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake 11 to 13 minutes until golden brown; cool.
Mix cream cheese, salad dressing, dill and onion salt until well blended.
Spread over crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Cut into 24 squares.

title: mary ann's salad delight
directions: Let first 4 ingredients simmer as you mix gelatine and water and let set 10 minutes.
Pour gelatine into pineapple mixture and let set until it starts to gel.
Add 1 cup shredded American cheese and Cool Whip.
Fold into mixture and refrigerate.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise, curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Then add the chicken, celery, grapes and almonds.
Garnish with pineapple chunks and paprika.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Mix all and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 box dry yellow cake mix on top.
Melt oleo and pour all over top of cake (and nuts, if desired).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: almond bark cookie
directions: Mix all together; form into balls any size you want. Chill. Dip in white or chocolate bark. Place on wax paper and let harden.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and set aside.
Cook prunes.
Drain off 1/4 cup juice and beat eggs, oil, buttermilk, vanilla and juice.
Then mix real good. Then add dry ingredients slowly to mixture.
Beat real good.
Bake in loaf pan, greased and floured at 350° for 1 hour.
Real moist.

title: bacon-corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble. Spoon 2 tablespoons bacon fat into round pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inches. Sprinkle with bacon.
Mix flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix in remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Carefully pour batter over bacon.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and cracks feel dry.
Immediately invert onto heatproof serving plate.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sticky rolls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine butter, brown sugar and corn syrup.
Spread evenly in an 8-inch round pan. Sprinkle with pecans. Remove breadsticks from
can and leave in coils.
Combine sugar and cinnamon. Dip one side of the coil in mixture. Arrange, sugar side down, in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar. Bake 19 to 24 minutes. Cool 1 minute.

title: margarita ice cream
directions: Combine ice cream, limeade, tequila, Cointreau, grated lime peel and lime juice in a bowl and mix well.
Freeze until firm.

title: scuppernong or muscadine hull sauce
directions: Wash and pulp grapes, separating hulls and pulp.
Use only very ripe grapes.
Cut hulls in half.
Cook until tender.
Heat pulp until seeds separate.
Run through colander to remove seeds.
Weigh to see that you have no more than 6 pounds when combined.

title: snappy chicken fingers
directions: Combine cheese, pesto and pimento.
Add chicken. Toss gently to mix.
Place roll halves on cookie sheet.
Top each roll half with chicken mixture.
Broil 5-inches from heat for 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Cut each roll half into 4 slices.
Makes 16 appetizers.

title: parmesan fish
directions: Melt the butter and saute the onions.
Add the milk and cornstarch mixture; bring to a boil.
Let mixture thicken, stirring constantly.
Add the salt; it should get to the consistency of marmalade.
In a Pyrex dish, pour enough of the sauce to cover bottom of dish; place fish on top and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over this.
Repeat layers until you have used all the sauce.
Bake at 450° until it is golden brown.
Serve with potatoes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Let stand for 10 minutes when done.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Put pineapple in bottom of flat dish.
Mix sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Pour over pineapple;
sprinkle topping on pineapple of cheese,
crackers and butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lentil soup
directions: Bring lentils, olives, mushrooms and spices to a boil in the water that the lentils have been soaked in. Reduce heat to low and simmer for approximately 1 hour. Make rice according to directions. Add lentils along with salsa. Let simmer for 15 minutes and serve.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Prepare jello following directions on jello box.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Fold into jello.
Allow this to jell firmly in refrigerator.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread on top of jello mixture.
Serve.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and mold into ball.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Place in refrigerator until chilled well.
Serve with crackers of your choice.
Good with Ritz.

title: pizza cubed steaks
directions: In 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch glass baking dish, combine first 7 ingredients.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook in countertop microwave oven for 3 minutes; stir.
Add meat in single layer; sprinkle with 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Cover; micro-cook 5 minutes.
Turn meat over; micro-cook, covered, 3 minutes more or until done.
Remove from oven.
Cut cheese in triangles; place one triangle atop each steak.
Let stand one minute to melt cheese.
Serves 4.

title: unbelievable lasagne
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking pan, spread about 1 cup sauce.
Arrange a layer of lasagne.
Top with a layer of sauce, then Ricotta cheese, ground beef, sharp Cheddar cheese and then Mozzarella cheese.
Top with lasagne and cover generously with spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Allow to stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: prize pastry
directions: Put everthang 'ceptin' watah in a bowl 'n mix wid a pastry cutter til hit looks lak meal...then very gradually add watah (mixin' all the while wid the cutter) til thoroughly mixed 'n can be handled reel easy with the hands 'n will form into a ball. Role out as needed 'n can be kept in the ice box fur 4 to 5 days.

title: sand cake
directions: Crush wafers in large plastic bag. Pour milk into large bowl. Add dry pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes, until well blended. Let stand 5 minutes. Gently stir in whipped topping and 1/2 of the crushed wafers. Spoon into 13 x 9 dish; sprinkle with remaining crushed wafers. Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve. Decorate with gummies.

title: french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread.
Soak bread in mixture. Cook on lightly oiled griddle over low heat.
Turn frequently to brown evenly.
Serve with sugar and cinnamon mixed together: maple syrup, honey or jam.
Contains 90 calories per slice.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Grease tube pan.
Sprinkle bottom of pan with chopped nuts. Stack rolls around pan.
Sprinkle pudding (dry) over rolls.
Stir melted butter, brown sugar and cinnamon together and pour over. Put in cold oven overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: long johns
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup lukewarm water; add 1 teaspoon sugar and let stand for 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients and add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Let rise 3 times, then roll to about 1/4 inch thickness and cut into desired shape.
Bake in very hot grease.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting, crushed crackers and nuts.

title: sausage omelet
directions: Brown sausage, crumble and drain it; cool.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Put into buttered 8 x 12-inch casserole. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: shirley's cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars; beat eggs and vanilla well; add to butter mixture.
Add flour, soda and cinnamon.
Mix well; add chips.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: herbed chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken and cool.
Preserve 2 cups of chicken broth. Remove chicken from bones and tear into bite-size pieces.
Place in shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Combine soups and 1 cup broth. Pour over chicken.
Mix butter and remaining cup of broth.
Stir in stuffing.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine 1 c. cream chicken soup and 1 c. sour cream. Mix together 1/2 c. butter (melted) and 2 c. stuffing mix. Boil squash for 5 min. and drain. Mix in soup and sour cream mixture. Pour in casserole dish. Cover with stuffing mixture. Cook at 350 Degree for 25-30 min. (Option-layer ingredients.)

title: pink salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and Eagle condensed milk.
Fold in strawberry pie filling.
Fold in pineapple (drain off juice). Fold in pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps for a month.

title: dido's delight pound cake
directions: Beat eggs in small bowl.
Cream together shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs to creamed mixture and cream again.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: honey drops
directions: Heat honey to boiling.
Add baking soda, butter or margarine, lemon juice and salt.
Boil to hard ball stage.
Pour into well buttered pan.
Cool.
Pull until white and porous.
Cut in 1-inch pieces.

title: salmon patties with lemon cream sauce
directions: Drain salmon and set aside the liquid. In a medium bowl, pour in the salmon and "flake" it with a fork. Chop the pepper(s) and onion and add to salmon. Beat the egg and add to salmon. Add 1/2 of the crushed crackers or bread crumbs. Add 1/4 cup retained liquid. Mix well and form into patties. (Add additional water if mixture is too dry.) Roll formed patties in the remaining crumbs. Heat small amount of oil in skillet and place in the patties. Cook over medium heat until light brown, turning only once. Drain on paper towel.

title: minutemen macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon, 1 inch apart, onto well-greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes about 30.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve 1 package lemon jello in 1 cup hot water.
Cool until starts to congeal.
Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/3 cup sugar and oleo and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream 8 ounces cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Prepare Dream Whip; add to cheese mixture.
Add both to jello.
Pour over crust and cover with favorite flavor pie filling.
Chill.

title: chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk together in microwave.
Mix cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and chips together.
Press 1/2 of dough into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread caramel mixture over the top.
Loosely spread the rest of the dough mixture over caramel layer.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in a preheated 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownie mix according to package directions.
Cool slightly.
Mix coffee and sugar.
Poke holes with a fork in brownie mix and pour coffee mixture over this.
Mix chocolate mousse according to directions.
Layer 1/2 of brownie mix in bottom of large glass bowl (crumble), then 1/2 of chocolate mousse, 1/2 of crushed candy bars and 1/2 of whipped topping.
Repeat layers. Enjoy!

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Combine corn, broccoli, egg, 1/2 cup crumbs, onion, 2 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole.
Combine 1/4 cup crumbs and remaining butter.
Sprinkle over vegetable mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brenda's pigs in a blanket
directions: Unroll pkg. of crescent rolls.
Cut each roll into 3 triangles.
Place 1 sausage in each triangle, starting with the wide end.
Bake according to package directions.
Great with cheese also.

title: celery soup
directions: Cook celery until soft.
Add broth mix.
Pour into blender. Add milk and blend 10 to 15 seconds. Reheat and serve.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter together until crumbly. Set aside.
Stir next
8 ingredients together in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to just below boiling point and cook a few minutes more.
Sprinkle 2/3 of peanut butter mixture in bottom of baked pie shell.
Pour custard over this.
Use remaining peanut butter mixture for top.
Make a meringue of egg whites, cream of tartar and 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread over custard and sprinkle with remainder of peanut butter mixture. Bake at 350° until meringue is browned.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.

title: smoked salmon and dill vegetable bites
directions: In bowl, stir together all ingredients except vegetables. Spoon or pipe with pastry tube a small amount of cheese mixture in/on each piece of vegetable. Place on serving plate. Cover and chill at least 2 or up to 24 hours. Makes about 1 1/3 cups filling (enough for 4 to 5 dozen appetizers).

title: spaghetti pie
directions: For crust, cook spaghetti according to package directions. Drain. Combine 1 egg, Parmesan cheese and margarine. Stir in hot spaghetti.
Press mixture evenly into bottom and up sides of a 9-inch plate. Drain cottage cheese .
Combine with 1 egg. Spread over crust. Set aside.
In a large skillet, cook meat, onion and green pepper until meat is brown. Drain fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Heat through.
Spoon over cottage cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake about 5 minutes more or until cheese melts and crust sets.
Let stand 5 minutes. Cut into wedges.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: boiled drop cookies
directions: Boil in a pan all the ingredients except the oats for 2 minutes.
Remove from the heat and add the oats; stir.
Spoon drops onto waxed paper.
Cool and serve.

title: almond brittle cookies
directions: Line 10 x 15-inch pan with foil.
Lay out crackers and sprinkle with almonds.
Place sugar and butter in a pan at the same time. Bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Spoon over crackers.
Bake for 15 minutes at 300°.

title: banana walnut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Break eggs, saving white of one egg.
Sift flour and then measure.
Add 1 cup of the flour, then add buttermilk.
Now add rest of flour.
Add mashed bananas and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then watch 5 or 10 minutes more.
Let cool at least 10 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Sprinkle top with small amount of cheese and small amount of potato chips.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Serve with broccoli.

title: drunkards lamb stew
directions: Using a large frying pan, brown lamb scraps in oil, and transfer to crock-pot or large casserole.
Leave oil and drippings in pan.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: First bake a Duncan Hines white cake in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Let cake cool on rack 10 minutes.
With a toothpick, make holes about 1 inch apart all over cake.
Pour 1/2 cup green creme de menthe over cake.
Let cool completely.

title: tomato chicken rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 11 x 13 pan place chicken tenders. In large mixing bowl add tomatoes, sugar and seasonings. Mix well, then pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour. About 20 minutes before chicken is done start your rice according to box directions.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together in a saucepan.
Add egg yolks, milk, butter, lemon juice and peel.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly to avoid scorching.
Cool in refrigerator.
Stir sour cream into cooled mixture and pour into baked pie shell.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Put a layer of graham crackers on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Mix pudding mix with milk.
Beat with mixer on low speed until thick. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put pudding mix on top of crackers, then layer crackers again. Refrigerate overnight. Spread chocolate frosting on top. Ready to serve.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Line large dish with layer of tortillas and sprinkle with chicken broth.
Saute onions, green pepper and chili powder.
Add soups.
Pour layer of soup mixture over tortillas, then layer of chicken, then layer of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Pour over all the Ro-Tel tomatoes with chili powder.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain.
Add eggs, cheese, soup, sour cream and onion.
Top
with bread crumbs. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Stir in the remaining ingredients. Form into cakes.
Saute in butter.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Beat cheese with milk until fluffy.
Add chopped ingredients and blend well.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture and place on baking sheet.
Bake 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: beef sticks
directions: Day 1 to 4:
Mix thoroughly, cover and refrigerate (mix each day).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Trim tough ends from broccoli stalks.
Separate into even-size pieces.
Cook broccoli in boiling water until crisp-tender, about 6 to 10 minutes.
Drain well.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon
until
crisp. (I cook mine in the oven on a cookie sheet.)
Brown
hamburger meat; drain.
Crumble bacon. Mix all ingredients
together.
Bake
at 350° about 1 hour or until done.

title: comphermore cake
directions: Beat together cake mix, butterscotch pudding, vanilla pudding, water and eggs.

title: chicken with cashews
directions: Remove skin from chicken
breasts;
cut meat from bones and cut into 1-inch
cubes.
Prepare seasoning sauce.
Combine water, soy
sauce,
syrup,
vinegar
and
cornstarch.
Blend thoroughly and set aside.
Add
oil
to wok, pouring it around sides. Preheat
to
Add chicken cubes; stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes
or until
chicken turns white.
Make well in center. Add
onions, garlic, ginger and red pepper; stir-fry 1 minute. Make well in center.
Stir seasoning sauce, then add to center of wok.
Bring to boil without stirring, about 1 minute.
Cook an
additional
1 minute or until thickened, stirring rest of ingredients with sauce.

title: reese's pieces cookies
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix in flour and soda.
Stir in candy pieces.
Roll in walnut size balls; press with fork on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for about 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pans.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, onion and carrots in water until tender; don't drain.
Add creamed soups, butter, milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until heated.

title: refrigerator oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter, shortening and sugars until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape into rolls and wrap in waxed paper. Store in refrigerator or freezer until ready to bake. Slice and bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: pierogi
directions: Mix Egg Beaters,
salt, water and flour together.
Roll out to 1/8 inch thickness
and
cut
into approximately 4 inch circles. Brown
meat and drain off excess fat.
Mix meat with mashed potatoes,
pepper,
onion
powder,
garlic
powder and seasoning salt.

title: brandied fruit
directions: Mix in glass jar one kind of fruit and 1 cup sugar.
Let stand in kitchen with jar lid tilted slightly to admit air.
This is to admit yeast from the air to start fermentation.
Stir daily as it starts to work.
Takes about 10 days to have fermentation achieve a brandy flavor.
At two week intervals, add another cup of fruit and 1 cup sugar.
Stir daily until taste returns.
Add only one kind of fruit at a time, so if you add peaches at one addition time, for instance, you add pineapple two weeks later and so on.
If an apothecary jar is used and fermentation is underway, the lid probably doesn't need to be tilted as preserves of fermentation would lift the lid enough for air to escape.
No lid should be put on tightly or fruit might spoil.

title: pineapple and cucumber salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Add hot water, lemon juice, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Color with a tiny bit of food coloring. Let stand until gelatin begins to set, then add pineapple and cucumber.
Put in a ring mold and serve on lettuce with mayonnaise which has been mixed with cream and chopped parsley in the center.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: hushpuppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and add buttermilk until mixture has consistency of cornbread.
Deep fry in oil until brown.

title: crisp cucumber slices
directions: Bring all ingredients except cucumbers to a boil.
Slice cucumbers very thin.
Pack in jars (about 2 1/2 to 3 pints).
Pour hot liquid over cucumber slices in the jars.
Place in warm water in canner.
Just bring to boil.
Remove.
Cucumbers will look raw in can.
Let set two or three weeks before using.
Will keep sealed in a cool dark place all winter.

title: cake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients (except powdered sugar) together.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix water, sugar and Jell-O.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Let mixture cool completely.
Crumble cake into a large bowl.
Pour cooled Jell-O mixture over cake. Cover with frozen strawberries.
May add some fresh strawberries in season.
Cover top with Cool Whip.
May garnish top with whole berries.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: breaded tenderloin sandwiches
directions: First, beat egg and milk until beaten.
Then pound pork chops about 1/8-inch thick.
Dip pork chop in egg mixture and then in cracker crumbs.
Place in fryer in medium hot oil until golden brown.

title: chicken-arroz con pollo
directions: Brown chickens in skillet, skin on, for 10 minutes.
Remove chickens.
Place in casserole dish.
Cook onion and garlic in skillet in chicken drippings for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until soft.
Add water, bouillon cube, tomatoes, bay leaf and oregano.
Bring mixture to boil.
Stir in rice.
Cook 15 minutes and pour over chicken in casserole.

title: strawberry pie (2)
directions: Combine sugar and water. Bring to a boil. Stir in paste of cornstarch and 1/2 c. water. Boil until clear and thick for 5 minutes. Stir in jello.
Cool. Fold in strawberries and pour into baked pie shell. Top with whipped cream.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with spoon and chill.

title: sharp's barbecue sauce
directions: Makes enough sauce to do 25 fryers.
Baste fryers with sauce each time you turn.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: sunny gelatin
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over gelatin.
Stir in cream cheese and beat with a beater.
Add 3 cups of juice from peaches plus cold water.
Add fruit and put in refrigerator.
Fruit will sink to the bottom, gelatin will form a middle layer and lightened cheese will rise to the top.

title: golfer's delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts in long Pyrex dish. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool completely. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar. Fold in 1/2 carton Cool Whip. Spread cream mixture on top of cool crust. Mix pudding and milk until thick. Pour over cream cheese mixture. Spread remaining Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate.

title: deep-fried turkey
directions: Mix salt into the butter and inject into bird at points around the breast, in legs and thighs.
You can get an injector needle at any grocery store or hardware store.
Use all the butter mixture.
Now let bird drain for a few minutes before placing in cooker.
Make sure your oil is 350° at all times throughout the cooking time.
While the bird is draining, rub olive oil all over the bird and mix spices and rub the bird good with these.
Rub and rub until you hurt.
Now, place the turkey on the stand and deep-fry for 45 minutes.

title: just right boiled custard
directions: Cook in double boiler until marshmallows dissolve.
Cook longer if you want it to be thicker.

title: corn shell casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: awesome potatoes
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and butter.
Mix with cheese, hash browns, salt, pepper and onions.
Top with either corn flakes and butter or cheese.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef and cheese bake casserole
directions: Brown beef with salt, pepper, onion, green pepper and garlic salt.
Stir in tomato sauce and oregano; set aside.
Blend cream cheese and sour cream.
Add cottage cheese and mix well.
Place half of the cooked noodles in a prepared 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Cover with cheese mixture.
Spread with remaining noodles, then beef mixture.
If prepared ahead of time, refrigerate, then bake. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: mother's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except water.
Let it set for a few minutes and then rework the batter, adding about 1/2 cup water or a little more.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Best baked in an iron skillet (8-wedge skillet).
Grease 8-wedges skillet with Crisco and put in preheated oven until Crisco melts and skillet is hot. Pour batter in skillet.
If the batter starts to sizzle, then the pan is just right.
Makes a good crust on cornbread.
Bake 5 minutes on lower rack of oven.
Cornbread will start to rise. Move up in oven and bake until golden brown.
Makes 2 pans of bread.

title: sweet onion cheese spread
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions and garlic in butter until tender. Remove from heat; stir in cheese, mayonnaise and hot pepper sauce. Transfer to an ungreased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve with crackers. Yields about 5 cups.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook chicken, then debone. Mix broth, onion, soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and simmer until onion is tender. Add chicken. Pour into casserole dish lined with Doritos. Slice cheese on top. Cover casserole so cheese won't burn. Put in oven on 375° until cheese melts.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Cook rice and put in refrigerator to get cold, about 2 hours. Whip whipping cream.
Combine all ingredients and put in rice including whipping cream.
Juice from cherries can be used to tint mixture pink.

title: bran muffins
directions: Add boiling water to shortening and let melt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 20 minutes. Mixture will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.
Bake as needed. Makes good blueberry muffins.
Add to mixture before baking.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Flour chicken and fry in oil.
Add juice and sliced rinds of lemons.
Add parsley and serve.
This is good served with boiled new potatoes.
The juice (lemon butter and pan drippings) from the chicken make a good sauce.

title: paisley fruit cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In large mixer bowl, combine cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, sour cream and 2 teaspoons vanilla; beat on medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Add flour, one tablespoon at a time, blending well.
Add eggs; beat well.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and 3 tablespoons of sugar together.
Work in half of the butter.
Beat egg and add with milk to dry ingredients to form dough; pat into pan.
Arrange apples into dough.
Sprinkle remaining sugar over dough and pour remaining melted butter over, topping off with sprinkling of cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: hash brown and ham casserole
directions: Combine sour cream and soup, then stir in frozen potatoes, ham, cheese (Cheddar or American) and onion.
Turn mixture into a 9 x 13-inch dish; spread evenly.

title: chicken and rice(from the parsonage kitchen)
directions: Sprinkle rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In a bowl, combine mushroom soup and water; stir until smooth.
Cover rice with 1/2 of mixture.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Add pieces of raw chicken, skin side up, and pour on remainder of mushroom soup mixture. Cover with foil tightly and bake at 350° for about 2 hours (depending on how large the chicken pieces are).
Don't open until done.
It must be covered with foil.

title: never fail hot roll filling
directions: Cook nuts, 1/2 c. butter, milk, 1 c. sugar and 1 egg together until thick.
Cool.
Boil sour cream, butter, 1 c. sugar.
Cool to lukewarm and add 2 eggs, yeast (room temp.) and flour as needed. Don't let rise.
Roll out 3 rolls (make 3).
Put filling on it. Roll up - let rise.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cook over medium heat until almost tender, stirring often.
Place in baking dish.

title: oatmeal brownies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, cocoa and milk; bring to boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, oatmeal and peanut butter. Mix well.
Spoon brownies like cookies on a piece of wax paper.

title: macho man chili
directions: Combine meat with onions, bell peppers, beans, tomatoes and 2 cups water.
In separate pan combine all other ingredients.
Cook for 20 minutes and fold in with meat mixture.
Simmer 2 hours. Serve.

title: apple squares
directions: Combine sugar and shortenings and mix well.
Add flour gradually until mixture looks like fine crumbs.
Press half of mixture into 8 x 13-inch oblong ungreased pan.
Combine apples, spices and sugar.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture, pressing firmly around edges.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: old-timey applesauce cake
directions: Beat sugar and shortening together.
Heat applesauce.
Mix soda, allspice and cinnamon into applesauce.
Pour applesauce mixture into sugar and shortening.
Mix and add to flour mix. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Slowly bake at 250° until done.

title: cocoa krispies squares
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in double boiler. Add Cocoa Krispies and coat well.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch greased (with margarine) pan.
Refrigerate.

title: tossed vegetables vinaigrette
directions: Place first six ingredients in a blender or the work bowl of a food processor fitted with a metal blade.
Process until thoroughly mixed.
Set aside.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Shape into a loaf.
Put into a greased pan. Put bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients and make a well in center.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Cool and ice as desired.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a glass or plastic bowl.
Cover surface directly with plastic wrap and refrigerate 30 minutes to blend flavors.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Remove seeds from peppers and put in blender.
Add the seedless, chopped green pepper and puree.
Pour into heavy pan of sugar.
I rinse the blender down with the vinegar and then pour into pan to cook.
Bring to a boil and cook for 15 minutes. Remove from heat and add Certo and a few drops of food coloring. Skim off any foam and pour immediately into jars.
I prefer the 4-ounce jars.
Will make about 10 to 12 jars.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Dice bacon and cook in skillet until crisp.
Add meat and brown well.
Add remaining ingredients being careful to see that the noodles are well dampened.
Cover closely and cook rapidly until steam starts coming from the cover.
Turn to simmer and complete cooking.
Total time:
40 minutes.

title: honey curry chicken
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in casserole dish; add chicken and coat.
Cover and bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: yum-a-setta
directions: Add hamburger, onion, brown sugar and tomato soup.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix cream of chicken soup.
Layer hamburger mix, layer of cheese, noodles and soup until all ingredients are used.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: scones
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening.
Add milk and egg.
Place on lightly floured pastry cloth. Gently knead 20 times.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes. Serve hot with butter and jam. Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: short-cut halupki(cabbage rolls)
directions: Cook rice in water until water is gone, then cool it at least 10 minutes.
In a large
bowl beat egg, and mix in rice, meat, onion, garlic powder,
and
salt.
Cut cabbage into thin wedges.

title: pumpkin nut muffins
directions: Combine and beat two minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender by boiling.
Cook celery and onion in 2 cups of chicken broth, then add margarine.
Skin and bone the chicken.
Cut into small pieces and place into a large baking dish.
Mix both cans of soup with the milk and 1/4 cup of broth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix dressing with celery mixture and add 1 egg.
Mix well and spoon over chicken.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350° (30 minutes covered and then 30 minutes uncovered).

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Wash chicken breasts and pat dry.
In skillet, heat olive oil. In bowl, beat egg.
Add bread crumbs, salt, pepper, oregano and basil.
Dip chicken breasts in egg wash, then in bread crumb mixture.
Place in hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Place fried chicken breasts on paper towel to drain.
When finished frying, place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bottom of pan should be covered with spaghetti sauce.
After placing chicken in pan, cover with sauce.
Add garlic and onion.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Cover with foil.
Place in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour. Remove foil.
Place in oven for 10 minutes.
Take out of oven and let settle for 5 minutes.
Serve with spaghetti.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and blend with creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts and zucchini with wooden spoon.
Bake in 2 loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: six layer cookies(rich, but good)
directions: Melt margarine over low heat in a 13 x 7-inch pan.
Add graham crackers crumbs and pat down; don't stir.
Add a layer of coconut and a layer of chocolate chips.
Pour milk evenly over ingredients.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut each slice of bread in 5 strips.
Bake on cookie sheets at 200° for 2 hours, not touching.
Heat peanut butter (all) and oil in double boiler.
Dip bread in mixture.
While warm, roll in crushed graham crackers and powdered sugar.
Cool on wax paper. Enjoy!

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers (have to use hands).
Add melted butter, eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Mix ingredients with mixer.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour in ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not let cake cool in pan.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain liquid from each can.
Slice onion thinly into rings. Place all ingredients in a large bowl except onion rings and lettuce.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Add onion before serving in a lettuce leaf lined bowl.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Scoop potatoes from shells.
Mash with sour cream and milk.
Mix in next four ingredients.
Fill shells.
Top with cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 300° to 350°.
Serves 4.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in deep heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook until meat turns white and tender.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
Heat small amount of water or chicken broth in skillet.
Add vegetables, beginning with those that take longer to stir-fry, until all vegetables are crisp but tender.
Add more liquid if needed.
Do not overcook vegetables.
Toss chicken with vegetables.
Add salt, pepper and soy sauce to taste while cooking vegetables.
Serve hot over steamed rice.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine ingredients; let set for 2 hours.

title: john ben getty
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and green pepper until done.
Salt to taste, then add 2 cans of tomato soup, mushroom soup and corn. Layer in pan, meat mixture first, then noodles and cheese.
Top last with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: almond and cashew milk formula
directions: Soak all together overnight.
Blend and strain.

title: moist dark chocolate cake
directions: Sift the first 6 ingredients together.
Add margarine.
Melt in coffee, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Makes a runny batter.
Bake in 8-inch pans at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot cream sherbet
directions: Puree fruit.
Add condensed milk and juices.
Freeze until mushy.
Add cream (whipped until stiff).
Freeze until bottom and sides of mixture are hard.
Turn into bowl and beat well.
Return to freezer until hard.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
While noodles are cooking, heat butter in double boiler until melted.
Stir in cream, 1 cup Romano cheese and salt.
Heat, stirring occasionally until smooth.
Drain noodles.
Toss with cream mixture, adding remaining cup of Romano cheese and pepper until evenly coated. Sauce thickens after mixed with noodles and sets for a while.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Place everything in a plastic bag and shake until potatoes are coated.
Place in a shallow baking dish and put in an oven at 450° for about 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: cheesy zucchini bake
directions: Combine tomatoes, zucchini, yellow squash, seasonings and Cheddar cheese.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Add cream and salt; boil 5 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Add powdered sugar until right consistency.
Good on cinnamon rolls.

title: russian lentil soup
directions: In a large soup pot, put 16 cups of water, lentils and a teaspoon of salt and let boil for 1 hour.
After it is 1/2 cooked (half an hour), change the water (drain the water and add 16 cups more water).
Let cook until done.
In a skillet, pour oil and cook onion until golden brown; then add flour and saute a little more. Add the mixture to the lentils along with the carrots, rice and garlic powder.
Salt and pepper to taste.
(You can also add 2 tablespoons of chopped parsley for color.)
Cook until done (about 1/2 hour).

title: homemade paste
directions: Mix flour and enough water to make a thin, creamy mixture. Boil slowly for 4 or 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add a little water if too thick.
Add oil of wintergreen so the paste will stay fresh; cool.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix all together the cake mix, vanilla, chopped nuts, and 1 beaten egg.
Pour into greased oblong pan.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Place pecans and coconut in blender; chop fine. Add jello, dry and mix. Add sugar to blender and mix in. Mix in salt and vanilla. Add milk. Chill dough mixture. Form in strawberry shapes and roll in red sugar crystals. Dye slivered almonds green to use for stems in top.

title: lemon cake
directions: Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Glaze while hot.

title: salad rice and frank bake
directions: Cook rice with onion, following label directions; drain. Spoon into 8-cup baking dish.
Stir in frankfurters and celery. Blend remaining ingredients.
Fold into rice mixture and cover. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley, if you wish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Put grated cheese on top. Put crushed crackers on top of cheese and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 400° (or until it is bubbly and topping is brown).

title: cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Mix cheese, onions and garlic together well.
Spread a little on the slices of meat (fold each slice in half or diagonal, depending on how you want the finished roll up to look) and roll the meat with the filling in the center.
Makes 16 or more, depending on how much filling you want in each hors d'oeuvre and whether you want to add thin spears of pickle, celery or even green onion for variety.

title: lemon asparagus
directions: In a large skillet, cook asparagus spears as directed on package. Dot with butter and sprinkle with lemon juice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cook Rice-A-Roni, using broth from chicken.
Blend egg, onion, mayonnaise and soup.
Layer Rice-A-Roni, then chicken in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Melt 1/2 cup butter; blend flour and chicken bouillon cubes. Cook over low heat. Gradually add milk. Cook until thick and pour over broccoli. Pour 2/3 bag of stuffing. Heat 2/3 cup water and 6 tablespoons butter and pour over stuffing. Mix together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Don't cover.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually, beating all the time.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla and flour gradually.
Bake in ungreased tube pan.
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour (approximate).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Butter and flour pans.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour. Makes 3 loaves.

title: chicken francaise
directions: Dip chicken in egg/lemon juice. Coat with bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in oil.
In a separate pot, melt butter. Add garlic, chicken broth and lemon juice.
Pour the sauce over the chicken in glass pan. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Add wine and bake 30 minutes longer (uncover the pan for the last 15 minutes). Enjoy!

title: washday peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Stir until well blended.
Melt butter in 2-quart baking dish.
Pour in flour mixture.
Add cooked fruit.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add chilies with liquid; let set. Boil chicken until done; cool, then cut into small pieces.
In large pan or skillet, add the 2 cans of soup and
1 1/2 cans milk. Add chicken, then onion and chilies; heat and stir.
In casserole dish, layer soup and chicken mixture.
Tear tortillas in pieces. Add a layer, then layer of cheese.
Keep layering; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet tortilla crisps
directions: Cut each tortilla into 8 wedges.
Brush with margarine.
Place tortillas on an ungreased baking sheet.
Combine sugar and cinnamon, stirring well.
Sprinkle sugar mixture evenly over tortilla wedges.
Bake at 425° for 4 to 6 minutes or until wedges are lightly browned.

title: chow chow
directions: Wash, clean, drain and chop vegetables.
Dissolve salt in 8 cups water.
Pour over vegetables, and let stand 1 hour.
Drain (rinse if too salty).
Mix vegetables with sugar, seed and vinegar.
Bring to a boil, simmer 20 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer the lettuce, celery, green onions, green bell peppers, peas, mayonnaise, grated cheese and bacon bits (jar or fresh).
Put in order as given and let stand for 8 hours or overnight.
Makes 10 to 12 servings or more.

title: chicken and vegetable casserole
directions: Fry chicken and then cut into bite size pieces.
Melt margarine in a saucepan. Saute onion, then add thawed vegetables. Stir in soup and sour cream. Add croutons.
Add cooked rice, chicken and mushrooms.
Put into a baking dish. Sprinkle more croutons on the top.
Bake at 350° until casserole is warm and the croutons have browned.

title: quick zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 2 small loaves.

title: spinach and dill dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine dressing, sour cream, parsley and dill.
Stir in spinach until well mixed.
Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours.
Stir and serve on crackers.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Arrange spareribs in large baking dish. Add onions and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over spareribs. Cover and bake in medium oven about 1 1/2 hours, basting frequently. Remove cover and bake 20 minutes longer. Can also be made with beef spareribs.

title: oven-roasted vegetables
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Place vegetables in a large roasting pan. Toss with the olive oil, salt and pepper to mix and coat. Spread in a single layer in the pan. Roast for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are
lightly browned and tender.

title: feed "em" all cake
directions: Bake cake mix in two 9 x 13-inch pans and cool.
Slice a layer of bananas on cake and top with crushed pineapple.
Mix in separate bowl cream cheese, pudding and milk.
Ice the top layer with this mixture.
Then ice the cake again with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Measure shortening and cut into flour mixture with pastry blender, two knives or blending fork, until mixture looks like "meal".
Stir in almost all the milk.
If dough does not seem pliable, add the remaining milk.
Use enough milk to make a soft, puffy dough, easy to roll out.
Knead (fold dough over and press lightly with heel of hand about six times) on a lightly floured board (as lightly floured as you would powder your face).
Too much handling makes tough biscuits.
Roll or pat out 1/4 inch thick for thin biscuits and 1/2 inch thick for thick soft biscuits.
Cut and place on ungreased cookie sheet, close together for biscuits with soft sides, an inch apart for biscuits with crusty sides.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add chuck and cook until meat is brown.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer a few minutes.
Prepare noodles as directed on package; drain. Mix cream cheese and sour cream together thoroughly.
In a 4-quart casserole, layer noodles, cheese mixture and meat sauce.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fruit yogurt
directions: Soak
pineapple
juice
in blender while boiling water. When water
boils,
whiz ingredients in blender briefly.
Add cashews and
half
of
boiling
water
to mixture in blender. Blend smooth.
Add all except frozen fruit and blend.
Gradually
add and blend frozen fruit.
Pour into container(s) and refrigerate or serve immediately.
Makes 5 cups.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients and form into meatballs.
Cook in hot spaghetti sauce for at least 1 1/2 hours.
Use a wooden or plastic spoon to stir around occasionally.

title: oyster snacks
directions: Combine dressing mix with dill seed, spices and oil.
Pour over crackers; stir to coat.
Place in warm oven (250°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir gently halfway through baking.

title: cheeseburger chowder
directions: In a large saucepan cook beef and drain.
Stir in soup, milk, potatoes, chilies, taco seasoning, onion, chili powder until blended.
Simmer uncovered for five minutes or until heated through.
Garnish with corn chips, cheese and green onions.

title: lentil-vegetable stew(adas mah khodra)
directions: Combine water, lentils and ribs in large skillet.
Bring to boil over high heat, then lower heat to medium.
Skim off foam. Cover and cook until lentils are tender, approximately 1 hour.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In a large pan, combine margarine, oil, cocoa and water. Bring to a rapid boil; remove from heat.
Sift together flour and sugar; stir into hot mixture.
Add small amount of hot mixture into eggs.
Combine with remaining hot mixture.
Add buttermilk and baking soda; beat well.
Stir in remaining flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured 17 x 12-inch sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut into 2 3/8-inch pieces.

title: checkerboard cheese bake
directions: Trim and thinly slice summer squash.
Saute in 2 tablespoons butter.
Set aside.
Tear spinach into bite-sized pieces and saute in 2 tablespoons butter.
Set aside.
Saute tomatoes in 2 tablespoons butter.
Set aside.
Combine cottage cheese, crackers and herbs in a small bowl.
Put squash into a 2 quart baking dish. Add 1/2 cheese mixture, all of the spinach, remaining cheese mixture and tomato slices.
Top with Provolone cheese arranged in a checkerboard fashion.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon torte
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add vinegar.
Beat until stiff. Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Make pie filling as directed on package.
Cool thoroughly.
Layer: spread 1/2 of Cool Whip on meringue layer; spread all lemon filling next and add rest of Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Beat together eggs, milk and oil.
Add to corn meal mixture along with cheese, onion, corn and garlic. Stir until just combined.
Pour into two greased 8 x 8-inch pans. Bake 20 to 30 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: perfect fudge
directions: Mix together first three ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until soft ball stage when tested in water.
Remover from heat and mix other ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour in buttered dish.

title: idiot's delight
directions: Blend all but flour.
Add flour and work well with hands until well blended.
Form roll and slice 1/4-inch thick, or pinch off and roll in balls.
May be rolled around olives.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix beaten egg, butter and Parmesan cheese with pasta.
Pat down in 9 x 13-inch pan; top with cottage or Ricotta cheese.
