Cook hamburg, green pepper, onion and garlic. Drain well.
Mix it with spaghetti sauce, salt, pepper and oregano.
Pour on top of cheese.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cook another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pone(heritage)
directions: Combine potatoes, water, sugar, salt and ginger.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender and caramelized, stirring occasionally, about 2 hours. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soup with milk; reserve 1/2 cup of the mixture.
Mix the rest of the soup and milk with the mushrooms and rice, plus 1/2 of the onion soup.
Pour mixture into an ungreased baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch).
Place chicken breasts on top.
Pour the 1/2 cup reserved soup-milk over the chicken; sprinkle the rest of the soup mix over the top.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°, then uncovered for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pizza rustica
directions: Cook sausage (remove casing) and remove fat particles.
Mix Ricotta and Mozzarella together.
Add sausage, ham, eggs, sugar and parsley.
Blend all ingredients.
Place in uncooked pastry shell.
Cover with crust.
Make slits to allow steam to escape. Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350° to 375° in a hot oven.

title: corn muffin pudding
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° about 1 to 1 1/2 hours until golden brown. Serve with ham, chicken or turkey, etc.

title: anise cookie cordiales
directions: In small bowl,	combine
flour	and
baking powder; set aside. In large
bowl,
combine sugar and butter;
beat until creamy. Add eggs, liqueur,	water
and anise seed; beat until well blended.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate bits and almonds.
Cover;
chill
several hours.
Preheat oven to
375°; divide dough
in
fourths.	With
floured
hands
on greased cookie sheet shape dough into
four
1/2 x 2 x 1/2 inch loaves.
Bake at 375°
for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; cut into 1 inch slices.
Place
slices
back
on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Turn cookies on other side.
Bake at 375° for 7 more
minutes.
Cool
completely.
Makes
1/2 dozen.

title: jello and cranberry holiday salad
directions: Dissolve
gelatin in boiling water, add orange rind and cranberry sauce.
Chill until thickened; stir in pineapple and celery.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart mold.
Chill until firm, 3 to 4 hours.
Unmold on crisp salad greens.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add butter, sugar, flour, milk and vanilla.
Beat again until well blended.
Stir in coconut.
Pour filling into pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool thoroughly and cut.

title: peach (or mango) salsa
directions: Finely chop or dice and mix fruit, cilantro, hot pepper, green onion and ginger root.
Add sugar and squeezed lime juice.
Let sit for 30 minutes.
Serve over grilled chicken or fish.

title: seafood medley
directions: Combine soup and milk.
Heat.
Add seafood.
Heat and serve over patty shell or toast.

title: oven-fried garlic chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a shallow bowl, blend together bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
In a small saucepan, heat butter and garlic over very low heat until butter melts.
Remove from heat.
Brush chicken pieces with garlic butter, then roll in bread crumb mixture and butter; sprinkle over chicken.
Place chicken skin side up on a large, foil lined baking sheet.
Mix together any remaining crumb mixture and butter; sprinkle over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: apple pie(no apples)
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil.
Add cream of tartar. Add Ritz crackers.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add lemon juice. Pour into prepared pie shell.
Cover with top pastry crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients on low until just mixed, then beat on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven
in 13 x 9-inch pan for 35 to 45 minutes; 24 to 30 muffins for 25 to 30 minutes (done when toothpick comes out clean).
Best if stored overnight before serving.
Makes 24 muffins or 1 (13 x 9-inch) cake.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add next, still beating.
Scald milk and add butter.
Add this last and give it a dozen more hard beats.
Grease and flour pan (8 x 11-inch pan). Bake in moderate oven for 25 minutes.
Allow to cool and pour over it the icing.

title: mr. vogler's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl; beat with mixer.
Pour into 10-inch pie crust.
Bake in 425° oven 45 to 55 minutes.
Insert knife in center, if it comes out clean pie is done.
Foil strips on crust all around edge for first 30 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Heat 1/2 of milk over boiling water (double boiler). Meanwhile, cream eggs, sugar, flour and salt with beaters.
When milk is scalding hot, add egg mixture after adding about a cup of hot milk to the bowl of eggs.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens, then remove from heat.
Add remaining uncooked milk and vanilla extract.
Freeze in either old fashioned hand turned or electric ice cream freezer.
Makes about a gallon of ice cream.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: With fork, beat cream cheese until smooth. Stir in crushed pineapple, 1 cup of the pecans and rest of ingredients. Shape into ball and roll in remaining cup of nuts.

title: tomato dip
directions: Toss first 4 ingredients, mix in next 4.
Serve cold with Fritos.
Remaining dip may be served in a hollowed out tomato for a salad the next day.

title: cinnamon crisps
directions: In a small bowl sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream shortening and 3/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add 1/2 of the flour mixture; mix after each addition.
Form rounded teaspoons of dough into a ball and roll in sugar.
Place on greased baking sheets then flatten into 1/8 inch thick circle.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: angi's quick marinara sauce
directions: Lightly saute garlic and pepper flakes in olive oil.
Add tomatoes and cook lightly for about 20 to 30 plus minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Add basil and parsley.

title: layer salad
directions: Mix all together.
Grate sharp Cheddar cheese on top.
Chill and serve.

title: italian potato salad
directions: Soak onion, oregano, parsley and tomatoes in olive oil and vinegar while cooking potatoes.
Cook potatoes until tender; let cool.
Pour mixture over potatoes; toss well.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cream puffs
directions: Dissolve butter in boiling water.
Add flour and cook until very thick, stirring constantly (about five minutes).
Cool until lukewarm.
Beat in eggs one at a time beating well after each addition.
Drop in heaping tbsp on greased cookie sheet.
Keep each mound well apart.
Bake in preheated oven 450 degrees for 15 minutes.
Then 375 degrees for 25 minutes to 400 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool and fill with sweetened whipped cream or cream filling.
(I use cooked vanilla pudding.)
Frost with chocolate or maple icing (optional).

title: brownie peanut butter mousse cake
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to directions on package, baking batter in a spring-form pan.
Cool brownies completely in pan.
Combine cream cheese and peanut butter and mix well.	Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Whip heavy cream until soft peaks form.
Fold whipped cream into peanut butter mixture.
Spoon over cooled brownies.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.	Remove spring-form pan side and serve.

title: pepper nachos
directions: Place tortilla chips in single layer in large baking pan or cookie sheet with sides.
Sprinkle cheese over chips and scatter small spoonfuls of relish on top.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes or until hot.
Serve with sour cream and/or salsa sauce.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: watergate cake
directions: To cake mix, add eggs, pudding, oil and 7-Up. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 13 x 9 pan.

title: date and nut pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Beat eggs separately.
Add yolks and fold in whites last (looks different but is okay).
Bake 35 to 40 minutes; test for doneness with toothpick.
Serves 8.
Serve with ice cream, whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Very rich so serve small amount.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, then milk.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into 4 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: corn moussaka
directions: Spread corn in bottom of casserole dish. Brown beef and drain. Add flour and stir 1 minute. Add tomato sauce, garlic salt and cinnamon.
Mix well and pour over corn.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Combine eggs and cottage cheese. Spread over beef. Top with grated Parmesan, Mozzarella
and nuts. Bake 15 minutes more. Serves 6.
May add chopped green pepper and bacon, if desired.

title: chocolate butter creams
directions: Beat cream cheese, milk and vanilla until fluffy; stir in powdered sugar replacement.
Form into 30 balls and dip each one in chocolate.
Yield: 30 creams.

title: paulova(meringue)
directions: Prepare trays.	(I use 2 round pizza trays.)
Grease very well.
Sprinkle with equal quantities of cornstarch and powdered sugar sifted together.

title: pecan pie
directions: Prick holes in bottom of crust, but not all the way through the crust. Mix ingredients and pour into the crust.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour or until the middle doesn't shake.

title: cheatin' cheese biscuits(reduced fat, no sugar)
directions: Cream the butter and then add the remaining ingredients. Mixture is very stiff.
Chill, then roll it on waxed paper, cut or squeeze it through a cookie press.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix together.
Pat out on pizza pan.
Put whatever pizza ingredients you desire on top.
Bake at 350° to 375° until done.

title: rocky road squares
directions: In microwave:
5 minutes High heat or in top of double boiler over boiling water melt chocolate with sweetened condensed milk and butter.
Remove from heat.
In a large bowl combine nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in chocolate mixture.
Spread in waxed paper-lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Remove from pan, peel off waxed paper.
Cover and store at room temperature.

title: baked beans
directions: Clean and soak beans overnight in water keeping beans covered with water.
Drain water and add fresh water. Add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Bring to a boil; drain.
Repeat 3 times.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg thoroughly.
Stir in milk and orange juice.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in.
Blend in nuts and apricots.
Pour into greased 8-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes until toothpick comes out clean (top will crack open).
Makes two 8-inch loaves.

title: one bowl macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in egg whites and extract.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Top with 1/2 cherry.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until edges are golden.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 65 cookies.

title: oodles and oodles of cheesy noodles
directions: Boil noodles until tender.
Drain. Put hot noodles back into pan.
Stir in can of soup and milk.
Stir in grated cheese, until melted. Serve and enjoy!

title: grandma dicke's turkey dressing
directions: Brown and drain hamburger; set aside.
Cook giblets and save liquid.
Grind giblets, celery and onion together.
Mix with double bag of Katherine Clark's stuffing.
Moisten with giblet liquid so there is no dry bread.
Salt cavity of the turkey and stuff with dressing (more than enough for a 20 pound turkey).
Do not pack it tight.
Heat rest in a dish for 20 to 30 minutes near the end of the turkey's cooking time.

title: swiss deer steaks
directions: Pound steaks or chops in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in butter on both sides.
Put in casserole or baking dish.
Add mushroom soup and 1/2 can of water.
Put slices of onions on steaks and cover.
Bake for 1 hour at 275° until tender.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Peel and devein 2 pounds of medium shrimp.
Season heavily with Tony's seasoning.
Put seasoned shrimp in a large Ziploc bag and marinate overnight.

title: country kitchen chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender; debone and cut in bite size pieces. Saute onions and peppers in margarine.
Stir in stuffing mix. Place 1/2 of the mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix together mushroom soup, chicken soup and broth.
Put layer of chicken over stuffing mix, then 1/2 soup mixture.
Repeat layers. Top with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach; mix all ingredients.
Serve with crackers.

title: corn custard
directions: Place corn in greased 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Beat eggs, sugar and salt slightly.
Make paste of cornstarch and 2 tablespoons milk.
Scald remaining milk; add to cornstarch mixture.
Add butter.
Slowly add egg mixture to milk mixture; blend well and pour over corn.
Set casserole in pan of hot water 1-inch deep.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: one cup cobbler
directions: Place a 9 x 13-inch baking dish in oven to melt butter.
Mix together all other ingredients, except pie filling, in a mixing bowl.
After butter is melted, pour the mixture down the center of the baking dish.
This will push the butter to the sides.
Pour the pie filling down the center on top of mixture.
It will spread itself. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Top with your favorite ice cream and enjoy.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Drain and cool.
Combine zucchini, tomatoes, peppers and seasoning.
Pour dressing over pasta and mix well.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: crescent lasagna
directions: In a skillet, saut beef until brown and crumbly. Drain excess fat and season with salt and pepper. Stir in spaghetti sauce. In a 9 x 13 baking dish, put a layer of crescent rolls. Spread a thin layer of beef and sauce mixture. Top with 1/3 of cottage cheese, 1/3 of Mozzarella cheese and 1/3 of Parmesan cheese. Repeat layering two more times. Place final layer of crescent rolls for top of dish. You may sprinkle sesame seeds on top for a garnish if you like. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown. Cool 10 minutes before cutting into squares to serve.

title: creamy cheese cake
directions: Mix these ingredients and line bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan with this mixture.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make holes in brownies with fork.
Pour in Kahlua.
Crumble 1/2 of brownies in truffle bowl.
Add 1/2 mousse, 1/2 Cool Whip and 1/2 Heath bars.
Repeat.
Refrigerate.
Spoon into dessert dishes and enjoy!
Serves up to 24 people or 1 chocoholic!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Mix oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in sugars and dry ingredients.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, until tests done.
Makes 2 large loaves or 3 small loaves.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, taco seasoning and milk until well blended.
Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange the remaining ingredients in the order given, on top of the cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate up to a day before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at at time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Mix well each time.
Stir in vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes; then remove from pan.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown 4 pork chops and remove from pan.
Pour into skillet 3 cups boiling water, 3 bouillon cubes and stir until dissolved. Add 1 cup uncooked rice, 1/2 cup celery and dash of Tabasco. Place pork chops on rice.
Cover and cook 45 minutes.

title: chuck roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
Place roast in roasting pan; sprinkle with onion soup.
Spread mushroom sauce on top.
Bake for 1 to 2 hours or until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: nita's pasta smothered with onions
directions: In covered saucepan, cook onions and garlic in butter and olive oil over low heat, about 20 minutes or until very tender, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and cook over medium-high heat, about 10 minutes or until onions are a deep, golden color, stirring frequently.
Stir in chicken broth and pepper.
Boil gently, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in cheese and parsley.
Toss onion mixture with pasta until coated.
Serve immediately.
Pass additional shredded Mozzarella over the top.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin pie - unbaked pie shell
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake 15 minutes at 425°; then reduce heat and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer at 350°.

title: eclair cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk; beat until thick.
Add Cool Whip and beat.
Pour 1/2 mixture over crackers.
Layer with more crackers; pour the remaining pudding mixture and top with another layer of crackers. Using 1/2 or more of icing recipe.
Mix and spread on top of crackers.
Make one day ahead and refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease 2 large loaf pans or 5 small ones.
Cream the butter with the sugar.
Add the eggs and beat well.
Add the mashed bananas, stirring to blend.
In a separate bowl, sift together the dry ingredients.
Fold the dry ingredients into the batter, mixing well.
Add the nuts.
Pour the batter into the pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: 5-layer dinner
directions: Layer in order given in a greased, oblong casserole.
Bake at 350° for 90 minutes.

title: kraut
directions: Make when signs are in head.

title: herbed stuffed eggs
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise.
Separate yolks and white halves.
Set white halves aside.
Mash yolks; add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Spoon mixture into white halves.
Add sliced scallions for garnish.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Bring sugar and Karo syrup to a boil, then remove from heat. Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies to sugar mixture.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Melt chocolate bits and butterscotch bits and spread over cookies in pan.
Cut into bars.

title: mayonnaise pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl. Stir in mayonnaise.
Add water. Roll out on lightly floured surface. Makes 1 double crust.

title: macaroni salad
directions: While cooking macaroni, dice all vegetables and cheese.
Also drain the can of peas.
After macaroni is cooked, drain (do not chill).
While hot, drizzle with oil and vinegar.
Add onion, seasonings and cheese.
Toss well.
Gently mix in ham and remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: mary's herbed chicken and shrimp
directions: Combine sour cream with herbs and seasonings.
Dip chicken into sour cream mixture, then roll in corn flake crumbs.
Place chicken pieces, skin side down, in well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add mushrooms, corn and soup.
Layer mashed potatoes on top of mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese and Velveeta on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy peanut butter chews
directions: In a small bowl, combine cereal and coconut; set aside.
In a 2-quart saucepan, combine peanut butter, margarine and marshmallows; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until marshmallows are melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and coconut.
Quickly drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool completely.
Store in refrigerator.

title: potato chip chicken casserole
directions: Bake or cook chicken as desired. Cut in bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients together except potato chips.
Bake half of the crushed chips in bottom of baking dish, then add above mixture. Add remainder of chips on top.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt butter and pour salt and sauce in butter. Add to mixture and bake.
Cook at 250° for 2 hours, stirring often.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: In a saucepan, lightly saute onion in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add broth; bring to a boil.
Put in 2 handfuls of egg noodles. Cook 3 minutes, uncovered.
Defrost broccoli about 3/4 of the way, then add to soup mixture. Add garlic, Old Bay seasoning, salt and pepper. Dice cheese and add to mixture.
Add the milk and simmer until cheese melts. Stir constantly to prevent scorching.

title: garden raw relish
directions: Combine all of the items in a large bowl with the salt and pepper.
Pour oil and vinegar over vegetables and toss well. Chill until ready to serve.
Goes well with any meat dish.

title: chocolate refrigerator pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

Place uncooked rice or dried beans or pie weights in the center of pie crust, over a sheet of aluminum foil and bake in the lower third of oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove the weights from the center, prick the bottom a few times with a fork, and bake 5 to 10 minutes more, until golden brown. Scald, heat but don't allow to boil, milk in a saucepan over medium heat.
In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, cocoa, salt and egg yolks.
Add milk slowly to the sugar mixture, stirring constantly. Pour mixture into the same saucepan and cook over medium heat just until it boils.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill in the refrigerator.
Top with whipped cream. Makes 1 pie.

title: baked carrots
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in hot oven 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, 1/2 white part of green onions and as much taco seasoning as you like (use to your liking). Spread on flat plate or tray in thin layer. Add a little more taco seasoning for looks. Add cheese spread out along with black olives, green onion slices and sliced tomato!

title: henry's strawberry pie
directions: In a saucepan, mash about 5 or 6 ripe berries and combine with sugar, flour and water.
Cook until thick and refrigerate until cold.
Just before serving, place the strawberries in the pie shell, reserving a few for garnish.
Pour the glaze over the berries.
Cover with whipped cream and garnish with the reserved berries.
Slice and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed in 2 8 inch round pans.
Let cool.

title: chocolate chip cheese squares
directions: Slice 1 package cookie dough and place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pat down to cover the bottom of pan.
Mix the eggs, sugar, vanilla and cream cheese.
Spread cheese mixture on top of cookie dough.
Slice second package of cookie dough and place on top of cream cheese mixture.
Do not pat down.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: grandma hazel's persimmon bread
directions: Note:
There is no sugar called for in this recipe.
I don't know if Grandma left it out or if there wasn't any called for. What I found is that if the persimmons are really sweet, you don't need sugar or honey.
After you mix the batter, taste it.
Add sugar or honey if it doesn't taste sweet enough.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda; cut in butter until mixture looks like coarse corn meal.
Stir in raisins and caraway.
Add buttermilk and egg to dry mixture, blending only until all flour is moistened.
Butter and
flour pan or skillet.
Bake for 1 hour or until knife comes out dry.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mincemeat
directions: Put altogether and put in roaster.
Cook in oven at low for 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: bacon delight salad
directions: Mix all together and add:

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water and butter to a boil.
Stir in flour.
Stir over low heat until mixture forms soft ball.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each egg is added.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes.
Fill with pudding or whipped cream.

title: jezabel sauce
directions: Mix jelly, preserves, mustard, horseradish and pepper and let stand at least half a day.
Good with any kind of pork.
Keeps forever in refrigerator.
Good with eggrolls, too.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers; remove centers and discard. Cook peppers 5 minutes in boiling water; drain peppers and set aside.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant in salty water until tender.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a glass pan and bake at 325° until firm. Squash may be substituted for eggplant if desired.

title: creole vegetables
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and celery in 2 tablespoons margarine in large skillet.
Add cabbage, tomatoes, beef bouillon, lemon pepper and sugar.
Bring to simmering and simmer 10 minutes.

title: chili verde
directions: Mix flour and water to thicken.
Melt shortening in large deep skillet.
Brown meat thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, covered.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes to desired consistency.

title: light fruitcake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine pecans, walnuts, the 3/4 pound of cherries, pineapple and raisins. Toss with 1 cup flour; set aside.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato juice.
Add just enough juice to form a ball.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot fat.
Cook until golden brown.

title: chicken fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix lightly.
Serve on crisp lettuce cup.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put pineapple on bottom, then the cherry filling.
Crumble dry cake mix on top, then sprinkle with almonds.
Layer top with thin slices of butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until you think it is done.

title: chicken 'n vegetables skillet
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and brown chicken; drain.
Add peas and carrots, golden mushroom soup mix and parsley blended with water.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes or until chicken is tender. Serve, if desired, with hot mashed potatoes.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine chopped potatoes, diced onion, chicken broth, and 2 cups of water into pot.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 20-25 minutes.
In a separate bowl, mix cream of chicken, cream of celery, and milk, and then whisk until smooth.
Add this mixture to the potato mixture after they have cooked 20-25 minutes.
Stir in margarine, salt, and pepper, and allow to cook another 10 minutes on slightly higher heat.
The longer it cooks, the thicker it will be.

title: fruit desserts
directions: Layer cookies, then the fruit.
Mix 1 package pudding with milk; pour over fruit, then another layer of cookies and fruit and the other instant pudding.
Pour over fruit and cookies.
Pour cherry juice over all ingredients.
Top with Cool Whip and cherries.
Refrigerate overnight or 3 hours before serving.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk in bowl.
Add pudding mix; beat with whisk (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices. Mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or until ready to serve.

title: speedy oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir the first 6 ingredients together until smooth.
Add the flour, oatmeal and nuts.
Stir until smooth.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use a 9 x 13 Pyrex dish.
Cut strips of bacon into halves.
Take a small handful of green beans and wrap in the bacon (5 to 6 green beans).
Place the bundles in the dish in rows.
Take a small pan and melt the butter and brown sugar.
Drizzle melted brown sugar/butter mixture over the bundles and cook the bundles for 20 to 30 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: dressing
directions: Cook the onion and celery until tender.
Grease the bottom of pan well.
Mix hush puppy mix until moist (with water).
Bake until desired brown.
Add the boiled eggs, soup and moist bread.
Add celery and onion to the mixture (pepper if desired).
Mix all ingredients well.
If more moisture is needed, use water.
Bake at 450° until desired brown.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with one stack of Ritz crackers (crushed).
Sprinkle this on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: health bread or radical raisin bread
directions: If you call this Health Bread your kid's won't touch it so make up a more tasty name.
This bread must sit 24 hours before slicing.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend all together.
Make the night before so flavors can blend.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese until soft.
Blend sour cream and taco mix to cream cheese.
Spread mixture into a 9-inch round pie plate. Spread salsa onto cheese/sour cream mixture.
Layer all remaining ingredients, ending with shredded cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with taco chips.

title: carp supreme
directions: You will need one 12 x 12-inch pine board.
Butter 1 side of pine board; cut carp in half.
Rub salt on both sides of carp; sprinkle pepper on pine board.
Place carp on pine board and insert in oven.
Bake 45 minutes.
Take out of oven and spread tomatoes over pine board.
Throw carp away and eat the board. Makes four 6 x 6-inch servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Combine ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Top individual servings with shredded cheese and serve with tortilla chips.

title: braided broccoli and chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Chop chicken and broccoli, place in large mixing bowl. Chop bell pepper, add to chicken, press garlic into mixing bowl. Shred cheese add to mixing bowl; mix gently. Add mayonnaise and salt, mix well. Unroll crescent rolls, do not separate. Arrange longest sides of dough across width of stone. Seal perforations in dough, on longest side of stone, cut dough into 1 1/2 inches apart, 3 inches deep (there will be 6 inches in center for filling). Spread filling evenly in center of dough. Lift strips of dough across filling evenly in center of dough across filling to meet in middle twisting each strip 1 turn. Continue alternating strips to form a braid, tuck ends up to seal braid. Brush with egg. Bake 25-28 minutes or until golden.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix the softened cream cheese and warm water until smooth. Add cake mix and margarine and mix well.
Add oil and sugar; beat. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until well mixed, approximately 4 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine eggs, corn, sour cream, and margarine.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.
Place cheese on top and bake 10 minutes more.

title: tandoori chicken(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Indian spices are available in any Asian or Indian stores.

title: four bean salad
directions: Combine green beans and wax beans.
Rinse and drain chickpeas and kidney beans and add all together.
Stir in vinegar, oil and sugar.
Slice onion and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Chop as many peppers as you need.
Mix all together and bake in greased pan for 35 minutes at 400°.

title: steak 'n ale marinade
directions: Use as a marinade for steaks, chicken, etc.

title: honey baked sweet potatoes
directions: Cook
sweet
potatoes
in
water until tender; cool and peel. Slice
1-inch thick.
Peel apple and slice about 1-inch thick. Alternate layers in buttered baking dish.
Melt butter in saucepan,
stir
in
honey, lemon juice and cinnamon until well mixed.
Pour
honey
mixture
over	sweet
potatoes
and apples; cover
and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove cover and bake for

15 minutes to slightly brown.	Top with marshmallows.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Put all ingredients in a big pot.
Mix well and pour into 6-quart freezer.
Use salt and ice and freeze until done, about 20 minutes.
If you want vanilla, omit chocolate syrup.
If you want pineapple or cherry, put into blender and add to mix.

title: chicken breasts and herb rice
directions: Spread uncooked rice in bottom of baking pan.
Cover with undiluted chicken and celery soups.
Top with chicken breasts. (The breasts are not browned.)
Sprinkle onion soup over all.
Pour 1 cup milk around sides.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: rich onion soup
directions: In a large kettle, cook onions in butter and oil over low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add sugar and mustard. Cook 30 minutes longer.
Blend in flour.
Stir in broth and wine and cook 30 minutes more.
Season to taste.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Cover with foil first 40 minutes of baking time.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Mix all together, except almonds.
Sprinkle 1/2 bag of slivered almonds on top.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Combine cream cheese, half and half and butter in a heavy-bottomed saucepan.
Stir over low heat until soft and creamy and butter is melted.
Remove from heat and blend in frosting mix. Stir.
Add peppermint extract.
Roll mixture into balls or drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Press with fork or cookie stamp for design.
Let mints stand, uncovered, at room temperature until firm and outside is dry.
Inside should still be creamy.

title: pear honey
directions: Wash, core and put pears through a meater grind or chopper. Add sugar and let stand 2 hours or overnight.
Cook like preserves (around 1 hour), then add pineapple about 20 minutes before canning.
You may want to use juice of 1 lemon (optional).
Put in clean, sterilized pint jars.
Makes about 5 pints.
Delicious served on toast and it can be mixed with peanut butter to make a sweet sandwich.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Make a well.
Add oil, pumpkin and water; blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg is added.
Fold in nuts.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass) for 1 hour.
Test center before removing from oven.
Cool.
Freezes well.

title: gram's lemon icebox pie
directions: Blend egg yolks and condensed milk. Slowly add lemon juice. Pour filling into pie crust. Let set 24 hours for best results. Keep refrigerated.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix all together and put in bottom and sides of pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until thick (stir while cooking).
Add 1/2 box strawberry jello.
Pour over strawberries in a baked pie crust and cover with whipping cream.

title: betty's brown edge cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter, sugar, vanilla and egg until light yellow color.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake a few minutes until edges start to brown.
Watch so cookies don't burn.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Thaw out bread dough.
Let rise partially.
Roll out to 1/2 inch thickness.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up into long roll.
Cut into 1 inch thickness. Put into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Cook topping until sugar dissolves, about 2 minutes.
Pour over rolls right before you put them into preheated 350° oven. Bake 25 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: mandarin almond salad
directions: In a small skillet melt 3 Tbsp. sugar over low heat. Add almonds; stir until cooked. Cool; break into small pieces and set aside. In a jar with tight-fitted lid, combine oil, vinegar, parsley, salt, pepper, hot sauce, and 1 Tbsp. sugar. Shake well. Just before serving, combine lettuce, oranges, onion and almonds in a large bowl. Shake dressing, pour over salad and toss.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Season ground chuck to taste with salt, pepper and garlic salt while browning with diced onions in a large skillet.
Drain fat. Add beans and barbecue sauce.
Stir until simmering.
Add brown sugar.
Reduce heat until barely simmering.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
For additional options, add diced green pepper or sliced sausage.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grate the Parmesan cheese, if it isn't already.
Combine all ingredients in your food processor, adding the cheese and jalapenos to taste.
Process until mostly smooth.
Pour the mixture into a small casserole.
Bake until bubbly and golden (about 30 minutes).
Serve surrounded by tortilla chips.

title: champagne chicken
directions: Flatten chicken with palm of hand.
Combine flour, salt and pepper and dust breasts on both sides.
Saute in butter and oil 5 minutes.
Turn chicken and add champagne.
Cook another 15 minutes until chicken is done and champagne reduced by half.
Remove chicken; keep warm.
Add cream to pan juices and cook until thickened.
Add sauteed mushrooms if desired.
Pour sauce over chicken.

title: hot cabbage slaw
directions: Put all in frying pan and cover and let cook for 2 hours or until all is soft.
You can use half fresh cabbage and 1 cup sauerkraut.
You can add smoked sausage.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix the sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan; stir in cold water.
Add 2 cups of the berries.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add the margarine, lemon rind and lemon juice and stir. You may taste to adjust to your liking for sweetness.
Put remaining 2 cups of berries in bottom of pie crust.
Cover with cooked blueberries.
Cool. Garnish with whipped topping.
Very good topped with fresh whipped cream! Contains 289 calories per serving.

title: steve's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together until moist.
Put mixture onto floured surface.
Roll it with rolling pin.
Cut out with biscuit cutter and put in greased pan.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix all together.
Bake a pie crust for 5 minutes. Pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand until firm.

title: sharon dillahunty's cornbread dressing
directions: Cook the onions and celery with the margarine until done but not brown.
Set aside.
(A black iron skillet works best!
Don't wash after cooking onions, just add cornmeal mixture and cook.) Mix the cornmeal mix, eggs, sage, garlic powder and seasoned salt, pepper and milk together.
Add the onion mixture to the cornbread mixture and cook at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done and brown.
Crumble bread and add enough broth to make a very, very thin mixture (will appear to be almost runny).
Bake at 325° until set and brown.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter both sides of the bread.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat the remaining ingredients together.
Pour over bread. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick taco salad
directions: In large skillet, prepare Rice-A-Roni as package directs.
Add browned ground beef, salsa and chili powder and continue cooking over low heat 3 to 4 minutes until heated through.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to cake package directions.
Blend margarine, sugar and syrup in a 2 x 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange pineapple slices on blended mixture and heat in oven for 15 minutes.
While heating, mix cake batter as directed.
Pour over heated ingredients and bake 45 to 55 minutes or until done.
Invert pan, let stand 1 minute and remove pan.

title: pizza appetizer
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, dried oregano, garlic powder and red pepper well.
Spread in bottom of 9-inch pan or quiche pan. Layer pizza sauce and toppings.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Add Mozzarella cheese and bake another 5 minutes.
Use Fritos to dip.

title: cheese ball
directions: Leave cheese on counter to get soft, while chopping meat and onions.
Chop meat and spread out on a dinner plate and set aside. Chop green part only of the green onions.
Put softened cheese into a bowl and add the onions and mix by hand.
Roll into 1 big ball and roll ball onto the meat until covered.
Chill.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda together in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and liquid drained from fruit cocktail.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in fruit.
Pour into layer baking sheet.
Mix the brown sugar and chopped nuts; sprinkle on top of cake.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: date bread
directions: Combine dates, boiling water and soda.
Set aside.
In bowl, combine sugar, eggs, salt and butter.
Alternate adding flour and date mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into an 8-inch square cake pan.
Make 3 craters in dry ingredients and put oil in one, vinegar in the other and vanilla in the last one.
Pour water over the top and, with a fork, mix until well blended and no dry ingredients are showing. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not remove from pan.
Cool on rack and frost with favorite frosting.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes about
1/4-inch	thick.	Place
aluminum foil in a baking pan.
(You
will need a sheet large enough to line the pan and fold over
the
top.)
Place a layer of potatoes; sprinkle with salt	and
pepper.
Layer
potatoes
with bacon, onion and cheese.
Place
another
layer of potatoes on top and cover with	remaining ingredients.	Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion in boiling water 5 to 10 minutes. Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots. Fold in drained squash and onions.
Combine stuffing mix with butter.
Place in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Save a little stuffing mix for topping.
Spoon squash mixture on stuffing mix.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet crisps
directions: Place flour in a medium bowl; make a well in center.
Add egg yolks; work with your fingertips until blended.
Add sour cream, vanilla, liquor or vinegar and salt.
Blend well.
On a lightly floured board, work mixture into a smooth dough.
Dough should have tiny air bubbles throughout.
Cover and refrigerate for later use.
For immediate use, on a lightly floured board, roll out dough to about 1/16-inch thick.
Slice into 1 1/2-inch wide strips.
Cut strips diagonally into 5-inch wide.
Cut 1-inch slits lengthwise in center of each strip.
Pull 1 end of strip back through slit so strip resembles a bow tie.
Repeat.
In large skillet, heat 1-inch vegetable shortening.
Fry to golden brown in less than one minute.
Drain on towels.
Let cool and dust with powdered sugar.
Serve at room temperature.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Add broccoli to pot 2 to 3 minutes before pasta is done.
Drain in colander, rinse under cold running water and drain well.
Put into large serving bowl; stir in dressing, then remaining ingredients and toss to mix and coat.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Pour in pie shell.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.
